ofound realization. Nothing is passive. Everything that exists, from a stone to a civilization, is actively participating in its own ongoing reconstruction. Existence is an act of relentless effort. And that connects directly to you, the listener, how you learn a new skill, how you reconstruct the memories of your childhood, how you build an understanding of your life. None of it is just passively storing facts on a biological hard drive. It's an act of process. You are performing an act of reconstructive repair every single second. You are actively building persistence fields in your own mind, fighting back against the noise, trying to find stable alignment with a chaotic world. You are, quite literally, a localized persistence attractor within the manifold of reality. Which brings me to one final lingering thought to leave you with. If affliction's math is right, if existence is merely persistent admissibility within a set of constraints, and reality is just whatever pushes back and refuses our reconstructions, what happens to our own identity as human beings when our technology begins to fundamentally alter those constraints? It is the existential question of the 21st century. I mean, as we develop advanced artificial intelligence capable of mapping multidimensional biological states, as we invent cellular repair mechanisms, as we build neural interfaces that can directly edit the traces of our memory... We aren't just making tools anymore. No. We are changing the underlying constraints of the universe. And if we change the constraints, we fundamentally change what is admissible. Are we about to reconstruct ourselves into an entirely new dimension of existence? It's very possible. Will the specific structural distinctions that make us human even remain recoverable a thousand years from now? Or will they shatter under the transformation of our own technology? It is something to seriously think about the next time you look at the coffee cup on your desk and assume it's just a solid, simple object. Absolutely. Thank you for joining us on this deep dive into the architecture of reality. It has been an absolute privilege to unpack this with you. Until next time, keep questioning the constraints.", "segments": [{"id": 0, "seek": 0, "start": 0.0, "end": 1.84, "text": " So, picture this.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 11, 3036, 341, 13, 50457], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 1, "seek": 0, "start": 2.16, "end": 9.4, "text": " Thousands of years ago, deep inside the Escarol Cave, that's in what is now Portugal human beings, painted on these rock walls.", "tokens": [50473, 40535, 295, 924, 2057, 11, 2452, 1854, 264, 2313, 6166, 401, 41100, 11, 300, 311, 294, 437, 307, 586, 23011, 1952, 8958, 11, 11797, 322, 613, 3727, 7920, 13, 50835], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 2, "seek": 0, "start": 9.48, "end": 11.48, "text": " Yeah, Paleolithic cave art.", "tokens": [50839, 865, 11, 50007, 42878, 11730, 1523, 13, 50939], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 3, "seek": 0, "start": 11.84, "end": 12.84, "text": " Incredible stuff.", "tokens": [50957, 35261, 1507, 13, 51007], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 4, "seek": 0, "start": 12.94, "end": 13.16, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51012, 1779, 13, 51023], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 5, "seek": 0, "start": 13.780000000000001, "end": 18.62, "text": " But today, obviously, the people who made that art are entirely gone.", "tokens": [51054, 583, 965, 11, 2745, 11, 264, 561, 567, 1027, 300, 1523, 366, 7696, 2780, 13, 51296], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 6, "seek": 0, "start": 19.080000000000002, "end": 23.14, "text": " I mean, their language, their culture, their daily struggles, just totally erased.", "tokens": [51319, 286, 914, 11, 641, 2856, 11, 641, 3713, 11, 641, 5212, 17592, 11, 445, 3879, 38359, 13, 51522], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 7, "seek": 0, "start": 23.240000000000002, "end": 24.44, "text": " Completely lost to time.", "tokens": [51527, 39978, 2731, 281, 565, 13, 51587], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 8, "seek": 0, "start": 24.54, "end": 24.86, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51592, 7587, 13, 51608], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20589919317336308, "compression_ratio": 1.50390625, "no_speech_prob": 6.983370045426929e-13}, {"id": 9, "seek": 2486, "start": 24.86, "end": 35.64, "text": " And even the physical pigment they use to paint the walls has, in a lot of places at least, been completely washed away or chemically altered by millennia of geological activity.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 754, 264, 4001, 31325, 436, 764, 281, 4225, 264, 7920, 575, 11, 294, 257, 688, 295, 3190, 412, 1935, 11, 668, 2584, 16300, 1314, 420, 4771, 984, 28783, 538, 21362, 654, 295, 1519, 4383, 5191, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 10, "seek": 2486, "start": 35.92, "end": 37.28, "text": " Just eroded into nothing.", "tokens": [50918, 1449, 1189, 12340, 666, 1825, 13, 50986], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 11, "seek": 2486, "start": 37.56, "end": 37.74, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51000, 865, 13, 51009], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 12, "seek": 2486, "start": 38.2, "end": 46.739999999999995, "text": " So, to a classical physicist, or really anyone operating under standard common sense, the original event and the physical objects associated with it are just destroyed, right?", "tokens": [51032, 407, 11, 281, 257, 13735, 42466, 11, 420, 534, 2878, 7447, 833, 3832, 2689, 2020, 11, 264, 3380, 2280, 293, 264, 4001, 6565, 6615, 365, 309, 366, 445, 8937, 11, 558, 30, 51459], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 13, "seek": 2486, "start": 46.86, "end": 47.8, "text": " Like erased by time.", "tokens": [51465, 1743, 38359, 538, 565, 13, 51512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 14, "seek": 2486, "start": 47.84, "end": 48.22, "text": " They're gone.", "tokens": [51514, 814, 434, 2780, 13, 51533], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 15, "seek": 2486, "start": 48.4, "end": 49.519999999999996, "text": " That's the classical assumption.", "tokens": [51542, 663, 311, 264, 13735, 15302, 13, 51598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 16, "seek": 2486, "start": 49.96, "end": 51.14, "text": " But here's the wild thing.", "tokens": [51620, 583, 510, 311, 264, 4868, 551, 13, 51679], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.09469989222339076, "compression_ratio": 1.6305084745762712, "no_speech_prob": 7.579605888242968e-13}, {"id": 17, "seek": 5114, "start": 51.14, "end": 56.7, "text": " A recent study actually scraped the calcite crust that formed like over where that art used to be.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 5162, 2979, 767, 13943, 3452, 264, 2104, 66, 642, 18156, 300, 8693, 411, 670, 689, 300, 1523, 1143, 281, 312, 13, 50643], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15333358840186997, "compression_ratio": 1.5747126436781609, "no_speech_prob": 1.466480365960865e-12}, {"id": 18, "seek": 5114, "start": 57.28, "end": 62.94, "text": " And from that crust, scientists reconstructed the ancient, degraded DNA of the painters themselves.", "tokens": [50672, 400, 490, 300, 18156, 11, 7708, 31499, 292, 264, 7832, 11, 24740, 292, 8272, 295, 264, 48643, 2969, 13, 50955], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15333358840186997, "compression_ratio": 1.5747126436781609, "no_speech_prob": 1.466480365960865e-12}, {"id": 19, "seek": 5114, "start": 63.16, "end": 63.5, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50966, 865, 13, 50983], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15333358840186997, "compression_ratio": 1.5747126436781609, "no_speech_prob": 1.466480365960865e-12}, {"id": 20, "seek": 5114, "start": 63.84, "end": 65.78, "text": " So, the physical paint didn't survive.", "tokens": [51000, 407, 11, 264, 4001, 4225, 994, 380, 7867, 13, 51097], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15333358840186997, "compression_ratio": 1.5747126436781609, "no_speech_prob": 1.466480365960865e-12}, {"id": 21, "seek": 5114, "start": 66.8, "end": 72.7, "text": " But a highly specific molecular, well, what we're going to call a distinction, actually did survive.", "tokens": [51148, 583, 257, 5405, 2685, 19046, 11, 731, 11, 437, 321, 434, 516, 281, 818, 257, 16844, 11, 767, 630, 7867, 13, 51443], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15333358840186997, "compression_ratio": 1.5747126436781609, "no_speech_prob": 1.466480365960865e-12}, {"id": 22, "seek": 5114, "start": 72.82, "end": 76.4, "text": " Which, you know, forces us to ask a rather uncomfortable question.", "tokens": [51449, 3013, 11, 291, 458, 11, 5874, 505, 281, 1029, 257, 2831, 10532, 1168, 13, 51628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15333358840186997, "compression_ratio": 1.5747126436781609, "no_speech_prob": 1.466480365960865e-12}, {"id": 23, "seek": 7640, "start": 76.4, "end": 86.44000000000001, "text": " If the original material is gone, but the structural information can still be pulled out of the rock tens of thousands of years later, what does it actually mean for something to exist over time?", "tokens": [50365, 759, 264, 3380, 2527, 307, 2780, 11, 457, 264, 15067, 1589, 393, 920, 312, 7373, 484, 295, 264, 3727, 10688, 295, 5383, 295, 924, 1780, 11, 437, 775, 309, 767, 914, 337, 746, 281, 2514, 670, 565, 30, 50867], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12607724189758301, "compression_ratio": 1.587360594795539, "no_speech_prob": 1.6875383469089345e-12}, {"id": 24, "seek": 7640, "start": 86.68, "end": 87.06, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50879, 7587, 13, 50898], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12607724189758301, "compression_ratio": 1.587360594795539, "no_speech_prob": 1.6875383469089345e-12}, {"id": 25, "seek": 7640, "start": 87.54, "end": 95.48, "text": " And today, we are looking at a framework that argues this cave art example isn't just like a neat archaeology trick.", "tokens": [50922, 400, 965, 11, 321, 366, 1237, 412, 257, 8388, 300, 38218, 341, 11730, 1523, 1365, 1943, 380, 445, 411, 257, 10654, 21894, 1793, 4282, 13, 51319], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12607724189758301, "compression_ratio": 1.587360594795539, "no_speech_prob": 1.6875383469089345e-12}, {"id": 26, "seek": 7640, "start": 95.68, "end": 99.42, "text": " It is literally the fundamental operating system of reality.", "tokens": [51329, 467, 307, 3736, 264, 8088, 7447, 1185, 295, 4103, 13, 51516], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12607724189758301, "compression_ratio": 1.587360594795539, "no_speech_prob": 1.6875383469089345e-12}, {"id": 27, "seek": 7640, "start": 99.54, "end": 101.10000000000001, "text": " It's a massive paradigm shift.", "tokens": [51522, 467, 311, 257, 5994, 24709, 5513, 13, 51600], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12607724189758301, "compression_ratio": 1.587360594795539, "no_speech_prob": 1.6875383469089345e-12}, {"id": 28, "seek": 7640, "start": 101.2, "end": 101.88000000000001, "text": " It really is.", "tokens": [51605, 467, 534, 307, 13, 51639], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12607724189758301, "compression_ratio": 1.587360594795539, "no_speech_prob": 1.6875383469089345e-12}, {"id": 29, "seek": 10188, "start": 101.88, "end": 103.53999999999999, "text": " So, welcome to the Deep Dive.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 11, 2928, 281, 264, 14895, 413, 488, 13, 50448], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 30, "seek": 10188, "start": 103.78, "end": 110.38, "text": " The source we are unpacking today is this incredibly dense June 2026 monograph by an author known as Flixion.", "tokens": [50460, 440, 4009, 321, 366, 26699, 278, 965, 307, 341, 6252, 18011, 6928, 945, 10880, 1108, 3108, 538, 364, 3793, 2570, 382, 3235, 970, 313, 13, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 31, "seek": 10188, "start": 110.61999999999999, "end": 116.3, "text": " It's titled Persistence Before Truth, Recoverable Distinction as the Condition of Reference, Explanation, and Knowledge.", "tokens": [50802, 467, 311, 19841, 14006, 468, 655, 4546, 20522, 11, 1300, 12516, 712, 9840, 12987, 382, 264, 21793, 849, 295, 1300, 5158, 11, 12514, 282, 399, 11, 293, 32906, 13, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 32, "seek": 10188, "start": 116.39999999999999, "end": 117.74, "text": " Rolls right off the tongue, right?", "tokens": [51091, 9926, 82, 558, 766, 264, 10601, 11, 558, 30, 51158], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 33, "seek": 10188, "start": 117.88, "end": 122.5, "text": " But our mission for this Deep Dive is to completely dismantle the way you think about the universe.", "tokens": [51165, 583, 527, 4447, 337, 341, 14895, 413, 488, 307, 281, 2584, 30506, 306, 264, 636, 291, 519, 466, 264, 6445, 13, 51396], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 34, "seek": 10188, "start": 122.6, "end": 123.56, "text": " We're taking the whole thing apart.", "tokens": [51401, 492, 434, 1940, 264, 1379, 551, 4936, 13, 51449], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 35, "seek": 10188, "start": 123.78, "end": 124.0, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51460, 865, 13, 51471], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11252001754376066, "compression_ratio": 1.5121107266435987, "no_speech_prob": 1.8683216865961194e-12}, {"id": 36, "seek": 12400, "start": 124.0, "end": 144.38, "text": " We are going to strip away the comforting illusion that reality is made of static, solid objects, and we're replacing it with a model where everything from human memory to biological evolution, even the fundamental geometry of space and time, is built entirely on something called recoverable distinctions.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 366, 516, 281, 12828, 1314, 264, 38439, 18854, 300, 4103, 307, 1027, 295, 13437, 11, 5100, 6565, 11, 293, 321, 434, 19139, 309, 365, 257, 2316, 689, 1203, 490, 1952, 4675, 281, 13910, 9303, 11, 754, 264, 8088, 18426, 295, 1901, 293, 565, 11, 307, 3094, 7696, 322, 746, 1219, 8114, 712, 1483, 49798, 13, 51384], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.066089928150177, "compression_ratio": 1.5376884422110553, "no_speech_prob": 1.3248580834832047e-12}, {"id": 37, "seek": 14438, "start": 144.38, "end": 148.18, "text": " It is an ambitious piece of literature, to say the least.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 364, 20239, 2522, 295, 10394, 11, 281, 584, 264, 1935, 13, 50555], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1356306504667475, "compression_ratio": 1.5204918032786885, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891267914261206e-12}, {"id": 38, "seek": 14438, "start": 148.42, "end": 153.84, "text": " I mean, Flixion is pulling from higher category theory, computational biology, thermodynamics, epistemology.", "tokens": [50567, 286, 914, 11, 3235, 970, 313, 307, 8407, 490, 2946, 7719, 5261, 11, 28270, 14956, 11, 8810, 35483, 11, 2388, 43958, 1793, 13, 50838], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1356306504667475, "compression_ratio": 1.5204918032786885, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891267914261206e-12}, {"id": 39, "seek": 14438, "start": 154.01999999999998, "end": 155.22, "text": " Just light reading for a Tuesday.", "tokens": [50847, 1449, 1442, 3760, 337, 257, 10017, 13, 50907], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1356306504667475, "compression_ratio": 1.5204918032786885, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891267914261206e-12}, {"id": 40, "seek": 14438, "start": 155.51999999999998, "end": 156.24, "text": " Right, exactly.", "tokens": [50922, 1779, 11, 2293, 13, 50958], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1356306504667475, "compression_ratio": 1.5204918032786885, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891267914261206e-12}, {"id": 41, "seek": 14438, "start": 156.51999999999998, "end": 162.04, "text": " But the core argument is that our entire scientific worldview has been built on a flawed premise.", "tokens": [50972, 583, 264, 4965, 6770, 307, 300, 527, 2302, 8134, 41141, 575, 668, 3094, 322, 257, 38823, 22045, 13, 51248], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1356306504667475, "compression_ratio": 1.5204918032786885, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891267914261206e-12}, {"id": 42, "seek": 14438, "start": 162.42, "end": 165.04, "text": " We have literally been looking at the universe backward.", "tokens": [51267, 492, 362, 3736, 668, 1237, 412, 264, 6445, 23897, 13, 51398], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1356306504667475, "compression_ratio": 1.5204918032786885, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891267914261206e-12}, {"id": 43, "seek": 16504, "start": 165.04, "end": 175.92, "text": " Okay, let's unpack this, because I promise you by the end of this conversation, we are going to take you on a journey from the chemical breakdown of ancient DNA all the way to the mathematical geometry of cause and effect.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 718, 311, 26699, 341, 11, 570, 286, 6228, 291, 538, 264, 917, 295, 341, 3761, 11, 321, 366, 516, 281, 747, 291, 322, 257, 4671, 490, 264, 7313, 18188, 295, 7832, 8272, 439, 264, 636, 281, 264, 18894, 18426, 295, 3082, 293, 1802, 13, 50909], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11530712672642299, "compression_ratio": 1.639240506329114, "no_speech_prob": 1.728188989483237e-12}, {"id": 44, "seek": 16504, "start": 176.0, "end": 176.62, "text": " It's quite a trip.", "tokens": [50913, 467, 311, 1596, 257, 4931, 13, 50944], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11530712672642299, "compression_ratio": 1.639240506329114, "no_speech_prob": 1.728188989483237e-12}, {"id": 45, "seek": 16504, "start": 176.92, "end": 183.06, "text": " And we are going to do it by focusing on the mechanics, like how this actually works, without burying you in academic jargon.", "tokens": [50959, 400, 321, 366, 516, 281, 360, 309, 538, 8416, 322, 264, 12939, 11, 411, 577, 341, 767, 1985, 11, 1553, 2779, 1840, 291, 294, 7778, 15181, 10660, 13, 51266], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11530712672642299, "compression_ratio": 1.639240506329114, "no_speech_prob": 1.728188989483237e-12}, {"id": 46, "seek": 16504, "start": 183.56, "end": 186.22, "text": " And I see you've already set the tone with your backdrop today.", "tokens": [51291, 400, 286, 536, 291, 600, 1217, 992, 264, 8027, 365, 428, 32697, 965, 13, 51424], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11530712672642299, "compression_ratio": 1.639240506329114, "no_speech_prob": 1.728188989483237e-12}, {"id": 47, "seek": 16504, "start": 186.57999999999998, "end": 188.62, "text": " I thought a visual aid would help ground us.", "tokens": [51442, 286, 1194, 257, 5056, 9418, 576, 854, 2727, 505, 13, 51544], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11530712672642299, "compression_ratio": 1.639240506329114, "no_speech_prob": 1.728188989483237e-12}, {"id": 48, "seek": 16504, "start": 189.01999999999998, "end": 191.57999999999998, "text": " So behind me is this dynamic abstraction.", "tokens": [51564, 407, 2261, 385, 307, 341, 8546, 37765, 13, 51692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11530712672642299, "compression_ratio": 1.639240506329114, "no_speech_prob": 1.728188989483237e-12}, {"id": 49, "seek": 19158, "start": 191.58, "end": 196.16000000000003, "text": " You'll notice it's mostly just shifting, chaotic geometry.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 603, 3449, 309, 311, 5240, 445, 17573, 11, 27013, 18426, 13, 50594], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 50, "seek": 19158, "start": 196.42000000000002, "end": 197.42000000000002, "text": " Lots of constant motion.", "tokens": [50607, 15908, 295, 5754, 5394, 13, 50657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 51, "seek": 19158, "start": 197.52, "end": 198.26000000000002, "text": " It looks like noise.", "tokens": [50662, 467, 1542, 411, 5658, 13, 50699], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 52, "seek": 19158, "start": 198.4, "end": 200.06, "text": " Constant noise and degradation, yeah.", "tokens": [50706, 37413, 5658, 293, 40519, 11, 1338, 13, 50789], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 53, "seek": 19158, "start": 200.74, "end": 208.88000000000002, "text": " But if you watch closely, certain patterns, like a geometric lattice or a spiral, they imperceptibly align.", "tokens": [50823, 583, 498, 291, 1159, 8185, 11, 1629, 8294, 11, 411, 257, 33246, 34011, 420, 257, 25165, 11, 436, 10100, 1336, 3545, 7975, 13, 51230], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 54, "seek": 19158, "start": 209.06, "end": 209.84, "text": " Oh, I see it.", "tokens": [51239, 876, 11, 286, 536, 309, 13, 51278], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 55, "seek": 19158, "start": 209.9, "end": 210.14000000000001, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51281, 1779, 13, 51293], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 56, "seek": 19158, "start": 210.42000000000002, "end": 215.9, "text": " They hold their shape for a fleeting moment against the chaos, and then they dissolve right back into the noise.", "tokens": [51307, 814, 1797, 641, 3909, 337, 257, 7025, 9880, 1623, 1970, 264, 14158, 11, 293, 550, 436, 30150, 558, 646, 666, 264, 5658, 13, 51581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15167715997979192, "compression_ratio": 1.5421686746987953, "no_speech_prob": 1.6947606512607294e-12}, {"id": 57, "seek": 21590, "start": 215.9, "end": 222.64000000000001, "text": " It's a visual representation of stability emerging from transformation rather than the other way around.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 257, 5056, 10290, 295, 11826, 14989, 490, 9887, 2831, 813, 264, 661, 636, 926, 13, 50702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13581641884737236, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.2992370851047652e-12}, {"id": 58, "seek": 21590, "start": 222.84, "end": 224.12, "text": " It's incredibly hypnotic.", "tokens": [50712, 467, 311, 6252, 42944, 299, 13, 50776], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13581641884737236, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.2992370851047652e-12}, {"id": 59, "seek": 21590, "start": 224.26, "end": 228.26, "text": " But it also gets right to the heart of why Fliction's paper is so disruptive.", "tokens": [50783, 583, 309, 611, 2170, 558, 281, 264, 1917, 295, 983, 3235, 4105, 311, 3035, 307, 370, 37865, 13, 50983], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13581641884737236, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.2992370851047652e-12}, {"id": 60, "seek": 21590, "start": 228.56, "end": 229.0, "text": " How so?", "tokens": [50998, 1012, 370, 30, 51020], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13581641884737236, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.2992370851047652e-12}, {"id": 61, "seek": 21590, "start": 229.44, "end": 237.62, "text": " Well, because to even begin to grasp this new framework, we have to look at the hidden assumption that underlies pretty much all of human thought.", "tokens": [51042, 1042, 11, 570, 281, 754, 1841, 281, 21743, 341, 777, 8388, 11, 321, 362, 281, 574, 412, 264, 7633, 15302, 300, 833, 24119, 1238, 709, 439, 295, 1952, 1194, 13, 51451], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13581641884737236, "compression_ratio": 1.5, "no_speech_prob": 1.2992370851047652e-12}, {"id": 62, "seek": 23762, "start": 237.62, "end": 244.52, "text": " Like when you look at a coffee cup on your desk, your brain instantly categorizes it as a static, stable thing, an object.", "tokens": [50365, 1743, 562, 291, 574, 412, 257, 4982, 4414, 322, 428, 10026, 11, 428, 3567, 13518, 19250, 5660, 309, 382, 257, 13437, 11, 8351, 551, 11, 364, 2657, 13, 50710], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 63, "seek": 23762, "start": 244.74, "end": 245.64000000000001, "text": " You don't even think about it.", "tokens": [50721, 509, 500, 380, 754, 519, 466, 309, 13, 50766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 64, "seek": 23762, "start": 245.68, "end": 246.62, "text": " Well, you just accept it.", "tokens": [50768, 1042, 11, 291, 445, 3241, 309, 13, 50815], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 65, "seek": 23762, "start": 246.8, "end": 250.5, "text": " And we've built all of our hard sciences on that exact same intuition.", "tokens": [50824, 400, 321, 600, 3094, 439, 295, 527, 1152, 17677, 322, 300, 1900, 912, 24002, 13, 51009], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 66, "seek": 23762, "start": 250.88, "end": 252.28, "text": " We really have.", "tokens": [51028, 492, 534, 362, 13, 51098], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 67, "seek": 23762, "start": 252.46, "end": 259.14, "text": " If you trace the history of intellectual disciplines, you find this massive, unquestioned bedrock.", "tokens": [51107, 759, 291, 13508, 264, 2503, 295, 12576, 21919, 11, 291, 915, 341, 5994, 11, 517, 20343, 37579, 2901, 17799, 13, 51441], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 68, "seek": 23762, "start": 259.52, "end": 261.6, "text": " I mean, physics begins with observables, right?", "tokens": [51460, 286, 914, 11, 10649, 7338, 365, 9951, 2965, 11, 558, 30, 51564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 69, "seek": 23762, "start": 261.72, "end": 262.7, "text": " About particles and fields.", "tokens": [51570, 7769, 10007, 293, 7909, 13, 51619], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237260966465391, "compression_ratio": 1.5473684210526315, "no_speech_prob": 1.56717076382068e-12}, {"id": 70, "seek": 26270, "start": 262.7, "end": 265.59999999999997, "text": " Yeah, particles, fields, bodies with mass.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 10007, 11, 7909, 11, 7510, 365, 2758, 13, 50510], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 71, "seek": 26270, "start": 266.3, "end": 270.78, "text": " Logic begins with propositions that are just assumed to hold their value over time.", "tokens": [50545, 49898, 7338, 365, 7532, 2451, 300, 366, 445, 15895, 281, 1797, 641, 2158, 670, 565, 13, 50769], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 72, "seek": 26270, "start": 270.88, "end": 272.03999999999996, "text": " Cudor science too, right?", "tokens": [50774, 383, 532, 284, 3497, 886, 11, 558, 30, 50832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 73, "seek": 26270, "start": 272.2, "end": 272.7, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50840, 7587, 13, 50865], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 74, "seek": 26270, "start": 273.21999999999997, "end": 277.36, "text": " It begins with discrete symbols, ones and zeros, defined states.", "tokens": [50891, 467, 7338, 365, 27706, 16944, 11, 2306, 293, 35193, 11, 7642, 4368, 13, 51098], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 75, "seek": 26270, "start": 277.84, "end": 285.38, "text": " Every single one of these fields assumes that there is an entity, an object, that is inherently stable enough to be studied.", "tokens": [51122, 2048, 2167, 472, 295, 613, 7909, 37808, 300, 456, 307, 364, 13977, 11, 364, 2657, 11, 300, 307, 27993, 8351, 1547, 281, 312, 9454, 13, 51499], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 76, "seek": 26270, "start": 285.59999999999997, "end": 288.44, "text": " They take identity as a primitive fundamental given.", "tokens": [51510, 814, 747, 6575, 382, 257, 28540, 8088, 2212, 13, 51652], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16632638796411378, "compression_ratio": 1.565891472868217, "no_speech_prob": 1.5428653363583344e-12}, {"id": 77, "seek": 28844, "start": 288.44, "end": 290.62, "text": " They assume the electron is an electron.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 6552, 264, 6084, 307, 364, 6084, 13, 50474], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 78, "seek": 28844, "start": 291.0, "end": 293.04, "text": " The variable X is the variable X.", "tokens": [50493, 440, 7006, 1783, 307, 264, 7006, 1783, 13, 50595], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 79, "seek": 28844, "start": 293.34, "end": 297.06, "text": " You establish the thing and then you write the equation to see how it moves or interacts.", "tokens": [50610, 509, 8327, 264, 551, 293, 550, 291, 2464, 264, 5367, 281, 536, 577, 309, 6067, 420, 43582, 13, 50796], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 80, "seek": 28844, "start": 297.21999999999997, "end": 302.56, "text": " But Fleshamian points out that assuming stability in this universe is a massive logical leap, like a huge one.", "tokens": [50804, 583, 479, 904, 4822, 952, 2793, 484, 300, 11926, 11826, 294, 341, 6445, 307, 257, 5994, 14978, 19438, 11, 411, 257, 2603, 472, 13, 51071], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 81, "seek": 28844, "start": 302.62, "end": 303.1, "text": " It is.", "tokens": [51074, 467, 307, 13, 51098], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 82, "seek": 28844, "start": 303.3, "end": 307.04, "text": " Because we live in a reality characterized by relentless, violent transformation.", "tokens": [51108, 1436, 321, 1621, 294, 257, 4103, 29361, 538, 46136, 11, 11867, 9887, 13, 51295], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 83, "seek": 28844, "start": 307.78, "end": 309.84, "text": " Everything is constantly boiling and shifting.", "tokens": [51332, 5471, 307, 6460, 16208, 293, 17573, 13, 51435], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 84, "seek": 28844, "start": 310.08, "end": 314.28, "text": " Yeah, thermodynamics basically tells us that physical systems decay toward entropy.", "tokens": [51447, 865, 11, 8810, 35483, 1936, 5112, 505, 300, 4001, 3652, 21039, 7361, 30867, 13, 51657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14566846864413371, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248929506259112e-12}, {"id": 85, "seek": 31428, "start": 314.28, "end": 314.9, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50396], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 86, "seek": 31428, "start": 315.46, "end": 318.71999999999997, "text": " Biology shows us organisms constantly mutating and dying.", "tokens": [50424, 48132, 3110, 505, 22110, 6460, 5839, 990, 293, 8639, 13, 50587], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 87, "seek": 31428, "start": 319.46, "end": 321.23999999999995, "text": " In neuroscience, memories degrade.", "tokens": [50624, 682, 42762, 11, 8495, 368, 8692, 13, 50713], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 88, "seek": 31428, "start": 321.96, "end": 325.64, "text": " In engineering, signals are corrupted by thermal noise.", "tokens": [50749, 682, 7043, 11, 12354, 366, 39480, 538, 15070, 5658, 13, 50933], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 89, "seek": 31428, "start": 325.97999999999996, "end": 328.65999999999997, "text": " So transformation is actually the default state of reality.", "tokens": [50950, 407, 9887, 307, 767, 264, 7576, 1785, 295, 4103, 13, 51084], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 90, "seek": 31428, "start": 328.82, "end": 330.46, "text": " Transformation is the only constant.", "tokens": [51092, 6531, 8663, 307, 264, 787, 5754, 13, 51174], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 91, "seek": 31428, "start": 330.82, "end": 333.5, "text": " So the miracle isn't that things change.", "tokens": [51192, 407, 264, 14660, 1943, 380, 300, 721, 1319, 13, 51326], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 92, "seek": 31428, "start": 333.65999999999997, "end": 338.35999999999996, "text": " The miracle is that anything manages to stay the same for even a millisecond.", "tokens": [51334, 440, 14660, 307, 300, 1340, 22489, 281, 1754, 264, 912, 337, 754, 257, 27940, 18882, 13, 51569], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 93, "seek": 31428, "start": 338.5, "end": 340.84, "text": " That is the core inversion of this whole text.", "tokens": [51576, 663, 307, 264, 4965, 43576, 295, 341, 1379, 2487, 13, 51693], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19478907443509244, "compression_ratio": 1.672, "no_speech_prob": 2.696587744765999e-12}, {"id": 94, "seek": 34084, "start": 340.84, "end": 346.56, "text": " First, Fliction argues we have to stop starting our physics and philosophy with objects and then asking how they change.", "tokens": [50365, 2386, 11, 3235, 4105, 38218, 321, 362, 281, 1590, 2891, 527, 10649, 293, 10675, 365, 6565, 293, 550, 3365, 577, 436, 1319, 13, 50651], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 95, "seek": 34084, "start": 346.79999999999995, "end": 347.53999999999996, "text": " We have to flip it.", "tokens": [50663, 492, 362, 281, 7929, 309, 13, 50700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 96, "seek": 34084, "start": 347.96, "end": 355.53999999999996, "text": " We must start with the relentless transformations, the noise, the decay, the entropy, and ask what, if anything, survives them.", "tokens": [50721, 492, 1633, 722, 365, 264, 46136, 34852, 11, 264, 5658, 11, 264, 21039, 11, 264, 30867, 11, 293, 1029, 437, 11, 498, 1340, 11, 46231, 552, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 97, "seek": 34084, "start": 355.64, "end": 358.2, "text": " So objects are not the building blocks of reality.", "tokens": [51105, 407, 6565, 366, 406, 264, 2390, 8474, 295, 4103, 13, 51233], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 98, "seek": 34084, "start": 358.38, "end": 358.94, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [51242, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 99, "seek": 34084, "start": 359.21999999999997, "end": 363.14, "text": " In this framework, an object is just a stable bundle of surviving distinctions.", "tokens": [51284, 682, 341, 8388, 11, 364, 2657, 307, 445, 257, 8351, 24438, 295, 24948, 1483, 49798, 13, 51480], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 100, "seek": 34084, "start": 363.76, "end": 367.34, "text": " Identity is something that has to be achieved, not something you just get for free.", "tokens": [51511, 25905, 507, 307, 746, 300, 575, 281, 312, 11042, 11, 406, 746, 291, 445, 483, 337, 1737, 13, 51690], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14018101692199708, "compression_ratio": 1.71875, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442412953375344e-12}, {"id": 101, "seek": 36734, "start": 367.34, "end": 371.35999999999996, "text": " Okay, I want to make sure we nail down exactly why this matters logically.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 286, 528, 281, 652, 988, 321, 10173, 760, 2293, 983, 341, 7001, 38887, 13, 50566], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 102, "seek": 36734, "start": 371.59999999999997, "end": 371.76, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50578, 865, 13, 50586], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 103, "seek": 36734, "start": 371.85999999999996, "end": 378.85999999999996, "text": " Because Fliction introduces a formal proof early on called Theorem 1.1, the necessity of recoverable distinction.", "tokens": [50591, 1436, 3235, 4105, 31472, 257, 9860, 8177, 2440, 322, 1219, 440, 37956, 502, 13, 16, 11, 264, 24217, 295, 8114, 712, 16844, 13, 50941], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 104, "seek": 36734, "start": 378.97999999999996, "end": 380.65999999999997, "text": " Yes, the foundational part of the monograph.", "tokens": [50947, 1079, 11, 264, 32195, 644, 295, 264, 1108, 3108, 13, 51031], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 105, "seek": 36734, "start": 380.94, "end": 385.32, "text": " And the argument here isn't just, you know, science is hard because things decay.", "tokens": [51045, 400, 264, 6770, 510, 1943, 380, 445, 11, 291, 458, 11, 3497, 307, 1152, 570, 721, 21039, 13, 51264], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 106, "seek": 36734, "start": 385.65999999999997, "end": 385.84, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51281, 865, 13, 51290], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 107, "seek": 36734, "start": 385.96, "end": 392.91999999999996, "text": " The argument is that if we don't start with what survives transformation, the very concept of knowledge implodes.", "tokens": [51296, 440, 6770, 307, 300, 498, 321, 500, 380, 722, 365, 437, 46231, 9887, 11, 264, 588, 3410, 295, 3601, 8484, 4789, 13, 51644], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 108, "seek": 36734, "start": 393.26, "end": 395.65999999999997, "text": " It's what philosophers call a transcendental argument.", "tokens": [51661, 467, 311, 437, 36839, 818, 257, 28535, 14533, 6770, 13, 51781], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12091427006997353, "compression_ratio": 1.6, "no_speech_prob": 1.897736958897389e-12}, {"id": 109, "seek": 39566, "start": 395.66, "end": 405.88000000000005, "text": " It looks at a phenomenon, in this case, human inquiry in science, and asks, what must absolutely be true about the universe for this to even be possible?", "tokens": [50365, 467, 1542, 412, 257, 14029, 11, 294, 341, 1389, 11, 1952, 25736, 294, 3497, 11, 293, 8962, 11, 437, 1633, 3122, 312, 2074, 466, 264, 6445, 337, 341, 281, 754, 312, 1944, 30, 50876], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1169531599004218, "compression_ratio": 1.582375478927203, "no_speech_prob": 1.4609853040900567e-12}, {"id": 110, "seek": 39566, "start": 406.08000000000004, "end": 406.26000000000005, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50886, 1779, 13, 50895], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1169531599004218, "compression_ratio": 1.582375478927203, "no_speech_prob": 1.4609853040900567e-12}, {"id": 111, "seek": 39566, "start": 406.34000000000003, "end": 408.08000000000004, "text": " Like, what are the prerequisites for logic?", "tokens": [50899, 1743, 11, 437, 366, 264, 38333, 15398, 3324, 337, 9952, 30, 50986], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1169531599004218, "compression_ratio": 1.582375478927203, "no_speech_prob": 1.4609853040900567e-12}, {"id": 112, "seek": 39566, "start": 408.34000000000003, "end": 408.84000000000003, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50999, 7587, 13, 51024], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1169531599004218, "compression_ratio": 1.582375478927203, "no_speech_prob": 1.4609853040900567e-12}, {"id": 113, "seek": 39566, "start": 409.3, "end": 421.52000000000004, "text": " And Fliction mathematically proves that if no distinction survives transformation-like, if absolutely every property is instantly wiped out by the chaotic noise of the universe, then reference fails.", "tokens": [51047, 400, 3235, 4105, 44003, 25019, 300, 498, 572, 16844, 46231, 9887, 12, 4092, 11, 498, 3122, 633, 4707, 307, 13518, 26879, 484, 538, 264, 27013, 5658, 295, 264, 6445, 11, 550, 6408, 18199, 13, 51658], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1169531599004218, "compression_ratio": 1.582375478927203, "no_speech_prob": 1.4609853040900567e-12}, {"id": 114, "seek": 42152, "start": 421.52, "end": 426.29999999999995, "text": " Meaning, you can't point to a thing and say, that is the same thing I pointed to yesterday.", "tokens": [50365, 19948, 11, 291, 393, 380, 935, 281, 257, 551, 293, 584, 11, 300, 307, 264, 912, 551, 286, 10932, 281, 5186, 13, 50604], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 115, "seek": 42152, "start": 426.4, "end": 427.0, "text": " You can't.", "tokens": [50609, 509, 393, 380, 13, 50639], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 116, "seek": 42152, "start": 427.06, "end": 430.62, "text": " Because all the structural data that made it that specific thing is just gone.", "tokens": [50642, 1436, 439, 264, 15067, 1412, 300, 1027, 309, 300, 2685, 551, 307, 445, 2780, 13, 50820], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 117, "seek": 42152, "start": 430.97999999999996, "end": 431.41999999999996, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [50838, 48746, 736, 13, 50860], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 118, "seek": 42152, "start": 431.79999999999995, "end": 434.79999999999995, "text": " And if reference fails, then comparison is logically impossible.", "tokens": [50879, 400, 498, 6408, 18199, 11, 550, 9660, 307, 38887, 6243, 13, 51029], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 119, "seek": 42152, "start": 435.09999999999997, "end": 439.4, "text": " You can't say, this star is hotter than that star, or this cell is older than that cell.", "tokens": [51044, 509, 393, 380, 584, 11, 341, 3543, 307, 32149, 813, 300, 3543, 11, 420, 341, 2815, 307, 4906, 813, 300, 2815, 13, 51259], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 120, "seek": 42152, "start": 439.47999999999996, "end": 441.41999999999996, "text": " And if you can't compare, you cannot measure.", "tokens": [51263, 400, 498, 291, 393, 380, 6794, 11, 291, 2644, 3481, 13, 51360], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10549343549288236, "compression_ratio": 1.757847533632287, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171615912705106e-12}, {"id": 121, "seek": 44142, "start": 441.42, "end": 441.98, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50393], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 122, "seek": 44142, "start": 442.46000000000004, "end": 444.62, "text": " If measurement fails, communication fails.", "tokens": [50417, 759, 13160, 18199, 11, 6101, 18199, 13, 50525], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 123, "seek": 44142, "start": 445.1, "end": 452.22, "text": " And if you can't communicate measurements, scientific explanation and the evaluation of truth completely collapse.", "tokens": [50549, 400, 498, 291, 393, 380, 7890, 15383, 11, 8134, 10835, 293, 264, 13344, 295, 3494, 2584, 15584, 13, 50905], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 124, "seek": 44142, "start": 453.14000000000004, "end": 453.62, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [50951, 3153, 13, 50975], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 125, "seek": 44142, "start": 454.18, "end": 455.84000000000003, "text": " So what does this all mean?", "tokens": [51003, 407, 437, 775, 341, 439, 914, 30, 51086], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 126, "seek": 44142, "start": 456.20000000000005, "end": 463.36, "text": " If I'm hearing you right, if the universe were purely chaotic transformation with zero persistence, we wouldn't just be confused.", "tokens": [51104, 759, 286, 478, 4763, 291, 558, 11, 498, 264, 6445, 645, 17491, 27013, 9887, 365, 4018, 37617, 11, 321, 2759, 380, 445, 312, 9019, 13, 51462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 127, "seek": 44142, "start": 463.92, "end": 465.1, "text": " No, it's worse than that.", "tokens": [51490, 883, 11, 309, 311, 5324, 813, 300, 13, 51549], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17959731606876148, "compression_ratio": 1.5482456140350878, "no_speech_prob": 1.3506983075409207e-12}, {"id": 128, "seek": 46510, "start": 465.1, "end": 468.52000000000004, "text": " We wouldn't even have the cognitive architecture to realize we were confused.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 2759, 380, 754, 362, 264, 15605, 9482, 281, 4325, 321, 645, 9019, 13, 50536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10559586611661044, "compression_ratio": 1.6195286195286196, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308596404417507e-12}, {"id": 129, "seek": 46510, "start": 468.8, "end": 473.0, "text": " The fact that we can talk about a coffee cup means something is actively fighting off the entropy.", "tokens": [50550, 440, 1186, 300, 321, 393, 751, 466, 257, 4982, 4414, 1355, 746, 307, 13022, 5237, 766, 264, 30867, 13, 50760], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10559586611661044, "compression_ratio": 1.6195286195286196, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308596404417507e-12}, {"id": 130, "seek": 46510, "start": 473.0, "end": 482.40000000000003, "text": " The ability to do science proves that certain structural differences, distinctions, can survive the transformations of time and space.", "tokens": [50760, 440, 3485, 281, 360, 3497, 25019, 300, 1629, 15067, 7300, 11, 1483, 49798, 11, 393, 7867, 264, 34852, 295, 565, 293, 1901, 13, 51230], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10559586611661044, "compression_ratio": 1.6195286195286196, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308596404417507e-12}, {"id": 131, "seek": 46510, "start": 483.06, "end": 488.44, "text": " Okay, but I'm still trying to wrap my head around an object being a bundle of surviving distinctions.", "tokens": [51263, 1033, 11, 457, 286, 478, 920, 1382, 281, 7019, 452, 1378, 926, 364, 2657, 885, 257, 24438, 295, 24948, 1483, 49798, 13, 51532], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10559586611661044, "compression_ratio": 1.6195286195286196, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308596404417507e-12}, {"id": 132, "seek": 46510, "start": 488.92, "end": 490.64000000000004, "text": " Let's use an analogy to ground this.", "tokens": [51556, 961, 311, 764, 364, 21663, 281, 2727, 341, 13, 51642], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10559586611661044, "compression_ratio": 1.6195286195286196, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308596404417507e-12}, {"id": 133, "seek": 46510, "start": 490.74, "end": 492.0, "text": " Sure. Analogies are good here.", "tokens": [51647, 4894, 13, 16128, 664, 530, 366, 665, 510, 13, 51710], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10559586611661044, "compression_ratio": 1.6195286195286196, "no_speech_prob": 1.5308596404417507e-12}, {"id": 134, "seek": 49200, "start": 492.0, "end": 495.18, "text": " In classical philosophy, there's the old ship of Theseus puzzle, right?", "tokens": [50365, 682, 13735, 10675, 11, 456, 311, 264, 1331, 5374, 295, 1981, 301, 12805, 11, 558, 30, 50524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 135, "seek": 49200, "start": 495.64, "end": 498.36, "text": " You replace every plank of wood on a ship over time.", "tokens": [50547, 509, 7406, 633, 27861, 295, 4576, 322, 257, 5374, 670, 565, 13, 50683], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 136, "seek": 49200, "start": 498.52, "end": 500.58, "text": " And philosophers argue whether it's the same ship.", "tokens": [50691, 400, 36839, 9695, 1968, 309, 311, 264, 912, 5374, 13, 50794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 137, "seek": 49200, "start": 500.66, "end": 502.2, "text": " The classic identity paradox.", "tokens": [50798, 440, 7230, 6575, 26221, 13, 50875], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 138, "seek": 49200, "start": 502.54, "end": 502.76, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50892, 1779, 13, 50903], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 139, "seek": 49200, "start": 502.88, "end": 507.32, "text": " But I think Fliction's model requires something way more dynamic than a wooden ship.", "tokens": [50909, 583, 286, 519, 3235, 4105, 311, 2316, 7029, 746, 636, 544, 8546, 813, 257, 14744, 5374, 13, 51131], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 140, "seek": 49200, "start": 507.58, "end": 508.34, "text": " Think about a hurricane.", "tokens": [51144, 6557, 466, 257, 27136, 13, 51182], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 141, "seek": 49200, "start": 508.46, "end": 509.26, "text": " Oh, that's a good one.", "tokens": [51188, 876, 11, 300, 311, 257, 665, 472, 13, 51228], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 142, "seek": 49200, "start": 509.54, "end": 510.62, "text": " We give a hurricane a name.", "tokens": [51242, 492, 976, 257, 27136, 257, 1315, 13, 51296], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 143, "seek": 49200, "start": 510.7, "end": 511.44, "text": " We track it on radar.", "tokens": [51300, 492, 2837, 309, 322, 16544, 13, 51337], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 144, "seek": 49200, "start": 511.7, "end": 513.66, "text": " We talk about it as a singular object.", "tokens": [51350, 492, 751, 466, 309, 382, 257, 20010, 2657, 13, 51448], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 145, "seek": 49200, "start": 514.74, "end": 521.8, "text": " But physically, a hurricane is just a temporary pattern of moving air, heat, and water vapor.", "tokens": [51502, 583, 9762, 11, 257, 27136, 307, 445, 257, 13413, 5102, 295, 2684, 1988, 11, 3738, 11, 293, 1281, 20358, 13, 51855], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14093866482586928, "compression_ratio": 1.6869009584664536, "no_speech_prob": 1.7147303542353054e-12}, {"id": 146, "seek": 52200, "start": 522.0, "end": 523.86, "text": " Constantly cycling through new matter.", "tokens": [50365, 8574, 3627, 22425, 807, 777, 1871, 13, 50458], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 147, "seek": 52200, "start": 524.1, "end": 524.46, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50470, 7587, 13, 50488], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 148, "seek": 52200, "start": 524.98, "end": 530.98, "text": " The actual water droplets that make up the storm on Monday are completely gone and replaced by new ocean water by Wednesday.", "tokens": [50514, 440, 3539, 1281, 41573, 300, 652, 493, 264, 7679, 322, 8138, 366, 2584, 2780, 293, 10772, 538, 777, 7810, 1281, 538, 10579, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 149, "seek": 52200, "start": 531.48, "end": 534.76, "text": " The hurricane has zero material continuity.", "tokens": [50839, 440, 27136, 575, 4018, 2527, 23807, 13, 51003], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 150, "seek": 52200, "start": 535.02, "end": 535.64, "text": " None whatsoever.", "tokens": [51016, 14492, 17076, 13, 51047], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 151, "seek": 52200, "start": 536.14, "end": 540.76, "text": " So if I look at Fliction's framework, it seems to imply that the hurricane's identity is entirely relative.", "tokens": [51072, 407, 498, 286, 574, 412, 3235, 4105, 311, 8388, 11, 309, 2544, 281, 33616, 300, 264, 27136, 311, 6575, 307, 7696, 4972, 13, 51303], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 152, "seek": 52200, "start": 541.14, "end": 545.0, "text": " It's only an object depending on what kind of transformation it's subjected to.", "tokens": [51322, 467, 311, 787, 364, 2657, 5413, 322, 437, 733, 295, 9887, 309, 311, 32153, 281, 13, 51515], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1927475290200145, "compression_ratio": 1.5592592592592593, "no_speech_prob": 1.2155011155576267e-12}, {"id": 153, "seek": 54500, "start": 545.0, "end": 549.5, "text": " What's fascinating here is that a hurricane is the perfect empirical model for this.", "tokens": [50365, 708, 311, 10343, 510, 307, 300, 257, 27136, 307, 264, 2176, 31886, 2316, 337, 341, 13, 50590], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 154, "seek": 54500, "start": 549.8, "end": 552.46, "text": " In classical thought, identity is absolute, right?", "tokens": [50605, 682, 13735, 1194, 11, 6575, 307, 8236, 11, 558, 30, 50738], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 155, "seek": 54500, "start": 552.54, "end": 553.58, "text": " A thing is what it is.", "tokens": [50742, 316, 551, 307, 437, 309, 307, 13, 50794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 156, "seek": 54500, "start": 553.64, "end": 554.5, "text": " A table is a table.", "tokens": [50797, 316, 3199, 307, 257, 3199, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 157, "seek": 54500, "start": 554.58, "end": 554.74, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50844, 1779, 13, 50852], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 158, "seek": 54500, "start": 555.1, "end": 561.94, "text": " But Fliction demonstrates mathematically that identity is deeply relative, specifically to a designated family of transformations.", "tokens": [50870, 583, 3235, 4105, 31034, 44003, 300, 6575, 307, 8760, 4972, 11, 4682, 281, 257, 21688, 1605, 295, 34852, 13, 51212], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 159, "seek": 54500, "start": 562.44, "end": 563.3, "text": " Let's look at your hurricane.", "tokens": [51237, 961, 311, 574, 412, 428, 27136, 13, 51280], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 160, "seek": 54500, "start": 563.5, "end": 563.7, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [51290, 1033, 13, 51300], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12966807135220232, "compression_ratio": 1.543859649122807, "no_speech_prob": 1.9051680805876048e-12}, {"id": 161, "seek": 56370, "start": 563.7, "end": 569.1, "text": " Its identity easily survives the transformation of, say, continuous water molecule replacement.", "tokens": [50365, 6953, 6575, 3612, 46231, 264, 9887, 295, 11, 584, 11, 10957, 1281, 15582, 14419, 13, 50635], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 162, "seek": 56370, "start": 569.26, "end": 570.0200000000001, "text": " Because they shape holes.", "tokens": [50643, 1436, 436, 3909, 8118, 13, 50681], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 163, "seek": 56370, "start": 570.26, "end": 570.44, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50693, 1079, 13, 50702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 164, "seek": 56370, "start": 570.7800000000001, "end": 574.34, "text": " It also survives the transformation of moving across the Atlantic Ocean.", "tokens": [50719, 467, 611, 46231, 264, 9887, 295, 2684, 2108, 264, 20233, 18101, 13, 50897], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 165, "seek": 56370, "start": 574.74, "end": 582.62, "text": " But if it hits land, and you subject it to the transformation of removing the thermal energy of the ocean, the pattern shatters.", "tokens": [50917, 583, 498, 309, 8664, 2117, 11, 293, 291, 3983, 309, 281, 264, 9887, 295, 12720, 264, 15070, 2281, 295, 264, 7810, 11, 264, 5102, 402, 37690, 13, 51311], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 166, "seek": 56370, "start": 582.84, "end": 584.12, "text": " It stops being a hurricane.", "tokens": [51322, 467, 10094, 885, 257, 27136, 13, 51386], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 167, "seek": 56370, "start": 584.36, "end": 585.38, "text": " It just becomes rain.", "tokens": [51398, 467, 445, 3643, 4830, 13, 51449], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 168, "seek": 56370, "start": 585.48, "end": 585.82, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51454, 1079, 13, 51471], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 169, "seek": 56370, "start": 586.22, "end": 590.34, "text": " The hurricane only has identity relative to the transformations it can actually survive.", "tokens": [51491, 440, 27136, 787, 575, 6575, 4972, 281, 264, 34852, 309, 393, 767, 7867, 13, 51697], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 170, "seek": 56370, "start": 591.24, "end": 592.76, "text": " Fliction applies this everywhere.", "tokens": [51742, 3235, 4105, 13165, 341, 5315, 13, 51818], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15019395433623214, "compression_ratio": 1.8602941176470589, "no_speech_prob": 1.957555645359932e-12}, {"id": 171, "seek": 59276, "start": 592.76, "end": 593.74, "text": " Like in biology.", "tokens": [50365, 1743, 294, 14956, 13, 50414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 172, "seek": 59276, "start": 594.12, "end": 594.4, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50433, 7587, 13, 50447], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 173, "seek": 59276, "start": 594.96, "end": 601.08, "text": " A biological species has a stable identity under the transformation of standard environmental fluctuations.", "tokens": [50475, 316, 13910, 6172, 575, 257, 8351, 6575, 833, 264, 9887, 295, 3832, 8303, 45276, 13, 50781], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 174, "seek": 59276, "start": 601.64, "end": 604.4, "text": " Like, a cold winter doesn't destroy the species.", "tokens": [50809, 1743, 11, 257, 3554, 6355, 1177, 380, 5293, 264, 6172, 13, 50947], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 175, "seek": 59276, "start": 604.68, "end": 604.86, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50961, 1779, 13, 50970], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 176, "seek": 59276, "start": 605.18, "end": 611.6, "text": " But it does not have a stable identity under the transformation of millions of years of evolutionary pressure.", "tokens": [50986, 583, 309, 775, 406, 362, 257, 8351, 6575, 833, 264, 9887, 295, 6803, 295, 924, 295, 27567, 3321, 13, 51307], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 177, "seek": 59276, "start": 611.96, "end": 613.92, "text": " Or what about legal stuff, like a contract?", "tokens": [51325, 1610, 437, 466, 5089, 1507, 11, 411, 257, 4364, 30, 51423], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 178, "seek": 59276, "start": 614.14, "end": 614.8199999999999, "text": " Perfect example.", "tokens": [51434, 10246, 1365, 13, 51468], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 179, "seek": 59276, "start": 615.16, "end": 620.52, "text": " A legal contract survives the transformation of being translated into another language, assuming you have a good translator.", "tokens": [51485, 316, 5089, 4364, 46231, 264, 9887, 295, 885, 16805, 666, 1071, 2856, 11, 11926, 291, 362, 257, 665, 35223, 13, 51753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 180, "seek": 59276, "start": 620.72, "end": 620.9399999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51763, 1779, 13, 51774], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 181, "seek": 59276, "start": 621.04, "end": 621.9399999999999, "text": " The meaning persists.", "tokens": [51779, 440, 3620, 868, 1751, 13, 51824], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15934212187416533, "compression_ratio": 1.8006993006993006, "no_speech_prob": 1.8980244893135323e-12}, {"id": 182, "seek": 62194, "start": 621.94, "end": 626.94, "text": " But it doesn't survive the transformation of a Supreme Court judge ruling it unconstitutional.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 309, 1177, 380, 7867, 264, 9887, 295, 257, 11032, 7873, 6995, 21437, 309, 517, 25279, 41859, 13, 50615], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1592368928212968, "compression_ratio": 1.446927374301676, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054618993763484e-12}, {"id": 183, "seek": 62194, "start": 627.84, "end": 629.5200000000001, "text": " It ceases to be a valid contract.", "tokens": [50660, 467, 1769, 1957, 281, 312, 257, 7363, 4364, 13, 50744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1592368928212968, "compression_ratio": 1.446927374301676, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054618993763484e-12}, {"id": 184, "seek": 62194, "start": 630.2, "end": 634.9000000000001, "text": " So the object literally doesn't exist until you define the forces trying to tear it apart.", "tokens": [50778, 407, 264, 2657, 3736, 1177, 380, 2514, 1826, 291, 6964, 264, 5874, 1382, 281, 12556, 309, 4936, 13, 51013], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1592368928212968, "compression_ratio": 1.446927374301676, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054618993763484e-12}, {"id": 185, "seek": 62194, "start": 635.0600000000001, "end": 636.08, "text": " You have to start with the destruction.", "tokens": [51021, 509, 362, 281, 722, 365, 264, 13563, 13, 51072], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1592368928212968, "compression_ratio": 1.446927374301676, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054618993763484e-12}, {"id": 186, "seek": 63608, "start": 636.08, "end": 637.96, "text": " We start with the destructive forces.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 722, 365, 264, 26960, 5874, 13, 50459], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28841400146484375, "compression_ratio": 1.4242424242424243, "no_speech_prob": 2.072087510254783e-12}, {"id": 187, "seek": 63608, "start": 638.62, "end": 642.22, "text": " And the thing is just whatever structural pattern refuses to die.", "tokens": [50492, 400, 264, 551, 307, 445, 2035, 15067, 5102, 33222, 281, 978, 13, 50672], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28841400146484375, "compression_ratio": 1.4242424242424243, "no_speech_prob": 2.072087510254783e-12}, {"id": 188, "seek": 63608, "start": 642.62, "end": 644.76, "text": " Which leads us to the most practical question, I think.", "tokens": [50692, 3013, 6689, 505, 281, 264, 881, 8496, 1168, 11, 286, 519, 13, 50799], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28841400146484375, "compression_ratio": 1.4242424242424243, "no_speech_prob": 2.072087510254783e-12}, {"id": 189, "seek": 63608, "start": 644.9000000000001, "end": 645.36, "text": " Which is?", "tokens": [50806, 3013, 307, 30, 50829], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28841400146484375, "compression_ratio": 1.4242424242424243, "no_speech_prob": 2.072087510254783e-12}, {"id": 190, "seek": 63608, "start": 645.6, "end": 648.98, "text": " How does anything actually survive this constant bombardment?", "tokens": [50841, 1012, 775, 1340, 767, 7867, 341, 5754, 42894, 518, 30, 51010], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28841400146484375, "compression_ratio": 1.4242424242424243, "no_speech_prob": 2.072087510254783e-12}, {"id": 191, "seek": 63608, "start": 649.36, "end": 649.82, "text": " Ah.", "tokens": [51029, 2438, 13, 51052], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.28841400146484375, "compression_ratio": 1.4242424242424243, "no_speech_prob": 2.072087510254783e-12}, {"id": 192, "seek": 64982, "start": 649.82, "end": 655.22, "text": " This is where we leave philosophy and get into the hard mechanics of persistence.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 307, 689, 321, 1856, 10675, 293, 483, 666, 264, 1152, 12939, 295, 37617, 13, 50635], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2203688761767219, "compression_ratio": 1.4848484848484849, "no_speech_prob": 2.150752232560338e-12}, {"id": 193, "seek": 64982, "start": 656.32, "end": 662.2600000000001, "text": " Classical science, especially fundamental physics, has a deep-seated obsession with invariance.", "tokens": [50690, 9471, 804, 3497, 11, 2318, 8088, 10649, 11, 575, 257, 2452, 12, 405, 770, 30521, 365, 33270, 719, 13, 50987], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2203688761767219, "compression_ratio": 1.4848484848484849, "no_speech_prob": 2.150752232560338e-12}, {"id": 194, "seek": 64982, "start": 662.6400000000001, "end": 666.4000000000001, "text": " Invariance being things staying exactly mathematically the same.", "tokens": [51006, 31124, 3504, 719, 885, 721, 7939, 2293, 44003, 264, 912, 13, 51194], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2203688761767219, "compression_ratio": 1.4848484848484849, "no_speech_prob": 2.150752232560338e-12}, {"id": 195, "seek": 64982, "start": 666.7800000000001, "end": 668.24, "text": " Like the laws of conservation.", "tokens": [51213, 1743, 264, 6064, 295, 16185, 13, 51286], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2203688761767219, "compression_ratio": 1.4848484848484849, "no_speech_prob": 2.150752232560338e-12}, {"id": 196, "seek": 64982, "start": 668.6400000000001, "end": 669.6600000000001, "text": " Energy is conserved.", "tokens": [51306, 14939, 307, 1014, 6913, 13, 51357], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2203688761767219, "compression_ratio": 1.4848484848484849, "no_speech_prob": 2.150752232560338e-12}, {"id": 197, "seek": 66966, "start": 669.66, "end": 670.14, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50365, 1779, 13, 50389], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2456348737080892, "compression_ratio": 1.1946902654867257, "no_speech_prob": 1.7830531972781727e-12}, {"id": 198, "seek": 66966, "start": 670.48, "end": 675.86, "text": " Another's theorem, conservation of momentum, symmetry, these all rely on invariant properties.", "tokens": [50406, 3996, 311, 20904, 11, 16185, 295, 11244, 11, 25440, 11, 613, 439, 10687, 322, 33270, 394, 7221, 13, 50675], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2456348737080892, "compression_ratio": 1.1946902654867257, "no_speech_prob": 1.7830531972781727e-12}, {"id": 199, "seek": 66966, "start": 676.0799999999999, "end": 677.3199999999999, "text": " Meaning they don't change at all.", "tokens": [50686, 19948, 436, 500, 380, 1319, 412, 439, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2456348737080892, "compression_ratio": 1.1946902654867257, "no_speech_prob": 1.7830531972781727e-12}, {"id": 200, "seek": 67732, "start": 677.32, "end": 682.58, "text": " An invariant property is one that a specific transformation leaves completely untouched.", "tokens": [50365, 1107, 33270, 394, 4707, 307, 472, 300, 257, 2685, 9887, 5510, 2584, 1701, 36740, 13, 50628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 201, "seek": 67732, "start": 683.0400000000001, "end": 686.88, "text": " The state before the transformation is absolutely identical to the state after.", "tokens": [50651, 440, 1785, 949, 264, 9887, 307, 3122, 14800, 281, 264, 1785, 934, 13, 50843], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 202, "seek": 67732, "start": 687.2, "end": 690.4000000000001, "text": " And classical thinking treats invariance as the gold standard of reality, right?", "tokens": [50859, 400, 13735, 1953, 19566, 33270, 719, 382, 264, 3821, 3832, 295, 4103, 11, 558, 30, 51019], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 203, "seek": 67732, "start": 690.5, "end": 690.8000000000001, "text": " It does.", "tokens": [51024, 467, 775, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 204, "seek": 67732, "start": 690.9200000000001, "end": 693.9200000000001, "text": " But Fliction looks at this and points out a devastating limitation.", "tokens": [51045, 583, 3235, 4105, 1542, 412, 341, 293, 2793, 484, 257, 21280, 27432, 13, 51195], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 205, "seek": 67732, "start": 694.62, "end": 701.1600000000001, "text": " In the empirical, messy world of biology, human history, and communication, exact invariance is basically a myth.", "tokens": [51230, 682, 264, 31886, 11, 16191, 1002, 295, 14956, 11, 1952, 2503, 11, 293, 6101, 11, 1900, 33270, 719, 307, 1936, 257, 9474, 13, 51557], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 206, "seek": 67732, "start": 701.32, "end": 702.08, "text": " Because of the noise.", "tokens": [51565, 1436, 295, 264, 5658, 13, 51603], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 207, "seek": 67732, "start": 702.1800000000001, "end": 702.7800000000001, "text": " Because of the noise.", "tokens": [51608, 1436, 295, 264, 5658, 13, 51638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 208, "seek": 67732, "start": 702.7800000000001, "end": 707.0600000000001, "text": " If I copy a file on a hard drive enough times, eventually a bit flips.", "tokens": [51638, 759, 286, 5055, 257, 3991, 322, 257, 1152, 3332, 1547, 1413, 11, 4728, 257, 857, 40249, 13, 51852], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1114473044872284, "compression_ratio": 1.7398119122257054, "no_speech_prob": 1.5920920181169973e-12}, {"id": 209, "seek": 70732, "start": 707.32, "end": 710.36, "text": " If a cell divides enough times, a mutation happens.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 257, 2815, 41347, 1547, 1413, 11, 257, 27960, 2314, 13, 50517], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 210, "seek": 70732, "start": 710.46, "end": 710.82, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50522, 7587, 13, 50540], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 211, "seek": 70732, "start": 711.1400000000001, "end": 718.1800000000001, "text": " If persistence required perfect invariance, we would have no biological inheritance, no institutional memory, and no historical records.", "tokens": [50556, 759, 37617, 4739, 2176, 33270, 719, 11, 321, 576, 362, 572, 13910, 32122, 11, 572, 18391, 4675, 11, 293, 572, 8584, 7724, 13, 50908], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 212, "seek": 70732, "start": 718.32, "end": 720.8000000000001, "text": " The universe would just be empty of complex structures.", "tokens": [50915, 440, 6445, 576, 445, 312, 6707, 295, 3997, 9227, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 213, "seek": 70732, "start": 721.08, "end": 726.96, "text": " So Fliction introduces a mathematical framework that encompasses invariance but goes much, much further.", "tokens": [51053, 407, 3235, 4105, 31472, 257, 18894, 8388, 300, 49866, 33270, 719, 457, 1709, 709, 11, 709, 3052, 13, 51347], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 214, "seek": 70732, "start": 727.32, "end": 731.0600000000001, "text": " It relies on structured domains consisting of four elements.", "tokens": [51365, 467, 30910, 322, 18519, 25514, 33921, 295, 1451, 4959, 13, 51552], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 215, "seek": 70732, "start": 731.1800000000001, "end": 731.96, "text": " Let's walk through them.", "tokens": [51558, 961, 311, 1792, 807, 552, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 216, "seek": 70732, "start": 732.12, "end": 732.58, "text": " Let's do it.", "tokens": [51605, 961, 311, 360, 309, 13, 51628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 217, "seek": 70732, "start": 732.7600000000001, "end": 735.1800000000001, "text": " First, you have X, the state space.", "tokens": [51637, 2386, 11, 291, 362, 1783, 11, 264, 1785, 1901, 13, 51758], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15225639343261718, "compression_ratio": 1.6111111111111112, "no_speech_prob": 1.817924391751824e-12}, {"id": 218, "seek": 73518, "start": 735.18, "end": 737.66, "text": " This is all the possible states your system can be in.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 307, 439, 264, 1944, 4368, 428, 1185, 393, 312, 294, 13, 50489], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 219, "seek": 73518, "start": 737.88, "end": 738.9799999999999, "text": " Okay, so X is the arena.", "tokens": [50500, 1033, 11, 370, 1783, 307, 264, 18451, 13, 50555], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 220, "seek": 73518, "start": 739.3599999999999, "end": 743.5, "text": " Second, you have T, a family of transformations acting on that space.", "tokens": [50574, 5736, 11, 291, 362, 314, 11, 257, 1605, 295, 34852, 6577, 322, 300, 1901, 13, 50781], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 221, "seek": 73518, "start": 744.12, "end": 747.16, "text": " The heat, the noise, the passage of time.", "tokens": [50812, 440, 3738, 11, 264, 5658, 11, 264, 11497, 295, 565, 13, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 222, "seek": 73518, "start": 747.28, "end": 748.1999999999999, "text": " The destructive forces.", "tokens": [50970, 440, 26960, 5874, 13, 51016], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 223, "seek": 73518, "start": 748.52, "end": 750.78, "text": " Third, you have D, a collection of distinctions.", "tokens": [51032, 12548, 11, 291, 362, 413, 11, 257, 5765, 295, 1483, 49798, 13, 51145], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 224, "seek": 73518, "start": 751.04, "end": 755.3199999999999, "text": " These are the specific differences or structural relationships you actually care about preserving.", "tokens": [51158, 1981, 366, 264, 2685, 7300, 420, 15067, 6159, 291, 767, 1127, 466, 33173, 13, 51372], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 225, "seek": 73518, "start": 755.54, "end": 755.8599999999999, "text": " Got it.", "tokens": [51383, 5803, 309, 13, 51399], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 226, "seek": 73518, "start": 756.0799999999999, "end": 759.26, "text": " And fourth, and this is the absolute key to the entire monograph.", "tokens": [51410, 400, 6409, 11, 293, 341, 307, 264, 8236, 2141, 281, 264, 2302, 1108, 3108, 13, 51569], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1667954628927666, "compression_ratio": 1.6185185185185185, "no_speech_prob": 1.5402427597233093e-12}, {"id": 227, "seek": 75926, "start": 759.26, "end": 763.14, "text": " You have R, a family of reconstruction operators.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 362, 497, 11, 257, 1605, 295, 31565, 19077, 13, 50559], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 228, "seek": 75926, "start": 763.4399999999999, "end": 764.2, "text": " Reconstruction operators.", "tokens": [50574, 1300, 25279, 3826, 19077, 13, 50612], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 229, "seek": 75926, "start": 764.38, "end": 766.4399999999999, "text": " This is the mechanism that replaces invariance.", "tokens": [50621, 639, 307, 264, 7513, 300, 46734, 33270, 719, 13, 50724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 230, "seek": 75926, "start": 766.8, "end": 767.22, "text": " It is.", "tokens": [50742, 467, 307, 13, 50763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 231, "seek": 75926, "start": 767.6, "end": 776.28, "text": " Fliction states that a distinction persists not if it stays perfectly untouched, but if it can be structurally reconstructed after the transformation has occurred.", "tokens": [50782, 3235, 4105, 4368, 300, 257, 16844, 868, 1751, 406, 498, 309, 10834, 6239, 1701, 36740, 11, 457, 498, 309, 393, 312, 6594, 6512, 31499, 292, 934, 264, 9887, 575, 11068, 13, 51216], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 232, "seek": 75926, "start": 776.52, "end": 778.24, "text": " Okay, let's ground this in the real world.", "tokens": [51228, 1033, 11, 718, 311, 2727, 341, 294, 264, 957, 1002, 13, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 233, "seek": 75926, "start": 778.58, "end": 783.4399999999999, "text": " Let's look at a mundane, everyday example before we scale back up to ancient caves and DNA.", "tokens": [51331, 961, 311, 574, 412, 257, 43497, 11, 7429, 1365, 949, 321, 4373, 646, 493, 281, 7832, 32288, 293, 8272, 13, 51574], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 234, "seek": 75926, "start": 783.6, "end": 784.1, "text": " Sounds good.", "tokens": [51582, 14576, 665, 13, 51607], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1498106522993608, "compression_ratio": 1.6431226765799256, "no_speech_prob": 1.2445901514251956e-12}, {"id": 235, "seek": 78410, "start": 784.1, "end": 790.86, "text": " Imagine you have a receipt from a business dinner in your pocket, and it accidentally goes through the washing machine.", "tokens": [50365, 11739, 291, 362, 257, 33882, 490, 257, 1606, 6148, 294, 428, 8963, 11, 293, 309, 15715, 1709, 807, 264, 13836, 3479, 13, 50703], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 236, "seek": 78410, "start": 791.0600000000001, "end": 792.36, "text": " Happens to the best of us.", "tokens": [50713, 7412, 694, 281, 264, 1151, 295, 505, 13, 50778], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 237, "seek": 78410, "start": 792.5, "end": 792.74, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50785, 1779, 13, 50797], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 238, "seek": 78410, "start": 793.0400000000001, "end": 797.08, "text": " When you pull it out, it's just a crumpled, water-damaged mess.", "tokens": [50812, 1133, 291, 2235, 309, 484, 11, 309, 311, 445, 257, 941, 449, 15551, 11, 1281, 12, 10170, 2980, 2082, 13, 51014], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 239, "seek": 78410, "start": 797.72, "end": 798.5600000000001, "text": " The ink is bleeding.", "tokens": [51046, 440, 11276, 307, 19312, 13, 51088], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 240, "seek": 78410, "start": 798.9200000000001, "end": 800.0400000000001, "text": " The paper is degraded.", "tokens": [51106, 440, 3035, 307, 24740, 292, 13, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 241, "seek": 78410, "start": 800.44, "end": 803.6800000000001, "text": " The physical invariance of that piece of paper is utterly destroyed.", "tokens": [51182, 440, 4001, 33270, 719, 295, 300, 2522, 295, 3035, 307, 30251, 8937, 13, 51344], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 242, "seek": 78410, "start": 803.9200000000001, "end": 806.58, "text": " It is not the same arrangement of atoms it was yesterday?", "tokens": [51356, 467, 307, 406, 264, 912, 17620, 295, 16871, 309, 390, 5186, 30, 51489], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 243, "seek": 78410, "start": 806.72, "end": 806.86, "text": " No.", "tokens": [51496, 883, 13, 51503], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 244, "seek": 78410, "start": 807.26, "end": 809.74, "text": " So classical invariance says the object is gone.", "tokens": [51523, 407, 13735, 33270, 719, 1619, 264, 2657, 307, 2780, 13, 51647], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 245, "seek": 78410, "start": 809.74, "end": 810.12, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51647, 1779, 13, 51666], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.143247680058555, "compression_ratio": 1.6115107913669064, "no_speech_prob": 1.586021136472382e-12}, {"id": 246, "seek": 81012, "start": 810.12, "end": 815.02, "text": " The initial state X has been subjected to a highly destructive transformation, T, the washing machine.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 5883, 1785, 1783, 575, 668, 32153, 281, 257, 5405, 26960, 9887, 11, 314, 11, 264, 13836, 3479, 13, 50610], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10985192192925347, "compression_ratio": 1.553648068669528, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856361362809324e-12}, {"id": 247, "seek": 81012, "start": 815.22, "end": 815.3, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50620, 865, 13, 50624], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10985192192925347, "compression_ratio": 1.553648068669528, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856361362809324e-12}, {"id": 248, "seek": 81012, "start": 815.36, "end": 817.8, "text": " The physical properties are irrevocably altered.", "tokens": [50627, 440, 4001, 7221, 366, 16014, 20836, 1188, 28783, 13, 50749], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10985192192925347, "compression_ratio": 1.553648068669528, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856361362809324e-12}, {"id": 249, "seek": 81012, "start": 818.26, "end": 828.48, "text": " But if you take that receipt, smooth it out on a table under a bright light, and use your eyes to trace the faint bleeding ink, you can still read the final total.", "tokens": [50772, 583, 498, 291, 747, 300, 33882, 11, 5508, 309, 484, 322, 257, 3199, 833, 257, 4730, 1442, 11, 293, 764, 428, 2575, 281, 13508, 264, 21104, 19312, 11276, 11, 291, 393, 920, 1401, 264, 2572, 3217, 13, 51283], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10985192192925347, "compression_ratio": 1.553648068669528, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856361362809324e-12}, {"id": 250, "seek": 81012, "start": 828.58, "end": 830.02, "text": " You can still extract the meaning.", "tokens": [51288, 509, 393, 920, 8947, 264, 3620, 13, 51360], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10985192192925347, "compression_ratio": 1.553648068669528, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856361362809324e-12}, {"id": 251, "seek": 81012, "start": 830.4, "end": 830.6, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51379, 865, 13, 51389], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10985192192925347, "compression_ratio": 1.553648068669528, "no_speech_prob": 1.5856361362809324e-12}, {"id": 252, "seek": 83060, "start": 830.6, "end": 832.16, "text": " You can see that you spent $45.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 393, 536, 300, 291, 4418, 1848, 8465, 13, 50443], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15042609326979695, "compression_ratio": 1.4874371859296482, "no_speech_prob": 2.0522296969444076e-12}, {"id": 253, "seek": 83060, "start": 832.96, "end": 841.36, "text": " The physical paper didn't survive in its original state, but the distinction, the mathematical difference between $45 and $46 did.", "tokens": [50483, 440, 4001, 3035, 994, 380, 7867, 294, 1080, 3380, 1785, 11, 457, 264, 16844, 11, 264, 18894, 2649, 1296, 1848, 8465, 293, 1848, 16169, 630, 13, 50903], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15042609326979695, "compression_ratio": 1.4874371859296482, "no_speech_prob": 2.0522296969444076e-12}, {"id": 254, "seek": 83060, "start": 841.6, "end": 848.74, "text": " Because your visual cortex and your understanding of numerical shapes acted as the reconstruction operator, R.", "tokens": [50915, 1436, 428, 5056, 33312, 293, 428, 3701, 295, 29054, 10854, 20359, 382, 264, 31565, 12973, 11, 497, 13, 51272], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15042609326979695, "compression_ratio": 1.4874371859296482, "no_speech_prob": 2.0522296969444076e-12}, {"id": 255, "seek": 83060, "start": 848.84, "end": 849.6, "text": " That was the operator.", "tokens": [51277, 663, 390, 264, 12973, 13, 51315], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15042609326979695, "compression_ratio": 1.4874371859296482, "no_speech_prob": 2.0522296969444076e-12}, {"id": 256, "seek": 84960, "start": 849.6, "end": 850.2, "text": " You were.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 645, 13, 50395], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 257, "seek": 84960, "start": 850.62, "end": 855.58, "text": " You performed computational work to recover the distinction from a highly degraded trace.", "tokens": [50416, 509, 10332, 28270, 589, 281, 8114, 264, 16844, 490, 257, 5405, 24740, 292, 13508, 13, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 258, "seek": 84960, "start": 856.5400000000001, "end": 864.6800000000001, "text": " Flexion uses this exact math to prove that invariance is just a lazy, hyper-restrictive, special case of recoverability.", "tokens": [50712, 29208, 313, 4960, 341, 1900, 5221, 281, 7081, 300, 33270, 719, 307, 445, 257, 14847, 11, 9848, 12, 4149, 3740, 488, 11, 2121, 1389, 295, 8114, 2310, 13, 51119], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 259, "seek": 84960, "start": 864.9, "end": 865.16, "text": " Wait.", "tokens": [51130, 3802, 13, 51143], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 260, "seek": 84960, "start": 865.3000000000001, "end": 866.74, "text": " Invariance is a special case.", "tokens": [51150, 31124, 3504, 719, 307, 257, 2121, 1389, 13, 51222], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 261, "seek": 84960, "start": 866.84, "end": 867.08, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51227, 1079, 13, 51239], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 262, "seek": 84960, "start": 867.32, "end": 872.62, "text": " Invariance is simply recoverability, where the reconstruction operator is the identity operator,", "tokens": [51251, 31124, 3504, 719, 307, 2935, 8114, 2310, 11, 689, 264, 31565, 12973, 307, 264, 6575, 12973, 11, 51516], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18014561998975145, "compression_ratio": 1.6728971962616823, "no_speech_prob": 1.6743882755992923e-12}, {"id": 263, "seek": 87262, "start": 872.62, "end": 879.44, "text": " meaning you have to exert zero computational effort to recover the distinction, because the transformation didn't change it at all.", "tokens": [50365, 3620, 291, 362, 281, 31941, 4018, 28270, 4630, 281, 8114, 264, 16844, 11, 570, 264, 9887, 994, 380, 1319, 309, 412, 439, 13, 50706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 264, "seek": 87262, "start": 879.72, "end": 880.0600000000001, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [50720, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 50737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 265, "seek": 87262, "start": 880.14, "end": 881.34, "text": " It's like a persistence freebie.", "tokens": [50741, 467, 311, 411, 257, 37617, 1737, 7392, 13, 50801], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 266, "seek": 87262, "start": 881.44, "end": 881.76, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50806, 7587, 13, 50822], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 267, "seek": 87262, "start": 881.94, "end": 884.02, "text": " But in the real world, you almost always have to pay a toll.", "tokens": [50831, 583, 294, 264, 957, 1002, 11, 291, 1920, 1009, 362, 281, 1689, 257, 16629, 13, 50935], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 268, "seek": 87262, "start": 884.1, "end": 885.92, "text": " You have to do the actual work of reconstruction.", "tokens": [50939, 509, 362, 281, 360, 264, 3539, 589, 295, 31565, 13, 51030], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 269, "seek": 87262, "start": 886.58, "end": 888.88, "text": " And that brings us right back to the cave painters in Portugal.", "tokens": [51063, 400, 300, 5607, 505, 558, 646, 281, 264, 11730, 48643, 294, 23011, 13, 51178], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 270, "seek": 87262, "start": 888.88, "end": 892.94, "text": " It's the exact same mathematics, just scaled over tens of thousands of years.", "tokens": [51178, 467, 311, 264, 1900, 912, 18666, 11, 445, 36039, 670, 10688, 295, 5383, 295, 924, 13, 51381], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 271, "seek": 87262, "start": 893.4, "end": 893.5, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51404, 1779, 13, 51409], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1514038454022324, "compression_ratio": 1.5971223021582734, "no_speech_prob": 1.8687826893598602e-12}, {"id": 272, "seek": 89350, "start": 893.5, "end": 906.06, "text": " Because the original painters, their physical bodies, the actual event of painting, all of it was subjected to the transformation of deep time, geological shifting, and chemical degradation.", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 264, 3380, 48643, 11, 641, 4001, 7510, 11, 264, 3539, 2280, 295, 5370, 11, 439, 295, 309, 390, 32153, 281, 264, 9887, 295, 2452, 565, 11, 1519, 4383, 17573, 11, 293, 7313, 40519, 13, 50993], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08831410748617989, "compression_ratio": 1.7411347517730495, "no_speech_prob": 1.4493942070842314e-12}, {"id": 273, "seek": 89350, "start": 906.38, "end": 909.86, "text": " And the paint itself, the physical invariance, was totally destroyed.", "tokens": [51009, 400, 264, 4225, 2564, 11, 264, 4001, 33270, 719, 11, 390, 3879, 8937, 13, 51183], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08831410748617989, "compression_ratio": 1.7411347517730495, "no_speech_prob": 1.4493942070842314e-12}, {"id": 274, "seek": 89350, "start": 910.06, "end": 911.96, "text": " But the researchers didn't look for invariance.", "tokens": [51193, 583, 264, 10309, 994, 380, 574, 337, 33270, 719, 13, 51288], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08831410748617989, "compression_ratio": 1.7411347517730495, "no_speech_prob": 1.4493942070842314e-12}, {"id": 275, "seek": 89350, "start": 912.24, "end": 913.96, "text": " They looked for recoverable distinctions.", "tokens": [51302, 814, 2956, 337, 8114, 712, 1483, 49798, 13, 51388], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08831410748617989, "compression_ratio": 1.7411347517730495, "no_speech_prob": 1.4493942070842314e-12}, {"id": 276, "seek": 89350, "start": 914.3, "end": 915.28, "text": " And they found them.", "tokens": [51405, 400, 436, 1352, 552, 13, 51454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08831410748617989, "compression_ratio": 1.7411347517730495, "no_speech_prob": 1.4493942070842314e-12}, {"id": 277, "seek": 89350, "start": 915.28, "end": 922.42, "text": " They found the human DNA from the sweat or breath of the painters had become embedded in the calcite crust on the wall.", "tokens": [51454, 814, 1352, 264, 1952, 8272, 490, 264, 11872, 420, 6045, 295, 264, 48643, 632, 1813, 16741, 294, 264, 2104, 66, 642, 18156, 322, 264, 2929, 13, 51811], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08831410748617989, "compression_ratio": 1.7411347517730495, "no_speech_prob": 1.4493942070842314e-12}, {"id": 278, "seek": 92242, "start": 922.42, "end": 925.3399999999999, "text": " Now, that DNA wasn't perfectly invariant either, right?", "tokens": [50365, 823, 11, 300, 8272, 2067, 380, 6239, 33270, 394, 2139, 11, 558, 30, 50511], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 279, "seek": 92242, "start": 925.4599999999999, "end": 926.8199999999999, "text": " No, it was heavily fragmented.", "tokens": [50517, 883, 11, 309, 390, 10950, 9241, 14684, 13, 50585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 280, "seek": 92242, "start": 927.4799999999999, "end": 934.28, "text": " It had specific patterns of chemical damage, like cytosine deamination, which actually proved it was ancient.", "tokens": [50618, 467, 632, 2685, 8294, 295, 7313, 4344, 11, 411, 40248, 329, 533, 368, 335, 2486, 11, 597, 767, 14617, 309, 390, 7832, 13, 50958], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 281, "seek": 92242, "start": 934.5, "end": 938.06, "text": " But modern genomic sequencing acted as a massive reconstruction operator.", "tokens": [50969, 583, 4363, 1049, 21401, 32693, 20359, 382, 257, 5994, 31565, 12973, 13, 51147], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 282, "seek": 92242, "start": 938.2199999999999, "end": 943.74, "text": " It took those fragmented traces, aligned them against known human reference genomes, and rebuilt the distinction.", "tokens": [51155, 467, 1890, 729, 9241, 14684, 26076, 11, 17962, 552, 1970, 2570, 1952, 6408, 1049, 18168, 11, 293, 38532, 264, 16844, 13, 51431], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 283, "seek": 92242, "start": 944.16, "end": 948.4, "text": " They could tell exactly which ancient hunter-gatherer clade those artists belonged to.", "tokens": [51452, 814, 727, 980, 2293, 597, 7832, 22970, 12, 70, 1172, 260, 596, 762, 729, 6910, 28611, 281, 13, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 284, "seek": 92242, "start": 948.76, "end": 949.86, "text": " The creators are dead.", "tokens": [51682, 440, 16039, 366, 3116, 13, 51737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 285, "seek": 92242, "start": 950.0999999999999, "end": 951.0999999999999, "text": " The event is over.", "tokens": [51749, 440, 2280, 307, 670, 13, 51799], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.08785414501903503, "compression_ratio": 1.6182965299684542, "no_speech_prob": 1.3724717976698608e-12}, {"id": 286, "seek": 95110, "start": 951.1, "end": 952.7, "text": " The physical medium is ruined.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4001, 6399, 307, 17013, 13, 50445], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 287, "seek": 95110, "start": 952.94, "end": 962.62, "text": " But the distinction, the specific genetic sequence that differentiated those humans from others survived because an admissible reconstruction procedure existed.", "tokens": [50457, 583, 264, 16844, 11, 264, 2685, 12462, 8310, 300, 27372, 770, 729, 6255, 490, 2357, 14433, 570, 364, 5910, 41073, 31565, 10747, 13135, 13, 50941], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 288, "seek": 95110, "start": 963.1800000000001, "end": 965.8000000000001, "text": " So existence over time is not about physical endurance.", "tokens": [50969, 407, 9123, 670, 565, 307, 406, 466, 4001, 30325, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 289, "seek": 95110, "start": 965.96, "end": 967.72, "text": " It is about reconstructive capacity.", "tokens": [51108, 467, 307, 466, 16891, 21673, 6042, 13, 51196], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 290, "seek": 95110, "start": 967.96, "end": 968.5, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51208, 7587, 13, 51235], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 291, "seek": 95110, "start": 968.64, "end": 972.1800000000001, "text": " But, you know, this immediately forces a massive question.", "tokens": [51242, 583, 11, 291, 458, 11, 341, 4258, 5874, 257, 5994, 1168, 13, 51419], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 292, "seek": 95110, "start": 972.32, "end": 972.48, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51426, 865, 13, 51434], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.23364586166188686, "compression_ratio": 1.5565217391304347, "no_speech_prob": 1.6750278464608415e-12}, {"id": 293, "seek": 97248, "start": 972.48, "end": 975.9, "text": " The universe inherently leans toward entropy.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 6445, 27993, 476, 599, 7361, 30867, 13, 50536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1887820423513219, "compression_ratio": 1.4974093264248705, "no_speech_prob": 2.1885566275914314e-12}, {"id": 294, "seek": 97248, "start": 976.76, "end": 977.8000000000001, "text": " Things want to break down.", "tokens": [50579, 9514, 528, 281, 1821, 760, 13, 50631], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1887820423513219, "compression_ratio": 1.4974093264248705, "no_speech_prob": 2.1885566275914314e-12}, {"id": 295, "seek": 97248, "start": 978.28, "end": 984.62, "text": " So if survival requires this active reconstruction, what is actually powering the reconstruction?", "tokens": [50655, 407, 498, 12559, 7029, 341, 4967, 31565, 11, 437, 307, 767, 1347, 278, 264, 31565, 30, 50972], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1887820423513219, "compression_ratio": 1.4974093264248705, "no_speech_prob": 2.1885566275914314e-12}, {"id": 296, "seek": 97248, "start": 984.9, "end": 986.3000000000001, "text": " Like, where does the energy come from?", "tokens": [50986, 1743, 11, 689, 775, 264, 2281, 808, 490, 30, 51056], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1887820423513219, "compression_ratio": 1.4974093264248705, "no_speech_prob": 2.1885566275914314e-12}, {"id": 297, "seek": 97248, "start": 986.32, "end": 986.46, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [51057, 865, 13, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1887820423513219, "compression_ratio": 1.4974093264248705, "no_speech_prob": 2.1885566275914314e-12}, {"id": 298, "seek": 97248, "start": 986.54, "end": 989.64, "text": " What is pushing back against the washing machine in the geological decay?", "tokens": [51068, 708, 307, 7380, 646, 1970, 264, 13836, 3479, 294, 264, 1519, 4383, 21039, 30, 51223], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1887820423513219, "compression_ratio": 1.4974093264248705, "no_speech_prob": 2.1885566275914314e-12}, {"id": 299, "seek": 98964, "start": 989.64, "end": 995.04, "text": " Affliction answers this by fundamentally redefining two concepts we think we already understand perfectly.", "tokens": [50365, 12840, 75, 4105, 6338, 341, 538, 17879, 38818, 1760, 732, 10392, 321, 519, 321, 1217, 1223, 6239, 13, 50635], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 300, "seek": 98964, "start": 995.6999999999999, "end": 996.98, "text": " Repair and memory.", "tokens": [50668, 3696, 1246, 293, 4675, 13, 50732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 301, "seek": 98964, "start": 997.4, "end": 997.62, "text": " Okay.", "tokens": [50753, 1033, 13, 50764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 302, "seek": 98964, "start": 997.84, "end": 998.6999999999999, "text": " Let's start with repair.", "tokens": [50775, 961, 311, 722, 365, 10535, 13, 50818], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 303, "seek": 98964, "start": 999.34, "end": 1001.72, "text": " Usually we think of repair as an afterthought, right?", "tokens": [50850, 11419, 321, 519, 295, 10535, 382, 364, 934, 43135, 11, 558, 30, 50969], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 304, "seek": 98964, "start": 1001.78, "end": 1003.12, "text": " Like an auxiliary intervention.", "tokens": [50972, 1743, 364, 43741, 13176, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 305, "seek": 98964, "start": 1003.42, "end": 1007.22, "text": " You drive your car, a belt snaps, and a mechanic comes in from the outside to fix it.", "tokens": [51054, 509, 3332, 428, 1032, 11, 257, 10750, 19206, 11, 293, 257, 23860, 1487, 294, 490, 264, 2380, 281, 3191, 309, 13, 51244], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 306, "seek": 98964, "start": 1007.28, "end": 1008.72, "text": " The car is the primary system.", "tokens": [51247, 440, 1032, 307, 264, 6194, 1185, 13, 51319], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 307, "seek": 98964, "start": 1008.84, "end": 1009.86, "text": " The repair is secondary.", "tokens": [51325, 440, 10535, 307, 11396, 13, 51376], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 308, "seek": 98964, "start": 1010.3199999999999, "end": 1010.52, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51399, 1779, 13, 51409], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 309, "seek": 98964, "start": 1010.64, "end": 1013.08, "text": " Repair is just what happens when the normal state fails.", "tokens": [51415, 3696, 1246, 307, 445, 437, 2314, 562, 264, 2710, 1785, 18199, 13, 51537], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1727587755988626, "compression_ratio": 1.5774647887323943, "no_speech_prob": 1.6684921673448816e-12}, {"id": 310, "seek": 101308, "start": 1013.08, "end": 1016.48, "text": " But in Fliction's framework, repair is constitutive.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 294, 3235, 4105, 311, 8388, 11, 10535, 307, 23079, 17254, 13, 50535], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 311, "seek": 101308, "start": 1016.96, "end": 1020.44, "text": " It is the primary fundamental force of existence.", "tokens": [50559, 467, 307, 264, 6194, 8088, 3464, 295, 9123, 13, 50733], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 312, "seek": 101308, "start": 1020.7, "end": 1020.84, "text": " Wait.", "tokens": [50746, 3802, 13, 50753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 313, "seek": 101308, "start": 1021.0400000000001, "end": 1022.2, "text": " The primary force?", "tokens": [50763, 440, 6194, 3464, 30, 50821], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 314, "seek": 101308, "start": 1022.3000000000001, "end": 1022.58, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50826, 1079, 13, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 315, "seek": 101308, "start": 1023.26, "end": 1026.32, "text": " A system isn't something that occasionally needs repair.", "tokens": [50874, 316, 1185, 1943, 380, 746, 300, 16895, 2203, 10535, 13, 51027], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 316, "seek": 101308, "start": 1026.9, "end": 1030.18, "text": " A system is a continuous process of repair.", "tokens": [51056, 316, 1185, 307, 257, 10957, 1399, 295, 10535, 13, 51220], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 317, "seek": 101308, "start": 1030.44, "end": 1031.18, "text": " Give me an example.", "tokens": [51233, 5303, 385, 364, 1365, 13, 51270], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 318, "seek": 101308, "start": 1031.56, "end": 1033.16, "text": " Biological homeostasis.", "tokens": [51289, 13007, 4383, 1280, 555, 26632, 13, 51369], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 319, "seek": 101308, "start": 1034.06, "end": 1036.8400000000001, "text": " Or the error-correcting codes in your computer's RAM.", "tokens": [51414, 1610, 264, 6713, 12, 19558, 2554, 278, 14211, 294, 428, 3820, 311, 14561, 13, 51553], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 320, "seek": 101308, "start": 1037.2, "end": 1042.4, "text": " Or the excision repair enzymes constantly fixing broken DNA strands in your body right now.", "tokens": [51571, 1610, 264, 1624, 1991, 10535, 29299, 6460, 19442, 5463, 8272, 29664, 294, 428, 1772, 558, 586, 13, 51831], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2312101397597999, "compression_ratio": 1.5842696629213484, "no_speech_prob": 1.8393600444838176e-12}, {"id": 321, "seek": 104240, "start": 1042.4, "end": 1045.02, "text": " These are active reconstruction operators.", "tokens": [50365, 1981, 366, 4967, 31565, 19077, 13, 50496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 322, "seek": 104240, "start": 1045.38, "end": 1047.14, "text": " So they are constantly fighting the decay.", "tokens": [50514, 407, 436, 366, 6460, 5237, 264, 21039, 13, 50602], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 323, "seek": 104240, "start": 1047.5800000000002, "end": 1052.52, "text": " Mathematically, a transformation pushes a distinction toward a region of lower recoverability.", "tokens": [50624, 15776, 40197, 11, 257, 9887, 21020, 257, 16844, 7361, 257, 4458, 295, 3126, 8114, 2310, 13, 50871], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 324, "seek": 104240, "start": 1053.0600000000002, "end": 1059.02, "text": " A repair operator exerts force to push that distinction back into a region of high recoverability.", "tokens": [50898, 316, 10535, 12973, 31941, 82, 3464, 281, 2944, 300, 16844, 646, 666, 257, 4458, 295, 1090, 8114, 2310, 13, 51196], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 325, "seek": 104240, "start": 1059.3000000000002, "end": 1060.2, "text": " It's like treading water.", "tokens": [51210, 467, 311, 411, 2192, 8166, 1281, 13, 51255], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 326, "seek": 104240, "start": 1060.5, "end": 1061.8600000000001, "text": " The baseline is just sinking.", "tokens": [51270, 440, 20518, 307, 445, 28148, 13, 51338], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 327, "seek": 104240, "start": 1062.0400000000002, "end": 1065.5, "text": " You only stay on the surface because you are actively, continuously swimming.", "tokens": [51347, 509, 787, 1754, 322, 264, 3753, 570, 291, 366, 13022, 11, 15684, 11989, 13, 51520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 328, "seek": 104240, "start": 1065.7800000000002, "end": 1067.0400000000002, "text": " That's a great way to picture it.", "tokens": [51534, 663, 311, 257, 869, 636, 281, 3036, 309, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 329, "seek": 104240, "start": 1067.14, "end": 1071.3600000000001, "text": " But to swim effectively, like to repair something, you have to know what it's supposed to look like in the first place.", "tokens": [51602, 583, 281, 7110, 8659, 11, 411, 281, 10535, 746, 11, 291, 362, 281, 458, 437, 309, 311, 3442, 281, 574, 411, 294, 264, 700, 1081, 13, 51813], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13909290401080182, "compression_ratio": 1.7608695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.4956233950966236e-12}, {"id": 330, "seek": 107136, "start": 1071.36, "end": 1073.1399999999999, "text": " And that's where memory comes in, right?", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 311, 689, 4675, 1487, 294, 11, 558, 30, 50454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 331, "seek": 107136, "start": 1073.4599999999998, "end": 1073.62, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50470, 1079, 13, 50478], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 332, "seek": 107136, "start": 1073.76, "end": 1076.26, "text": " And again, Flixirin just shreds our common sense definition.", "tokens": [50485, 400, 797, 11, 3235, 970, 347, 259, 445, 21567, 82, 527, 2689, 2020, 7123, 13, 50610], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 333, "seek": 107136, "start": 1076.6799999999998, "end": 1080.6599999999999, "text": " Because we intuitively think of memory like a digital hard drive.", "tokens": [50631, 1436, 321, 46506, 519, 295, 4675, 411, 257, 4562, 1152, 3332, 13, 50830], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 334, "seek": 107136, "start": 1081.02, "end": 1086.0, "text": " A passive storage bin where we save little video files of our past experiences.", "tokens": [50848, 316, 14975, 6725, 5171, 689, 321, 3155, 707, 960, 7098, 295, 527, 1791, 5235, 13, 51097], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 335, "seek": 107136, "start": 1086.1999999999998, "end": 1090.4199999999998, "text": " Which is a terrible, terrible metaphor for how the universe actually works.", "tokens": [51107, 3013, 307, 257, 6237, 11, 6237, 19157, 337, 577, 264, 6445, 767, 1985, 13, 51318], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 336, "seek": 107136, "start": 1091.04, "end": 1094.4599999999998, "text": " Flixirin defines memory entirely operationally.", "tokens": [51349, 3235, 970, 347, 259, 23122, 4675, 7696, 6916, 379, 13, 51520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 337, "seek": 107136, "start": 1094.6999999999998, "end": 1095.26, "text": " Meaning what?", "tokens": [51532, 19948, 437, 30, 51560], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1540701991379863, "compression_ratio": 1.5476190476190477, "no_speech_prob": 1.5674047346495024e-12}, {"id": 338, "seek": 109526, "start": 1095.26, "end": 1097.94, "text": " Memory is not a repository of representations.", "tokens": [50365, 38203, 307, 406, 257, 25841, 295, 33358, 13, 50499], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 339, "seek": 109526, "start": 1098.66, "end": 1102.5, "text": " Memory is information that constrains the reconstruction of the past.", "tokens": [50535, 38203, 307, 1589, 300, 11525, 1292, 264, 31565, 295, 264, 1791, 13, 50727], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 340, "seek": 109526, "start": 1102.9, "end": 1103.96, "text": " Constrains the reconstruction.", "tokens": [50747, 8574, 424, 1292, 264, 31565, 13, 50800], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 341, "seek": 109526, "start": 1104.3799999999999, "end": 1106.3799999999999, "text": " Okay, let's drill down into the mechanics of that.", "tokens": [50821, 1033, 11, 718, 311, 11392, 760, 666, 264, 12939, 295, 300, 13, 50921], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 342, "seek": 109526, "start": 1106.44, "end": 1109.8, "text": " Imagine a transformation completely obliterates a distinction.", "tokens": [50924, 11739, 257, 9887, 2584, 23740, 1681, 1024, 257, 16844, 13, 51092], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 343, "seek": 109526, "start": 1110.48, "end": 1115.7, "text": " Say, a document is burned to absolute ash and the ash just scattered in the wind.", "tokens": [51126, 6463, 11, 257, 4166, 307, 13490, 281, 8236, 12588, 293, 264, 12588, 445, 21986, 294, 264, 2468, 13, 51387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 344, "seek": 109526, "start": 1115.82, "end": 1116.26, "text": " Oligon.", "tokens": [51393, 422, 5073, 266, 13, 51415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.193360683529876, "compression_ratio": 1.6875, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980751878058586e-12}, {"id": 345, "seek": 111626, "start": 1116.26, "end": 1122.62, "text": " There are now infinitely many possible pasts that could have resulted in that exact scattering of ash.", "tokens": [50365, 821, 366, 586, 36227, 867, 1944, 1791, 82, 300, 727, 362, 18753, 294, 300, 1900, 42314, 295, 12588, 13, 50683], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 346, "seek": 111626, "start": 1122.96, "end": 1126.8, "text": " The document could have been a poem, a tax return, a drawing.", "tokens": [50700, 440, 4166, 727, 362, 668, 257, 13065, 11, 257, 3366, 2736, 11, 257, 6316, 13, 50892], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 347, "seek": 111626, "start": 1126.9, "end": 1129.82, "text": " Because there are infinite possibilities, reconstruction is impossible.", "tokens": [50897, 1436, 456, 366, 13785, 12178, 11, 31565, 307, 6243, 13, 51043], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 348, "seek": 111626, "start": 1130.22, "end": 1131.12, "text": " There's too much ambiguity.", "tokens": [51063, 821, 311, 886, 709, 46519, 13, 51108], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 349, "seek": 111626, "start": 1131.26, "end": 1134.24, "text": " You can't rebuild it because you don't know which direction to build toward.", "tokens": [51115, 509, 393, 380, 16877, 309, 570, 291, 500, 380, 458, 597, 3513, 281, 1322, 7361, 13, 51264], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 350, "seek": 111626, "start": 1134.32, "end": 1134.7, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51268, 7587, 13, 51287], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 351, "seek": 111626, "start": 1134.8799999999999, "end": 1138.94, "text": " So memory provides the traces that restrict that infinite space of possibilities.", "tokens": [51296, 407, 4675, 6417, 264, 26076, 300, 7694, 300, 13785, 1901, 295, 12178, 13, 51499], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 352, "seek": 111626, "start": 1139.24, "end": 1140.9, "text": " It cuts down the ambiguity.", "tokens": [51514, 467, 9992, 760, 264, 46519, 13, 51597], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 353, "seek": 111626, "start": 1141.1, "end": 1141.48, "text": " Oh, I see.", "tokens": [51607, 876, 11, 286, 536, 13, 51626], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11676360028130668, "compression_ratio": 1.6821428571428572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5370884903428972e-12}, {"id": 354, "seek": 114148, "start": 1141.48, "end": 1143.1, "text": " A fossil is a memory.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 18737, 307, 257, 4675, 13, 50446], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 355, "seek": 114148, "start": 1143.68, "end": 1145.54, "text": " A scar on your arm is a memory.", "tokens": [50475, 316, 10569, 322, 428, 3726, 307, 257, 4675, 13, 50568], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 356, "seek": 114148, "start": 1146.08, "end": 1148.84, "text": " The architectural layout of an old city is a memory.", "tokens": [50595, 440, 26621, 13333, 295, 364, 1331, 2307, 307, 257, 4675, 13, 50733], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 357, "seek": 114148, "start": 1149.3, "end": 1153.84, "text": " They are structural residues of previous states that constrain the possibilities,", "tokens": [50756, 814, 366, 15067, 13141, 1247, 295, 3894, 4368, 300, 1817, 7146, 264, 12178, 11, 50983], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 358, "seek": 114148, "start": 1154.38, "end": 1159.02, "text": " allowing repair mechanisms to successfully rebuild a lost distinction.", "tokens": [51010, 8293, 10535, 15902, 281, 10727, 16877, 257, 2731, 16844, 13, 51242], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 359, "seek": 114148, "start": 1159.3600000000001, "end": 1159.88, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [51259, 48746, 736, 13, 51285], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 360, "seek": 114148, "start": 1160.1, "end": 1164.58, "text": " And this leads to this wild concept in the text called historical computation.", "tokens": [51296, 400, 341, 6689, 281, 341, 4868, 3410, 294, 264, 2487, 1219, 8584, 24903, 13, 51520], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 361, "seek": 114148, "start": 1165.16, "end": 1168.14, "text": " The idea that history isn't just a list of stuff that happened.", "tokens": [51549, 440, 1558, 300, 2503, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 1329, 295, 1507, 300, 2011, 13, 51698], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 362, "seek": 114148, "start": 1168.64, "end": 1170.28, "text": " History is a computational substrate.", "tokens": [51723, 12486, 307, 257, 28270, 27585, 13, 51805], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 363, "seek": 114148, "start": 1170.6, "end": 1170.9, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51821, 1079, 13, 51836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1907076964507232, "compression_ratio": 1.7207547169811321, "no_speech_prob": 2.083786268536336e-12}, {"id": 364, "seek": 117090, "start": 1170.9, "end": 1175.3600000000001, "text": " Like, the past is actively doing mathematical work to make the present understandable.", "tokens": [50365, 1743, 11, 264, 1791, 307, 13022, 884, 18894, 589, 281, 652, 264, 1974, 25648, 13, 50588], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 365, "seek": 117090, "start": 1175.9, "end": 1178.66, "text": " In traditional computer science, everything is state-based, right?", "tokens": [50615, 682, 5164, 3820, 3497, 11, 1203, 307, 1785, 12, 6032, 11, 558, 30, 50753], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 366, "seek": 117090, "start": 1179.0800000000002, "end": 1183.8600000000001, "text": " A computer looks at its current state, applies an algorithm, and moves to the next state.", "tokens": [50774, 316, 3820, 1542, 412, 1080, 2190, 1785, 11, 13165, 364, 9284, 11, 293, 6067, 281, 264, 958, 1785, 13, 51013], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 367, "seek": 117090, "start": 1184.0400000000002, "end": 1185.38, "text": " It doesn't need to know how it got there.", "tokens": [51022, 467, 1177, 380, 643, 281, 458, 577, 309, 658, 456, 13, 51089], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 368, "seek": 117090, "start": 1185.42, "end": 1185.7800000000002, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51091, 7587, 13, 51109], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 369, "seek": 117090, "start": 1186.42, "end": 1190.2, "text": " A chess program doesn't care about the sequence of moves that led to the current board arrangement.", "tokens": [51141, 316, 24122, 1461, 1177, 380, 1127, 466, 264, 8310, 295, 6067, 300, 4684, 281, 264, 2190, 3150, 17620, 13, 51330], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 370, "seek": 117090, "start": 1190.38, "end": 1191.92, "text": " It only calculates from the current board.", "tokens": [51339, 467, 787, 4322, 1024, 490, 264, 2190, 3150, 13, 51416], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 371, "seek": 117090, "start": 1192.16, "end": 1199.3000000000002, "text": " But in biology and epistemology, the sequence, the trajectory, is the only way to reconstruct the truth.", "tokens": [51428, 583, 294, 14956, 293, 2388, 43958, 1793, 11, 264, 8310, 11, 264, 21512, 11, 307, 264, 787, 636, 281, 31499, 264, 3494, 13, 51785], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11425370208976805, "compression_ratio": 1.731629392971246, "no_speech_prob": 1.7082687261277263e-12}, {"id": 372, "seek": 119930, "start": 1199.3, "end": 1203.08, "text": " There's a specific paper, Flixion Cites, to prove this.", "tokens": [50365, 821, 311, 257, 2685, 3035, 11, 3235, 970, 313, 383, 3324, 11, 281, 7081, 341, 13, 50554], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659229006086077, "compression_ratio": 1.3206521739130435, "no_speech_prob": 1.6423776401375267e-12}, {"id": 373, "seek": 119930, "start": 1203.44, "end": 1210.1599999999999, "text": " A 2026 study by Wang, he, and Hu on something called multimodal lineage tracing.", "tokens": [50572, 316, 945, 10880, 2979, 538, 14499, 11, 415, 11, 293, 11874, 322, 746, 1219, 32972, 378, 304, 38257, 25262, 13, 50908], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659229006086077, "compression_ratio": 1.3206521739130435, "no_speech_prob": 1.6423776401375267e-12}, {"id": 374, "seek": 119930, "start": 1210.84, "end": 1214.08, "text": " Let's spend a minute on how this actually works because I found it mind-blowing.", "tokens": [50942, 961, 311, 3496, 257, 3456, 322, 577, 341, 767, 1985, 570, 286, 1352, 309, 1575, 12, 43788, 13, 51104], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659229006086077, "compression_ratio": 1.3206521739130435, "no_speech_prob": 1.6423776401375267e-12}, {"id": 375, "seek": 119930, "start": 1214.1599999999999, "end": 1215.2, "text": " It's a brilliant example.", "tokens": [51108, 467, 311, 257, 10248, 1365, 13, 51160], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659229006086077, "compression_ratio": 1.3206521739130435, "no_speech_prob": 1.6423776401375267e-12}, {"id": 376, "seek": 121520, "start": 1215.2, "end": 1218.98, "text": " So, in computational biology, scientists want to understand development.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 11, 294, 28270, 14956, 11, 7708, 528, 281, 1223, 3250, 13, 50554], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16875712076822916, "compression_ratio": 1.3785714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.875639834419962e-12}, {"id": 377, "seek": 121520, "start": 1219.48, "end": 1225.6000000000001, "text": " They want to know how a single stem cell divides and differentiates into a skin cell, a neuron, and a heart cell.", "tokens": [50579, 814, 528, 281, 458, 577, 257, 2167, 12312, 2815, 41347, 293, 27372, 1024, 666, 257, 3178, 2815, 11, 257, 34090, 11, 293, 257, 1917, 2815, 13, 50885], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16875712076822916, "compression_ratio": 1.3785714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.875639834419962e-12}, {"id": 378, "seek": 121520, "start": 1225.72, "end": 1225.98, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50891, 1779, 13, 50904], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16875712076822916, "compression_ratio": 1.3785714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.875639834419962e-12}, {"id": 379, "seek": 122598, "start": 1225.98, "end": 1228.26, "text": " But they have a massive physics problem.", "tokens": [50365, 583, 436, 362, 257, 5994, 10649, 1154, 13, 50479], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 380, "seek": 122598, "start": 1228.68, "end": 1229.82, "text": " They do not have a time machine.", "tokens": [50500, 814, 360, 406, 362, 257, 565, 3479, 13, 50557], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 381, "seek": 122598, "start": 1230.48, "end": 1238.38, "text": " They cannot record the molecular state of a cell, let it divide, and then record it again because the act of sequencing a cell destroys it.", "tokens": [50590, 814, 2644, 2136, 264, 19046, 1785, 295, 257, 2815, 11, 718, 309, 9845, 11, 293, 550, 2136, 309, 797, 570, 264, 605, 295, 32693, 257, 2815, 36714, 309, 13, 50985], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 382, "seek": 122598, "start": 1238.54, "end": 1242.76, "text": " The historical states, the ancestral cells, are physically annihilated.", "tokens": [50993, 440, 8584, 4368, 11, 264, 40049, 5438, 11, 366, 9762, 40430, 45678, 13, 51204], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 383, "seek": 122598, "start": 1243.16, "end": 1246.6, "text": " They are transformed out of existence by the very process of development.", "tokens": [51224, 814, 366, 16894, 484, 295, 9123, 538, 264, 588, 1399, 295, 3250, 13, 51396], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 384, "seek": 122598, "start": 1246.7, "end": 1248.66, "text": " So, all the scientists have are terminal states.", "tokens": [51401, 407, 11, 439, 264, 7708, 362, 366, 14709, 4368, 13, 51499], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 385, "seek": 122598, "start": 1248.76, "end": 1252.6, "text": " They just have a massive pile of current, present-day descendant cells.", "tokens": [51504, 814, 445, 362, 257, 5994, 14375, 295, 2190, 11, 1974, 12, 810, 16333, 394, 5438, 13, 51696], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 386, "seek": 122598, "start": 1252.72, "end": 1253.54, "text": " It's just the endpoints.", "tokens": [51702, 467, 311, 445, 264, 917, 20552, 13, 51743], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10767365283653384, "compression_ratio": 1.8035714285714286, "no_speech_prob": 1.6171620249513796e-12}, {"id": 387, "seek": 125354, "start": 1253.54, "end": 1261.32, "text": " Yeah, and they take these cells and use single-cell RNA sequencing to get a high-dimensional snapshot of what genes are turned on in each cell right now.", "tokens": [50365, 865, 11, 293, 436, 747, 613, 5438, 293, 764, 2167, 12, 4164, 22484, 32693, 281, 483, 257, 1090, 12, 18759, 30163, 295, 437, 14424, 366, 3574, 322, 294, 1184, 2815, 558, 586, 13, 50754], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12673631420841924, "compression_ratio": 1.6423076923076922, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491460111233257e-12}, {"id": 388, "seek": 125354, "start": 1261.76, "end": 1262.62, "text": " But they need the history.", "tokens": [50776, 583, 436, 643, 264, 2503, 13, 50819], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12673631420841924, "compression_ratio": 1.6423076923076922, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491460111233257e-12}, {"id": 389, "seek": 125354, "start": 1262.74, "end": 1262.8799999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50825, 1779, 13, 50832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12673631420841924, "compression_ratio": 1.6423076923076922, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491460111233257e-12}, {"id": 390, "seek": 125354, "start": 1262.94, "end": 1263.5, "text": " They need the tree.", "tokens": [50835, 814, 643, 264, 4230, 13, 50863], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12673631420841924, "compression_ratio": 1.6423076923076922, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491460111233257e-12}, {"id": 391, "seek": 125354, "start": 1263.84, "end": 1266.68, "text": " So, they use computational models, like one called TreeVe.", "tokens": [50880, 407, 11, 436, 764, 28270, 5245, 11, 411, 472, 1219, 22291, 53, 68, 13, 51022], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12673631420841924, "compression_ratio": 1.6423076923076922, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491460111233257e-12}, {"id": 392, "seek": 125354, "start": 1266.8999999999999, "end": 1276.54, "text": " And what TreeVe does is it looks at the tiny surviving distinctions in the RNA of the present-day cells, and it mathematically infers the historical trajectory.", "tokens": [51033, 400, 437, 22291, 53, 68, 775, 307, 309, 1542, 412, 264, 5870, 24948, 1483, 49798, 294, 264, 22484, 295, 264, 1974, 12, 810, 5438, 11, 293, 309, 44003, 1536, 433, 264, 8584, 21512, 13, 51515], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12673631420841924, "compression_ratio": 1.6423076923076922, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491460111233257e-12}, {"id": 393, "seek": 127654, "start": 1276.54, "end": 1283.62, "text": " It reconstructs the family tree of cell divisions that must have occurred to produce these specific terminal states.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 31499, 82, 264, 1605, 4230, 295, 2815, 24328, 300, 1633, 362, 11068, 281, 5258, 613, 2685, 14709, 4368, 13, 50719], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14933115727192647, "compression_ratio": 1.5570776255707763, "no_speech_prob": 1.8250353485405046e-12}, {"id": 394, "seek": 127654, "start": 1283.94, "end": 1285.94, "text": " It is a pure application of flixion's theory.", "tokens": [50735, 467, 307, 257, 6075, 3861, 295, 932, 970, 313, 311, 5261, 13, 50835], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14933115727192647, "compression_ratio": 1.5570776255707763, "no_speech_prob": 1.8250353485405046e-12}, {"id": 395, "seek": 127654, "start": 1286.76, "end": 1288.92, "text": " The scientists are not looking at invariant objects.", "tokens": [50876, 440, 7708, 366, 406, 1237, 412, 33270, 394, 6565, 13, 50984], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14933115727192647, "compression_ratio": 1.5570776255707763, "no_speech_prob": 1.8250353485405046e-12}, {"id": 396, "seek": 127654, "start": 1289.26, "end": 1290.56, "text": " The original cells are gone.", "tokens": [51001, 440, 3380, 5438, 366, 2780, 13, 51066], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14933115727192647, "compression_ratio": 1.5570776255707763, "no_speech_prob": 1.8250353485405046e-12}, {"id": 397, "seek": 127654, "start": 1291.06, "end": 1295.76, "text": " But the biological system preserved the distinctions through the transformations of development.", "tokens": [51091, 583, 264, 13910, 1185, 22242, 264, 1483, 49798, 807, 264, 34852, 295, 3250, 13, 51326], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14933115727192647, "compression_ratio": 1.5570776255707763, "no_speech_prob": 1.8250353485405046e-12}, {"id": 398, "seek": 129576, "start": 1295.76, "end": 1304.34, "text": " The algorithm acts as the reconstruction operator R, using the present-day molecular traces as memory to constrain the reconstruction of the past.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 9284, 10672, 382, 264, 31565, 12973, 497, 11, 1228, 264, 1974, 12, 810, 19046, 26076, 382, 4675, 281, 1817, 7146, 264, 31565, 295, 264, 1791, 13, 50794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13677120208740234, "compression_ratio": 1.6382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.7074283610238328e-12}, {"id": 399, "seek": 129576, "start": 1304.54, "end": 1306.86, "text": " The history itself is a computational resource.", "tokens": [50804, 440, 2503, 2564, 307, 257, 28270, 7684, 13, 50920], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13677120208740234, "compression_ratio": 1.6382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.7074283610238328e-12}, {"id": 400, "seek": 129576, "start": 1307.66, "end": 1311.04, "text": " The present state is unintelligible without recovering the trajectory.", "tokens": [50960, 440, 1974, 1785, 307, 517, 27356, 1553, 29180, 264, 21512, 13, 51129], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13677120208740234, "compression_ratio": 1.6382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.7074283610238328e-12}, {"id": 401, "seek": 129576, "start": 1311.18, "end": 1311.74, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51136, 7587, 13, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13677120208740234, "compression_ratio": 1.6382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.7074283610238328e-12}, {"id": 402, "seek": 129576, "start": 1312.1, "end": 1315.92, "text": " I have to admit, I read this section three times, and I found myself getting genuinely unsettled.", "tokens": [51182, 286, 362, 281, 9796, 11, 286, 1401, 341, 3541, 1045, 1413, 11, 293, 286, 1352, 2059, 1242, 17839, 43964, 1493, 13, 51373], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13677120208740234, "compression_ratio": 1.6382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.7074283610238328e-12}, {"id": 403, "seek": 129576, "start": 1316.04, "end": 1316.78, "text": " Why is that?", "tokens": [51379, 1545, 307, 300, 30, 51416], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13677120208740234, "compression_ratio": 1.6382978723404256, "no_speech_prob": 1.7074283610238328e-12}, {"id": 404, "seek": 131678, "start": 1316.78, "end": 1328.6399999999999, "text": " Because if memory is just a constraint on reconstruction, if it's just an active repair algorithm trying to rebuild a lost distinction from scattered traces, what does that say about human memory?", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 498, 4675, 307, 445, 257, 25534, 322, 31565, 11, 498, 309, 311, 445, 364, 4967, 10535, 9284, 1382, 281, 16877, 257, 2731, 16844, 490, 21986, 26076, 11, 437, 775, 300, 584, 466, 1952, 4675, 30, 50958], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12286738788380343, "compression_ratio": 1.5025125628140703, "no_speech_prob": 1.796751658046658e-12}, {"id": 405, "seek": 131678, "start": 1328.84, "end": 1334.78, "text": " It makes my own brain sound dangerously close to, like, a generative AI hallucination.", "tokens": [50968, 467, 1669, 452, 1065, 3567, 1626, 4330, 5098, 1998, 281, 11, 411, 11, 257, 1337, 1166, 7318, 35212, 2486, 13, 51265], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12286738788380343, "compression_ratio": 1.5025125628140703, "no_speech_prob": 1.796751658046658e-12}, {"id": 406, "seek": 131678, "start": 1335.42, "end": 1336.28, "text": " It really does.", "tokens": [51297, 467, 534, 775, 13, 51340], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12286738788380343, "compression_ratio": 1.5025125628140703, "no_speech_prob": 1.796751658046658e-12}, {"id": 407, "seek": 133628, "start": 1336.28, "end": 1341.56, "text": " Like, when I remember my tenth birthday party, I'm not hitting play on a secure video file.", "tokens": [50365, 1743, 11, 562, 286, 1604, 452, 27269, 6154, 3595, 11, 286, 478, 406, 8850, 862, 322, 257, 7144, 960, 3991, 13, 50629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10253081548781622, "compression_ratio": 1.6319702602230484, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359610064201058e-12}, {"id": 408, "seek": 133628, "start": 1341.98, "end": 1350.68, "text": " I am hallucinating a scene, and that hallucination is merely being constrained by a few surviving neurological traces in my synapses.", "tokens": [50650, 286, 669, 35212, 8205, 257, 4145, 11, 293, 300, 35212, 2486, 307, 17003, 885, 38901, 538, 257, 1326, 24948, 48185, 26076, 294, 452, 5451, 2382, 279, 13, 51085], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10253081548781622, "compression_ratio": 1.6319702602230484, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359610064201058e-12}, {"id": 409, "seek": 133628, "start": 1350.8799999999999, "end": 1357.32, "text": " It is unsettling, but neurobiologically and mathematically, flixion suggests that is precisely what is happening.", "tokens": [51095, 467, 307, 43964, 1688, 11, 457, 16499, 5614, 17157, 293, 44003, 11, 932, 970, 313, 13409, 300, 307, 13402, 437, 307, 2737, 13, 51417], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10253081548781622, "compression_ratio": 1.6319702602230484, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359610064201058e-12}, {"id": 410, "seek": 133628, "start": 1357.68, "end": 1360.3799999999999, "text": " Human memory is a reconstructive repair process.", "tokens": [51435, 10294, 4675, 307, 257, 16891, 21673, 10535, 1399, 13, 51570], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10253081548781622, "compression_ratio": 1.6319702602230484, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359610064201058e-12}, {"id": 411, "seek": 133628, "start": 1360.3999999999999, "end": 1363.36, "text": " I'm literally making it up, but within guardrails.", "tokens": [51571, 286, 478, 3736, 1455, 309, 493, 11, 457, 1951, 6290, 424, 4174, 13, 51719], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10253081548781622, "compression_ratio": 1.6319702602230484, "no_speech_prob": 1.6359610064201058e-12}, {"id": 412, "seek": 136336, "start": 1363.36, "end": 1373.12, "text": " You are taking present-day traces neurological residues, applying constraints based on your general knowledge of the world, and actively attempting to repair a degraded historical distinction.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 366, 1940, 1974, 12, 810, 26076, 48185, 13141, 1247, 11, 9275, 18491, 2361, 322, 428, 2674, 3601, 295, 264, 1002, 11, 293, 13022, 22001, 281, 10535, 257, 24740, 292, 8584, 16844, 13, 50853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 413, "seek": 136336, "start": 1373.76, "end": 1376.78, "text": " When you remember, you are literally reconstructing.", "tokens": [50885, 1133, 291, 1604, 11, 291, 366, 3736, 31499, 278, 13, 51036], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 414, "seek": 136336, "start": 1376.86, "end": 1378.82, "text": " Which explains false memories perfectly.", "tokens": [51040, 3013, 13948, 7908, 8495, 6239, 13, 51138], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 415, "seek": 136336, "start": 1379.02, "end": 1379.8, "text": " Yes, it does.", "tokens": [51148, 1079, 11, 309, 775, 13, 51187], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 416, "seek": 136336, "start": 1379.82, "end": 1387.76, "text": " If the constraints are weak or the traces are too degraded by time, my brain's reconstruction operator just fills in the gaps with whatever is highly probable.", "tokens": [51188, 759, 264, 18491, 366, 5336, 420, 264, 26076, 366, 886, 24740, 292, 538, 565, 11, 452, 3567, 311, 31565, 12973, 445, 22498, 294, 264, 15031, 365, 2035, 307, 5405, 21759, 13, 51585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 417, "seek": 136336, "start": 1387.9199999999998, "end": 1390.1999999999998, "text": " It converges on a plausible past.", "tokens": [51593, 467, 9652, 2880, 322, 257, 39925, 1791, 13, 51707], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 418, "seek": 136336, "start": 1390.1999999999998, "end": 1393.24, "text": " Right. It builds a completely false scene that feels entirely real.", "tokens": [51707, 1779, 13, 467, 15182, 257, 2584, 7908, 4145, 300, 3417, 7696, 957, 13, 51859], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06978632398873322, "compression_ratio": 1.6826347305389222, "no_speech_prob": 1.6047096377397319e-12}, {"id": 419, "seek": 139336, "start": 1393.36, "end": 1397.6, "text": " Because the mechanism of remembering is identical to the mechanism of generating.", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 264, 7513, 295, 20719, 307, 14800, 281, 264, 7513, 295, 17746, 13, 50577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653632416444666, "compression_ratio": 1.7303921568627452, "no_speech_prob": 1.77624928654474e-12}, {"id": 420, "seek": 139336, "start": 1398.02, "end": 1398.3, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50598, 1079, 13, 50612], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653632416444666, "compression_ratio": 1.7303921568627452, "no_speech_prob": 1.77624928654474e-12}, {"id": 421, "seek": 139336, "start": 1399.02, "end": 1405.6, "text": " A false memory is just a reconstruction operator converging on the wrong attractor because the constraints were insufficient.", "tokens": [50648, 316, 7908, 4675, 307, 445, 257, 31565, 12973, 9652, 3249, 322, 264, 2085, 5049, 284, 570, 264, 18491, 645, 41709, 13, 50977], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653632416444666, "compression_ratio": 1.7303921568627452, "no_speech_prob": 1.77624928654474e-12}, {"id": 422, "seek": 139336, "start": 1406.28, "end": 1413.6599999999999, "text": " Personal history, biological history, universal history, they are all just the collections of traces currently available for reconstruction.", "tokens": [51011, 25317, 2503, 11, 13910, 2503, 11, 11455, 2503, 11, 436, 366, 439, 445, 264, 16641, 295, 26076, 4362, 2435, 337, 31565, 13, 51380], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1653632416444666, "compression_ratio": 1.7303921568627452, "no_speech_prob": 1.77624928654474e-12}, {"id": 423, "seek": 141366, "start": 1413.66, "end": 1416.92, "text": " Okay. My brain is officially spinning, but we have to keep moving.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 13, 1222, 3567, 307, 12053, 15640, 11, 457, 321, 362, 281, 1066, 2684, 13, 50528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14042948513496212, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.861330750987933e-12}, {"id": 424, "seek": 141366, "start": 1417.5600000000002, "end": 1423.64, "text": " Because if we are constantly rebuilding reality from traces, we have to ask how we measure the quality of those traces.", "tokens": [50560, 1436, 498, 321, 366, 6460, 36717, 4103, 490, 26076, 11, 321, 362, 281, 1029, 577, 321, 3481, 264, 3125, 295, 729, 26076, 13, 50864], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14042948513496212, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.861330750987933e-12}, {"id": 425, "seek": 141366, "start": 1423.78, "end": 1425.48, "text": " Right. How do we know what's good information?", "tokens": [50871, 1779, 13, 1012, 360, 321, 458, 437, 311, 665, 1589, 30, 50956], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14042948513496212, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.861330750987933e-12}, {"id": 426, "seek": 141366, "start": 1425.74, "end": 1431.52, "text": " Exactly. And this is where affliction takes a sledgehammer to the foundations of physics and information theory.", "tokens": [50969, 7587, 13, 400, 341, 307, 689, 2096, 75, 4105, 2516, 257, 1061, 12203, 39985, 281, 264, 22467, 295, 10649, 293, 1589, 5261, 13, 51258], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14042948513496212, "compression_ratio": 1.4978354978354977, "no_speech_prob": 1.861330750987933e-12}, {"id": 427, "seek": 143152, "start": 1431.52, "end": 1434.66, "text": " I've updated the backdrop again to reflect this shift.", "tokens": [50365, 286, 600, 10588, 264, 32697, 797, 281, 5031, 341, 5513, 13, 50522], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13596014822683028, "compression_ratio": 1.4978902953586497, "no_speech_prob": 1.996903076922907e-12}, {"id": 428, "seek": 143152, "start": 1434.72, "end": 1435.16, "text": " Oh, nice.", "tokens": [50525, 876, 11, 1481, 13, 50547], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13596014822683028, "compression_ratio": 1.4978902953586497, "no_speech_prob": 1.996903076922907e-12}, {"id": 429, "seek": 143152, "start": 1435.26, "end": 1437.5, "text": " You'll see a complex topographical map.", "tokens": [50552, 509, 603, 536, 257, 3997, 1192, 48434, 4471, 13, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13596014822683028, "compression_ratio": 1.4978902953586497, "no_speech_prob": 1.996903076922907e-12}, {"id": 430, "seek": 143152, "start": 1438.04, "end": 1443.96, "text": " There are deep, stable valleys and basins surrounded by incredibly steep, jagged, unstable hills.", "tokens": [50691, 821, 366, 2452, 11, 8351, 45614, 293, 987, 1292, 13221, 538, 6252, 16841, 11, 6368, 3004, 11, 23742, 21379, 13, 50987], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13596014822683028, "compression_ratio": 1.4978902953586497, "no_speech_prob": 1.996903076922907e-12}, {"id": 431, "seek": 143152, "start": 1444.58, "end": 1448.44, "text": " This is a visual model of what affliction calls the persistence field.", "tokens": [51018, 639, 307, 257, 5056, 2316, 295, 437, 2096, 75, 4105, 5498, 264, 37617, 2519, 13, 51211], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13596014822683028, "compression_ratio": 1.4978902953586497, "no_speech_prob": 1.996903076922907e-12}, {"id": 432, "seek": 143152, "start": 1448.68, "end": 1452.56, "text": " It looks like a gravity well or, you know, a topographic map of a mountain range.", "tokens": [51223, 467, 1542, 411, 257, 12110, 731, 420, 11, 291, 458, 11, 257, 1192, 12295, 4471, 295, 257, 6937, 3613, 13, 51417], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13596014822683028, "compression_ratio": 1.4978902953586497, "no_speech_prob": 1.996903076922907e-12}, {"id": 433, "seek": 145256, "start": 1452.56, "end": 1454.34, "text": " The geometry works similarly.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 18426, 1985, 14138, 13, 50454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 434, "seek": 145256, "start": 1454.98, "end": 1459.98, "text": " To understand the persistence field, we have to fundamentally redefine information and entropy.", "tokens": [50486, 1407, 1223, 264, 37617, 2519, 11, 321, 362, 281, 17879, 38818, 533, 1589, 293, 30867, 13, 50736], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 435, "seek": 145256, "start": 1460.3799999999999, "end": 1461.8799999999999, "text": " Okay. Let's start with information.", "tokens": [50756, 1033, 13, 961, 311, 722, 365, 1589, 13, 50831], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 436, "seek": 145256, "start": 1462.7, "end": 1467.12, "text": " In the 20th century, Claude Shannon gave us classical information theory.", "tokens": [50872, 682, 264, 945, 392, 4901, 11, 12947, 2303, 28974, 2729, 505, 13735, 1589, 5261, 13, 51093], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 437, "seek": 145256, "start": 1467.6599999999999, "end": 1473.6399999999999, "text": " We learned to think of information as symbols, bits, ones and zeros transmitted over a wire.", "tokens": [51120, 492, 3264, 281, 519, 295, 1589, 382, 16944, 11, 9239, 11, 2306, 293, 35193, 25355, 670, 257, 6234, 13, 51419], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 438, "seek": 145256, "start": 1473.8799999999999, "end": 1476.8799999999999, "text": " We measure information by the predictability of the symbols?", "tokens": [51431, 492, 3481, 1589, 538, 264, 6069, 2310, 295, 264, 16944, 30, 51581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 439, "seek": 145256, "start": 1477.12, "end": 1478.1399999999999, "text": " But affliction says no.", "tokens": [51593, 583, 2096, 75, 4105, 1619, 572, 13, 51644], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 440, "seek": 145256, "start": 1478.56, "end": 1479.6799999999998, "text": " Information is not a symbol.", "tokens": [51665, 15357, 307, 406, 257, 5986, 13, 51721], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 441, "seek": 145256, "start": 1480.12, "end": 1481.8999999999999, "text": " Information is recoverable distinction.", "tokens": [51743, 15357, 307, 8114, 712, 16844, 13, 51832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1976511119741254, "compression_ratio": 1.7214285714285715, "no_speech_prob": 2.0204211567675934e-12}, {"id": 442, "seek": 148190, "start": 1482.5600000000002, "end": 1485.3200000000002, "text": " Which is a subtle, but profound shift.", "tokens": [50398, 3013, 307, 257, 13743, 11, 457, 14382, 5513, 13, 50536], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 443, "seek": 148190, "start": 1485.72, "end": 1491.24, "text": " A distinction only carries information to the extent that it remains available after transformation and reconstruction.", "tokens": [50556, 316, 16844, 787, 16402, 1589, 281, 264, 8396, 300, 309, 7023, 2435, 934, 9887, 293, 31565, 13, 50832], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 444, "seek": 148190, "start": 1492.0600000000002, "end": 1493.0400000000002, "text": " Let's illustrate that.", "tokens": [50873, 961, 311, 23221, 300, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 445, "seek": 148190, "start": 1493.52, "end": 1495.7, "text": " Say I write you a detailed letter and mail it.", "tokens": [50946, 6463, 286, 2464, 291, 257, 9942, 5063, 293, 10071, 309, 13, 51055], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 446, "seek": 148190, "start": 1496.38, "end": 1502.66, "text": " If the postal system drops it in a river and the ink washes away so thoroughly that absolutely no reconstruction operator can read it,", "tokens": [51089, 759, 264, 49645, 1185, 11438, 309, 294, 257, 6810, 293, 264, 11276, 48616, 1314, 370, 17987, 300, 3122, 572, 31565, 12973, 393, 1401, 309, 11, 51403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 447, "seek": 148190, "start": 1503.0400000000002, "end": 1506.0400000000002, "text": " then mathematically, no information was transmitted.", "tokens": [51422, 550, 44003, 11, 572, 1589, 390, 25355, 13, 51572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 448, "seek": 148190, "start": 1506.26, "end": 1506.5, "text": " None.", "tokens": [51583, 14492, 13, 51595], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 449, "seek": 148190, "start": 1506.68, "end": 1509.18, "text": " Information is not an intrinsic property of the paper.", "tokens": [51604, 15357, 307, 406, 364, 35698, 4707, 295, 264, 3035, 13, 51729], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 450, "seek": 148190, "start": 1509.66, "end": 1511.0400000000002, "text": " It is a relational property.", "tokens": [51753, 467, 307, 257, 38444, 4707, 13, 51822], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20071330112693583, "compression_ratio": 1.7094594594594594, "no_speech_prob": 1.5922315549365962e-12}, {"id": 451, "seek": 151104, "start": 1511.04, "end": 1512.96, "text": " It is entirely about what survives.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 7696, 466, 437, 46231, 13, 50461], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16220169289167538, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045766061331679e-12}, {"id": 452, "seek": 151104, "start": 1513.3999999999999, "end": 1515.82, "text": " And if information gets flipped, entropy gets flipped, too.", "tokens": [50483, 400, 498, 1589, 2170, 26273, 11, 30867, 2170, 26273, 11, 886, 13, 50604], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16220169289167538, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045766061331679e-12}, {"id": 453, "seek": 151104, "start": 1515.94, "end": 1516.1399999999999, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50610, 1779, 13, 50620], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16220169289167538, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045766061331679e-12}, {"id": 454, "seek": 151104, "start": 1516.5, "end": 1519.62, "text": " We are taught in high school physics that entropy is a measure of disorder.", "tokens": [50638, 492, 366, 5928, 294, 1090, 1395, 10649, 300, 30867, 307, 257, 3481, 295, 13399, 13, 50794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16220169289167538, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045766061331679e-12}, {"id": 455, "seek": 151104, "start": 1520.3799999999999, "end": 1525.48, "text": " The classic example, a shattered egg on the floor, has higher entropy than a whole egg on the counter.", "tokens": [50832, 440, 7230, 1365, 11, 257, 35209, 3777, 322, 264, 4123, 11, 575, 2946, 30867, 813, 257, 1379, 3777, 322, 264, 5682, 13, 51087], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16220169289167538, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045766061331679e-12}, {"id": 456, "seek": 151104, "start": 1525.86, "end": 1530.5, "text": " Affliction redefines entropy as the loss of recoverable distinction.", "tokens": [51106, 12840, 75, 4105, 38818, 1652, 30867, 382, 264, 4470, 295, 8114, 712, 16844, 13, 51338], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16220169289167538, "compression_ratio": 1.627906976744186, "no_speech_prob": 1.6045766061331679e-12}, {"id": 457, "seek": 153050, "start": 1530.5, "end": 1531.74, "text": " Okay, so the egg.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 370, 264, 3777, 13, 50427], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2191261351108551, "compression_ratio": 1.4972375690607735, "no_speech_prob": 2.0842539933535464e-12}, {"id": 458, "seek": 153050, "start": 1532.06, "end": 1532.34, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50443, 1079, 13, 50457], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2191261351108551, "compression_ratio": 1.4972375690607735, "no_speech_prob": 2.0842539933535464e-12}, {"id": 459, "seek": 153050, "start": 1532.48, "end": 1535.82, "text": " The shattered egg has higher entropy, but not just because it looks messy.", "tokens": [50464, 440, 35209, 3777, 575, 2946, 30867, 11, 457, 406, 445, 570, 309, 1542, 16191, 13, 50631], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2191261351108551, "compression_ratio": 1.4972375690607735, "no_speech_prob": 2.0842539933535464e-12}, {"id": 460, "seek": 153050, "start": 1536.34, "end": 1545.44, "text": " It has higher entropy because the structural distinctions that made it a functioning biological egg are now vastly more difficult, practically impossible to reconstruct.", "tokens": [50657, 467, 575, 2946, 30867, 570, 264, 15067, 1483, 49798, 300, 1027, 309, 257, 18483, 13910, 3777, 366, 586, 41426, 544, 2252, 11, 15667, 6243, 281, 31499, 13, 51112], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2191261351108551, "compression_ratio": 1.4972375690607735, "no_speech_prob": 2.0842539933535464e-12}, {"id": 461, "seek": 153050, "start": 1545.88, "end": 1546.24, "text": " Ah.", "tokens": [51134, 2438, 13, 51152], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2191261351108551, "compression_ratio": 1.4972375690607735, "no_speech_prob": 2.0842539933535464e-12}, {"id": 462, "seek": 154624, "start": 1546.24, "end": 1551.44, "text": " On our topographical map, entropy is motion up those steep, unstable hills.", "tokens": [50365, 1282, 527, 1192, 48434, 4471, 11, 30867, 307, 5394, 493, 729, 16841, 11, 23742, 21379, 13, 50625], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14354406595230101, "compression_ratio": 1.0273972602739727, "no_speech_prob": 1.7011357600349442e-12}, {"id": 463, "seek": 155144, "start": 1551.44, "end": 1551.92, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 50389], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15425165015530873, "compression_ratio": 1.6495327102803738, "no_speech_prob": 1.7211924160237535e-12}, {"id": 464, "seek": 155144, "start": 1551.92, "end": 1558.16, "text": " You are moving into regions where reconstruction fails, where distinctions are lost to ambiguity.", "tokens": [50389, 509, 366, 2684, 666, 10682, 689, 31565, 18199, 11, 689, 1483, 49798, 366, 2731, 281, 46519, 13, 50701], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15425165015530873, "compression_ratio": 1.6495327102803738, "no_speech_prob": 1.7211924160237535e-12}, {"id": 465, "seek": 155144, "start": 1558.5, "end": 1558.92, "text": " And repair.", "tokens": [50718, 400, 10535, 13, 50739], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15425165015530873, "compression_ratio": 1.6495327102803738, "no_speech_prob": 1.7211924160237535e-12}, {"id": 466, "seek": 155144, "start": 1559.28, "end": 1565.8200000000002, "text": " Repair, on the other hand, is motion down the hills into the deep basins where distinctions are stable and easily recoverable.", "tokens": [50757, 3696, 1246, 11, 322, 264, 661, 1011, 11, 307, 5394, 760, 264, 21379, 666, 264, 2452, 987, 1292, 689, 1483, 49798, 366, 8351, 293, 3612, 8114, 712, 13, 51084], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15425165015530873, "compression_ratio": 1.6495327102803738, "no_speech_prob": 1.7211924160237535e-12}, {"id": 467, "seek": 155144, "start": 1565.92, "end": 1571.24, "text": " Here's where it gets really interesting, because this totally reframes how we view science and human reasoning.", "tokens": [51089, 1692, 311, 689, 309, 2170, 534, 1880, 11, 570, 341, 3879, 13334, 1632, 577, 321, 1910, 3497, 293, 1952, 21577, 13, 51355], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15425165015530873, "compression_ratio": 1.6495327102803738, "no_speech_prob": 1.7211924160237535e-12}, {"id": 468, "seek": 157124, "start": 1571.24, "end": 1578.58, "text": " If entropy is the loss of distinction and repair is the recovery of distinction, then what is a scientific theory?", "tokens": [50365, 759, 30867, 307, 264, 4470, 295, 16844, 293, 10535, 307, 264, 8597, 295, 16844, 11, 550, 437, 307, 257, 8134, 5261, 30, 50732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 469, "seek": 157124, "start": 1578.96, "end": 1579.94, "text": " It's a repair operator.", "tokens": [50751, 467, 311, 257, 10535, 12973, 13, 50800], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 470, "seek": 157124, "start": 1580.28, "end": 1580.46, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50817, 1779, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 471, "seek": 157124, "start": 1580.76, "end": 1587.38, "text": " An explanation, whether it's Einstein's theory of relativity or just you explaining why you were late to work, is essentially a repair operator.", "tokens": [50841, 1107, 10835, 11, 1968, 309, 311, 23486, 311, 5261, 295, 45675, 420, 445, 291, 13468, 983, 291, 645, 3469, 281, 589, 11, 307, 4476, 257, 10535, 12973, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 472, "seek": 157124, "start": 1587.72, "end": 1592.1200000000001, "text": " Explanations are higher-order repair processes operating within distinction space.", "tokens": [51189, 12514, 282, 763, 366, 2946, 12, 4687, 10535, 7555, 7447, 1951, 16844, 1901, 13, 51409], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 473, "seek": 157124, "start": 1592.32, "end": 1593.66, "text": " Let's break that down mechanically.", "tokens": [51419, 961, 311, 1821, 300, 760, 4236, 984, 13, 51486], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 474, "seek": 157124, "start": 1594.24, "end": 1597.2, "text": " Imagine an ancient astronomer looking at the night sky.", "tokens": [51515, 11739, 364, 7832, 11117, 14301, 1237, 412, 264, 1818, 5443, 13, 51663], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15093612670898438, "compression_ratio": 1.7350746268656716, "no_speech_prob": 1.5310998996431735e-12}, {"id": 475, "seek": 159720, "start": 1597.2, "end": 1601.8600000000001, "text": " They observe a planet, say, Mars, moving weirdly.", "tokens": [50365, 814, 11441, 257, 5054, 11, 584, 11, 9692, 11, 2684, 48931, 13, 50598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 476, "seek": 159720, "start": 1602.28, "end": 1603.1200000000001, "text": " Retrograde motion.", "tokens": [50619, 11495, 340, 8692, 5394, 13, 50661], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 477, "seek": 159720, "start": 1603.24, "end": 1603.38, "text": " Yeah.", "tokens": [50667, 865, 13, 50674], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 478, "seek": 159720, "start": 1603.94, "end": 1607.42, "text": " Most nights it moves east, but occasionally it stops and moves west.", "tokens": [50702, 4534, 13249, 309, 6067, 10648, 11, 457, 16895, 309, 10094, 293, 6067, 7009, 13, 50876], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 479, "seek": 159720, "start": 1607.98, "end": 1609.94, "text": " The astronomer plots these dots on a chart.", "tokens": [50904, 440, 11117, 14301, 28609, 613, 15026, 322, 257, 6927, 13, 51002], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 480, "seek": 159720, "start": 1611.04, "end": 1615.1200000000001, "text": " Without a theory, this data is highly entropic in fliction sense.", "tokens": [51057, 9129, 257, 5261, 11, 341, 1412, 307, 5405, 948, 39173, 294, 932, 4105, 2020, 13, 51261], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 481, "seek": 159720, "start": 1615.3, "end": 1615.88, "text": " It's fragmented.", "tokens": [51270, 467, 311, 9241, 14684, 13, 51299], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 482, "seek": 159720, "start": 1616.04, "end": 1616.8, "text": " Doesn't make sense.", "tokens": [51307, 12955, 380, 652, 2020, 13, 51345], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 483, "seek": 159720, "start": 1616.94, "end": 1623.04, "text": " The distinctions between the dots are hard to predict, and if you lose a page of data, you can't reconstruct where Mars was.", "tokens": [51352, 440, 1483, 49798, 1296, 264, 15026, 366, 1152, 281, 6069, 11, 293, 498, 291, 3624, 257, 3028, 295, 1412, 11, 291, 393, 380, 31499, 689, 9692, 390, 13, 51657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15842508447581324, "compression_ratio": 1.5660377358490567, "no_speech_prob": 2.6248204998413627e-12}, {"id": 484, "seek": 162304, "start": 1623.04, "end": 1627.74, "text": " The data points are sitting high up on the unstable hills of the persistence field.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 1412, 2793, 366, 3798, 1090, 493, 322, 264, 23742, 21379, 295, 264, 37617, 2519, 13, 50600], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 485, "seek": 162304, "start": 1627.8799999999999, "end": 1634.46, "text": " But then, Johannes Kepler comes along and introduces the theory of planetary motion, and later Newton introduces gravity.", "tokens": [50607, 583, 550, 11, 48455, 3189, 22732, 1487, 2051, 293, 31472, 264, 5261, 295, 35788, 5394, 11, 293, 1780, 19541, 31472, 12110, 13, 50936], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 486, "seek": 162304, "start": 1635.1, "end": 1637.86, "text": " Suddenly, this theory acts as a global repair operator.", "tokens": [50968, 21194, 11, 341, 5261, 10672, 382, 257, 4338, 10535, 12973, 13, 51106], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 487, "seek": 162304, "start": 1637.94, "end": 1638.98, "text": " It connects everything.", "tokens": [51110, 467, 16967, 1203, 13, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 488, "seek": 162304, "start": 1639.32, "end": 1643.28, "text": " It draws an elegant elliptical pathway that connects all those fragmented dots.", "tokens": [51179, 467, 20045, 364, 21117, 8284, 22439, 804, 18590, 300, 16967, 439, 729, 9241, 14684, 15026, 13, 51377], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 489, "seek": 162304, "start": 1643.6599999999999, "end": 1649.78, "text": " It drastically lowers the entropy of the data because it creates a robust mathematical pathway to reconstruct those distinctions.", "tokens": [51396, 467, 29673, 44936, 264, 30867, 295, 264, 1412, 570, 309, 7829, 257, 13956, 18894, 18590, 281, 31499, 729, 1483, 49798, 13, 51702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 490, "seek": 162304, "start": 1649.96, "end": 1650.3999999999999, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51711, 7587, 13, 51733], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11262386816519278, "compression_ratio": 1.68, "no_speech_prob": 1.3940822237920591e-12}, {"id": 491, "seek": 165040, "start": 1650.4, "end": 1656.88, "text": " If I lose a month of observations, I can use the theory of gravity to perfectly reconstruct exactly where Mars was.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 286, 3624, 257, 1618, 295, 18163, 11, 286, 393, 764, 264, 5261, 295, 12110, 281, 6239, 31499, 2293, 689, 9692, 390, 13, 50689], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 492, "seek": 165040, "start": 1657.38, "end": 1659.8600000000001, "text": " The explanation repaired the structural relationships.", "tokens": [50714, 440, 10835, 36551, 264, 15067, 6159, 13, 50838], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 493, "seek": 165040, "start": 1660.24, "end": 1661.74, "text": " It didn't just describe the dots.", "tokens": [50857, 467, 994, 380, 445, 6786, 264, 15026, 13, 50932], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 494, "seek": 165040, "start": 1661.88, "end": 1663.8600000000001, "text": " It restored their structural alignment.", "tokens": [50939, 467, 23143, 641, 15067, 18515, 13, 51038], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 495, "seek": 165040, "start": 1664.38, "end": 1669.94, "text": " And the text highlights a fascinating, cutting-edge modern equivalent of this with AI flow matching.", "tokens": [51064, 400, 264, 2487, 14254, 257, 10343, 11, 6492, 12, 12203, 4363, 10344, 295, 341, 365, 7318, 3095, 14324, 13, 51342], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 496, "seek": 165040, "start": 1670.3000000000002, "end": 1670.5400000000002, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51360, 1779, 13, 51372], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 497, "seek": 165040, "start": 1670.64, "end": 1673.4, "text": " The 2026 work by Moorhead and colleagues.", "tokens": [51377, 440, 945, 10880, 589, 538, 3335, 284, 1934, 293, 7734, 13, 51515], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 498, "seek": 165040, "start": 1674.0600000000002, "end": 1679.66, "text": " Let's dive into how this AI actually works, because it perfectly maps on defliction's theory.", "tokens": [51548, 961, 311, 9192, 666, 577, 341, 7318, 767, 1985, 11, 570, 309, 6239, 11317, 322, 1060, 75, 4105, 311, 5261, 13, 51828], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16265832652216372, "compression_ratio": 1.5947712418300655, "no_speech_prob": 1.585881599652783e-12}, {"id": 499, "seek": 167966, "start": 1679.66, "end": 1682.5400000000002, "text": " So flow matching is used in computational biology.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 3095, 14324, 307, 1143, 294, 28270, 14956, 13, 50509], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 500, "seek": 167966, "start": 1682.96, "end": 1684.44, "text": " You have two massive data sets.", "tokens": [50530, 509, 362, 732, 5994, 1412, 6352, 13, 50604], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 501, "seek": 167966, "start": 1684.94, "end": 1688.16, "text": " Data set A is a distribution of cells from a healthy patient.", "tokens": [50629, 11888, 992, 316, 307, 257, 7316, 295, 5438, 490, 257, 4627, 4537, 13, 50790], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 502, "seek": 167966, "start": 1688.68, "end": 1692.6200000000001, "text": " Data set B is a distribution of cells from a patient with a specific disease.", "tokens": [50816, 11888, 992, 363, 307, 257, 7316, 295, 5438, 490, 257, 4537, 365, 257, 2685, 4752, 13, 51013], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 503, "seek": 167966, "start": 1692.88, "end": 1697.0400000000002, "text": " And these exist in high-dimensional space, like we're tracking thousands of genes per cell.", "tokens": [51026, 400, 613, 2514, 294, 1090, 12, 18759, 1901, 11, 411, 321, 434, 11603, 5383, 295, 14424, 680, 2815, 13, 51234], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 504, "seek": 167966, "start": 1697.42, "end": 1697.68, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [51253, 1779, 13, 51266], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 505, "seek": 167966, "start": 1697.8400000000001, "end": 1702.28, "text": " The AI's job is to figure out how to map the healthy cells onto the diseased cells.", "tokens": [51274, 440, 7318, 311, 1691, 307, 281, 2573, 484, 577, 281, 4471, 264, 4627, 5438, 3911, 264, 3814, 1937, 5438, 13, 51496], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14442629907645432, "compression_ratio": 1.6945606694560669, "no_speech_prob": 1.9054532257589685e-12}, {"id": 506, "seek": 170228, "start": 1702.28, "end": 1707.56, "text": " Under classical thinking, you might ask, how is the neural network memorizing the biological states?", "tokens": [50365, 6974, 13735, 1953, 11, 291, 1062, 1029, 11, 577, 307, 264, 18161, 3209, 10560, 3319, 264, 13910, 4368, 30, 50629], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659489106596186, "compression_ratio": 1.608, "no_speech_prob": 2.5736565656409027e-12}, {"id": 507, "seek": 170228, "start": 1708.26, "end": 1711.3799999999999, "text": " But Flicksham points out the AI isn't storing states at all.", "tokens": [50664, 583, 3235, 618, 2716, 335, 2793, 484, 264, 7318, 1943, 380, 26085, 4368, 412, 439, 13, 50820], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659489106596186, "compression_ratio": 1.608, "no_speech_prob": 2.5736565656409027e-12}, {"id": 508, "seek": 170228, "start": 1711.54, "end": 1712.0, "text": " Not at all.", "tokens": [50828, 1726, 412, 439, 13, 50851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659489106596186, "compression_ratio": 1.608, "no_speech_prob": 2.5736565656409027e-12}, {"id": 509, "seek": 170228, "start": 1712.24, "end": 1714.52, "text": " Flow matching works by using optimal transport theory.", "tokens": [50863, 32792, 14324, 1985, 538, 1228, 16252, 5495, 5261, 13, 50977], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659489106596186, "compression_ratio": 1.608, "no_speech_prob": 2.5736565656409027e-12}, {"id": 510, "seek": 170228, "start": 1714.96, "end": 1723.74, "text": " It calculates the most efficient mathematical path, the optimal vector field, to transform the probability distribution of healthy cells into the distribution of sick cells.", "tokens": [50999, 467, 4322, 1024, 264, 881, 7148, 18894, 3100, 11, 264, 16252, 8062, 2519, 11, 281, 4088, 264, 8482, 7316, 295, 4627, 5438, 666, 264, 7316, 295, 4998, 5438, 13, 51438], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1659489106596186, "compression_ratio": 1.608, "no_speech_prob": 2.5736565656409027e-12}, {"id": 511, "seek": 172374, "start": 1723.74, "end": 1726.04, "text": " It's drawing a map of the transformation.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 6316, 257, 4471, 295, 264, 9887, 13, 50480], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13820764422416687, "compression_ratio": 1.4808743169398908, "no_speech_prob": 1.861314271114911e-12}, {"id": 512, "seek": 172374, "start": 1726.72, "end": 1731.08, "text": " But why does the AI's math map actually mean anything in reality?", "tokens": [50514, 583, 983, 775, 264, 7318, 311, 5221, 4471, 767, 914, 1340, 294, 4103, 30, 50732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13820764422416687, "compression_ratio": 1.4808743169398908, "no_speech_prob": 1.861314271114911e-12}, {"id": 513, "seek": 172374, "start": 1731.42, "end": 1738.78, "text": " Because the model only succeeds if biologically relevant distinctions survive the mathematical transformation path it learns.", "tokens": [50749, 1436, 264, 2316, 787, 49263, 498, 3228, 17157, 7340, 1483, 49798, 7867, 264, 18894, 9887, 3100, 309, 27152, 13, 51117], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13820764422416687, "compression_ratio": 1.4808743169398908, "no_speech_prob": 1.861314271114911e-12}, {"id": 514, "seek": 172374, "start": 1738.86, "end": 1740.22, "text": " Oh, so it's proving persistence.", "tokens": [51121, 876, 11, 370, 309, 311, 27221, 37617, 13, 51189], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13820764422416687, "compression_ratio": 1.4808743169398908, "no_speech_prob": 1.861314271114911e-12}, {"id": 515, "seek": 172374, "start": 1740.56, "end": 1740.84, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51206, 1079, 13, 51220], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13820764422416687, "compression_ratio": 1.4808743169398908, "no_speech_prob": 1.861314271114911e-12}, {"id": 516, "seek": 174084, "start": 1740.84, "end": 1750.06, "text": " It maps the cells successfully because it is learning the actual topography of how recoverable distinction is transported through biological space.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 11317, 264, 5438, 10727, 570, 309, 307, 2539, 264, 3539, 1192, 5820, 295, 577, 8114, 712, 16844, 307, 29373, 807, 13910, 1901, 13, 50826], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1434087880452474, "compression_ratio": 1.593625498007968, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324703733585412e-12}, {"id": 517, "seek": 174084, "start": 1750.56, "end": 1754.12, "text": " The AI model is literally acting as a scientific explanation.", "tokens": [50851, 440, 7318, 2316, 307, 3736, 6577, 382, 257, 8134, 10835, 13, 51029], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1434087880452474, "compression_ratio": 1.593625498007968, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324703733585412e-12}, {"id": 518, "seek": 174084, "start": 1754.36, "end": 1754.86, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51041, 7587, 13, 51066], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1434087880452474, "compression_ratio": 1.593625498007968, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324703733585412e-12}, {"id": 519, "seek": 174084, "start": 1755.28, "end": 1764.08, "text": " It is a repair operator that restores structural alignment between two entirely different states, proving that the underlying distinctions persist across the disease transformation.", "tokens": [51087, 467, 307, 257, 10535, 12973, 300, 1472, 2706, 15067, 18515, 1296, 732, 7696, 819, 4368, 11, 27221, 300, 264, 14217, 1483, 49798, 13233, 2108, 264, 4752, 9887, 13, 51527], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1434087880452474, "compression_ratio": 1.593625498007968, "no_speech_prob": 1.8324703733585412e-12}, {"id": 520, "seek": 176408, "start": 1764.08, "end": 1771.1599999999999, "text": " Okay, I have a major problem with the explanation as repair operator idea, and I want to see if the framework holds up.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 286, 362, 257, 2563, 1154, 365, 264, 10835, 382, 10535, 12973, 1558, 11, 293, 286, 528, 281, 536, 498, 264, 8388, 9190, 493, 13, 50719], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 521, "seek": 176408, "start": 1771.22, "end": 1771.56, "text": " Bid me.", "tokens": [50722, 363, 327, 385, 13, 50739], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 522, "seek": 176408, "start": 1771.8799999999999, "end": 1781.8799999999999, "text": " If an explanation is just a mental framework that connects dots, lowers ambiguity, and makes things reconstructable, couldn't a completely unhinged conspiracy theory count as a good explanation?", "tokens": [50755, 759, 364, 10835, 307, 445, 257, 4973, 8388, 300, 16967, 15026, 11, 44936, 46519, 11, 293, 1669, 721, 31499, 712, 11, 2809, 380, 257, 2584, 517, 571, 292, 20439, 5261, 1207, 382, 257, 665, 10835, 30, 51255], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 523, "seek": 176408, "start": 1782.1, "end": 1783.22, "text": " Oh, I see where you're going.", "tokens": [51266, 876, 11, 286, 536, 689, 291, 434, 516, 13, 51322], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 524, "seek": 176408, "start": 1783.48, "end": 1785.86, "text": " Like, imagine someone who believes the Earth is flat.", "tokens": [51335, 1743, 11, 3811, 1580, 567, 12307, 264, 4755, 307, 4962, 13, 51454], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 525, "seek": 176408, "start": 1786.46, "end": 1790.1399999999999, "text": " They have built an incredibly intricate web of explanations.", "tokens": [51484, 814, 362, 3094, 364, 6252, 38015, 3670, 295, 28708, 13, 51668], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 526, "seek": 176408, "start": 1790.96, "end": 1792.82, "text": " To them, the data isn't entropic.", "tokens": [51709, 1407, 552, 11, 264, 1412, 1943, 380, 948, 39173, 13, 51802], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1237741298362857, "compression_ratio": 1.6266233766233766, "no_speech_prob": 1.9432699806948284e-12}, {"id": 527, "seek": 179282, "start": 1792.82, "end": 1798.82, "text": " Their theory perfectly organizes their worldview and makes their observations recoverable.", "tokens": [50365, 6710, 5261, 6239, 4645, 279, 641, 41141, 293, 1669, 641, 18163, 8114, 712, 13, 50665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 528, "seek": 179282, "start": 1799.6599999999999, "end": 1800.98, "text": " It's internally consistent.", "tokens": [50707, 467, 311, 19501, 8398, 13, 50773], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 529, "seek": 179282, "start": 1801.3799999999999, "end": 1801.6, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50793, 1779, 13, 50804], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 530, "seek": 179282, "start": 1801.96, "end": 1806.8799999999999, "text": " So by flexion's math, is the flat Earth theory just as valid as the theory of gravity?", "tokens": [50822, 407, 538, 5896, 313, 311, 5221, 11, 307, 264, 4962, 4755, 5261, 445, 382, 7363, 382, 264, 5261, 295, 12110, 30, 51068], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 531, "seek": 179282, "start": 1807.36, "end": 1813.52, "text": " If we connect this to the bigger picture, this is exactly why flexion includes a massive section on deception and illusion.", "tokens": [51092, 759, 321, 1745, 341, 281, 264, 3801, 3036, 11, 341, 307, 2293, 983, 5896, 313, 5974, 257, 5994, 3541, 322, 40451, 293, 18854, 13, 51400], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 532, "seek": 179282, "start": 1814.36, "end": 1818.82, "text": " Flexion mathematically distinguishes between internal persistence and external alignment.", "tokens": [51442, 29208, 313, 44003, 11365, 16423, 1296, 6920, 37617, 293, 8320, 18515, 13, 51665], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 533, "seek": 179282, "start": 1819.72, "end": 1820.86, "text": " Okay, walk me through that.", "tokens": [51710, 1033, 11, 1792, 385, 807, 300, 13, 51767], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 534, "seek": 179282, "start": 1820.8999999999999, "end": 1821.3799999999999, "text": " What's the difference?", "tokens": [51769, 708, 311, 264, 2649, 30, 51793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17593256632486978, "compression_ratio": 1.65625, "no_speech_prob": 1.655504184260026e-12}, {"id": 535, "seek": 182138, "start": 1821.38, "end": 1826.8000000000002, "text": " A conspiracy theory, or a deeply held delusion, has extremely high internal persistence.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 20439, 5261, 11, 420, 257, 8760, 5167, 1103, 5704, 11, 575, 4664, 1090, 6920, 37617, 13, 50636], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13390695217043855, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 1.8468306311331117e-12}, {"id": 536, "seek": 182138, "start": 1827.46, "end": 1830.7600000000002, "text": " All the internal concepts and distinctions tightly support each other.", "tokens": [50669, 1057, 264, 6920, 10392, 293, 1483, 49798, 21952, 1406, 1184, 661, 13, 50834], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13390695217043855, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 1.8468306311331117e-12}, {"id": 537, "seek": 182138, "start": 1830.8400000000001, "end": 1831.64, "text": " Like an echo chamber.", "tokens": [50838, 1743, 364, 14300, 13610, 13, 50878], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13390695217043855, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 1.8468306311331117e-12}, {"id": 538, "seek": 182138, "start": 1831.74, "end": 1832.18, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50883, 7587, 13, 50905], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13390695217043855, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 1.8468306311331117e-12}, {"id": 539, "seek": 182138, "start": 1832.5400000000002, "end": 1837.1200000000001, "text": " The logic is often perfectly circular, which makes it highly robust within its own closed system.", "tokens": [50923, 440, 9952, 307, 2049, 6239, 16476, 11, 597, 1669, 309, 5405, 13956, 1951, 1080, 1065, 5395, 1185, 13, 51152], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13390695217043855, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 1.8468306311331117e-12}, {"id": 540, "seek": 182138, "start": 1837.5, "end": 1842.14, "text": " It acts as a powerful local attractor, a deep basin on our topographical map.", "tokens": [51171, 467, 10672, 382, 257, 4005, 2654, 5049, 284, 11, 257, 2452, 34863, 322, 527, 1192, 48434, 4471, 13, 51403], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13390695217043855, "compression_ratio": 1.525, "no_speech_prob": 1.8468306311331117e-12}, {"id": 541, "seek": 184214, "start": 1842.14, "end": 1850.3000000000002, "text": " So to the person trapped inside it, it feels like an incredibly powerful explanation because it successfully repairs all their internal cognitive distinctions.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 281, 264, 954, 14994, 1854, 309, 11, 309, 3417, 411, 364, 6252, 4005, 10835, 570, 309, 10727, 28823, 439, 641, 6920, 15605, 1483, 49798, 13, 50773], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14413567711325254, "compression_ratio": 1.642570281124498, "no_speech_prob": 2.6244457995705517e-12}, {"id": 542, "seek": 184214, "start": 1850.3000000000002, "end": 1851.7, "text": " It feels like absolute truth.", "tokens": [50773, 467, 3417, 411, 8236, 3494, 13, 50843], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14413567711325254, "compression_ratio": 1.642570281124498, "no_speech_prob": 2.6244457995705517e-12}, {"id": 543, "seek": 184214, "start": 1851.7, "end": 1852.6000000000001, "text": " But it's not.", "tokens": [50843, 583, 309, 311, 406, 13, 50888], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14413567711325254, "compression_ratio": 1.642570281124498, "no_speech_prob": 2.6244457995705517e-12}, {"id": 544, "seek": 184214, "start": 1852.6000000000001, "end": 1857.0, "text": " But it suffers from a massive alignment deficit with external persistence.", "tokens": [50888, 583, 309, 33776, 490, 257, 5994, 18515, 22132, 365, 8320, 37617, 13, 51108], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14413567711325254, "compression_ratio": 1.642570281124498, "no_speech_prob": 2.6244457995705517e-12}, {"id": 545, "seek": 184214, "start": 1857.5600000000002, "end": 1864.68, "text": " It perfectly organizes the believer's mind, but it fails to align with distinctions arising from the broader physical environment.", "tokens": [51136, 467, 6239, 4645, 279, 264, 23892, 311, 1575, 11, 457, 309, 18199, 281, 7975, 365, 1483, 49798, 44900, 490, 264, 13227, 4001, 2823, 13, 51492], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14413567711325254, "compression_ratio": 1.642570281124498, "no_speech_prob": 2.6244457995705517e-12}, {"id": 546, "seek": 186468, "start": 1864.68, "end": 1868.3200000000002, "text": " Like the physics of horizons, satellite telemetry, or gravity.", "tokens": [50365, 1743, 264, 10649, 295, 7937, 892, 11, 16016, 4304, 5537, 627, 11, 420, 12110, 13, 50547], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17732261476062594, "compression_ratio": 1.446236559139785, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967482970199233e-12}, {"id": 547, "seek": 186468, "start": 1868.5600000000002, "end": 1869.0, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50559, 7587, 13, 50581], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17732261476062594, "compression_ratio": 1.446236559139785, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967482970199233e-12}, {"id": 548, "seek": 186468, "start": 1869.5, "end": 1874.1000000000001, "text": " Because of this alignment deficit, it is categorized mathematically as an illusion.", "tokens": [50606, 1436, 295, 341, 18515, 22132, 11, 309, 307, 19250, 1602, 44003, 382, 364, 18854, 13, 50836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17732261476062594, "compression_ratio": 1.446236559139785, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967482970199233e-12}, {"id": 549, "seek": 186468, "start": 1874.74, "end": 1880.88, "text": " It is a local attractor that will inevitably fragment and shatter when the domain of transformations is expanded.", "tokens": [50868, 467, 307, 257, 2654, 5049, 284, 300, 486, 28171, 26424, 293, 402, 1161, 562, 264, 9274, 295, 34852, 307, 14342, 13, 51175], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17732261476062594, "compression_ratio": 1.446236559139785, "no_speech_prob": 1.7967482970199233e-12}, {"id": 550, "seek": 188088, "start": 1880.88, "end": 1882.42, "text": " Oh, that makes so much sense.", "tokens": [50365, 876, 11, 300, 1669, 370, 709, 2020, 13, 50442], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 551, "seek": 188088, "start": 1883.16, "end": 1885.22, "text": " Truth is what survives domain expansion.", "tokens": [50479, 20522, 307, 437, 46231, 9274, 11260, 13, 50582], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 552, "seek": 188088, "start": 1886.0800000000002, "end": 1888.22, "text": " Falsehood shatters when the boundaries are pushed.", "tokens": [50625, 50040, 3809, 402, 37690, 562, 264, 13180, 366, 9152, 13, 50732], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 553, "seek": 188088, "start": 1888.38, "end": 1889.24, "text": " That is exactly it.", "tokens": [50740, 663, 307, 2293, 309, 13, 50783], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 554, "seek": 188088, "start": 1889.3000000000002, "end": 1890.72, "text": " That is incredibly satisfying.", "tokens": [50786, 663, 307, 6252, 18348, 13, 50857], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 555, "seek": 188088, "start": 1890.8400000000001, "end": 1894.2800000000002, "text": " The conspiracy theory is a fortress, but it's built in a tiny puddle.", "tokens": [50863, 440, 20439, 5261, 307, 257, 31826, 11, 457, 309, 311, 3094, 294, 257, 5870, 14166, 2285, 13, 51035], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 556, "seek": 188088, "start": 1895.0, "end": 1899.2600000000002, "text": " The moment you introduce the transformations of the wider ocean, the fortress dissolves.", "tokens": [51071, 440, 1623, 291, 5366, 264, 34852, 295, 264, 11842, 7810, 11, 264, 31826, 15840, 977, 13, 51284], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 557, "seek": 188088, "start": 1899.5400000000002, "end": 1900.88, "text": " It can't handle the new transformations.", "tokens": [51298, 467, 393, 380, 4813, 264, 777, 34852, 13, 51365], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 558, "seek": 188088, "start": 1901.7, "end": 1904.8400000000001, "text": " Which transitions us perfectly to the next logical problem.", "tokens": [51406, 3013, 23767, 505, 6239, 281, 264, 958, 14978, 1154, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 559, "seek": 188088, "start": 1905.44, "end": 1908.3200000000002, "text": " How do we actually build something that survives the ocean?", "tokens": [51593, 1012, 360, 321, 767, 1322, 746, 300, 46231, 264, 7810, 30, 51737], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14713271325375854, "compression_ratio": 1.662162162162162, "no_speech_prob": 2.2541486906224595e-12}, {"id": 560, "seek": 190832, "start": 1908.32, "end": 1913.4399999999998, "text": " How do we move from scattered traces up to actual robust truth?", "tokens": [50365, 1012, 360, 321, 1286, 490, 21986, 26076, 493, 281, 3539, 13956, 3494, 30, 50621], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 561, "seek": 190832, "start": 1913.76, "end": 1916.78, "text": " Fliction solves this by laying out a reconstructive hierarchy.", "tokens": [50637, 3235, 4105, 39890, 341, 538, 14903, 484, 257, 16891, 21673, 22333, 13, 50788], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 562, "seek": 190832, "start": 1917.36, "end": 1922.12, "text": " It is an epistemic ladder, mapping how we build robust realities out of fragile traces.", "tokens": [50817, 467, 307, 364, 2388, 468, 3438, 18325, 11, 18350, 577, 321, 1322, 13956, 27785, 484, 295, 23847, 26076, 13, 51055], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 563, "seek": 190832, "start": 1922.54, "end": 1923.22, "text": " Let's climb it.", "tokens": [51076, 961, 311, 10724, 309, 13, 51110], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 564, "seek": 190832, "start": 1923.5, "end": 1925.34, "text": " We start at the very bottom, level one.", "tokens": [51124, 492, 722, 412, 264, 588, 2767, 11, 1496, 472, 13, 51216], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 565, "seek": 190832, "start": 1925.5, "end": 1931.54, "text": " Level one is information, which, as we defined earlier, is just raw, recoverable distinction.", "tokens": [51224, 16872, 472, 307, 1589, 11, 597, 11, 382, 321, 7642, 3071, 11, 307, 445, 8936, 11, 8114, 712, 16844, 13, 51526], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 566, "seek": 190832, "start": 1932.12, "end": 1932.56, "text": " Correct.", "tokens": [51555, 12753, 13, 51577], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 567, "seek": 190832, "start": 1933.1, "end": 1935.24, "text": " But raw information is brittle.", "tokens": [51604, 583, 8936, 1589, 307, 49325, 13, 51711], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16969644455682664, "compression_ratio": 1.575875486381323, "no_speech_prob": 1.416163085236899e-12}, {"id": 568, "seek": 193524, "start": 1935.24, "end": 1943.1, "text": " A single data point on a graph or a single identified antigen in the body is information, but it isn't knowledge.", "tokens": [50365, 316, 2167, 1412, 935, 322, 257, 4295, 420, 257, 2167, 9234, 2511, 3213, 294, 264, 1772, 307, 1589, 11, 457, 309, 1943, 380, 3601, 13, 50758], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1360308548499798, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839963025786718e-12}, {"id": 569, "seek": 193524, "start": 1943.34, "end": 1943.44, "text": " Right.", "tokens": [50770, 1779, 13, 50775], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1360308548499798, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839963025786718e-12}, {"id": 570, "seek": 193524, "start": 1943.56, "end": 1945.8, "text": " That brings us to level two, knowledge.", "tokens": [50781, 663, 5607, 505, 281, 1496, 732, 11, 3601, 13, 50893], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1360308548499798, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839963025786718e-12}, {"id": 571, "seek": 193524, "start": 1946.32, "end": 1949.6200000000001, "text": " Knowledge is an organized network of these recoverable distinctions.", "tokens": [50919, 32906, 307, 364, 9983, 3209, 295, 613, 8114, 712, 1483, 49798, 13, 51084], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1360308548499798, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839963025786718e-12}, {"id": 572, "seek": 193524, "start": 1949.9, "end": 1950.84, "text": " So they're connected now.", "tokens": [51098, 407, 436, 434, 4582, 586, 13, 51145], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1360308548499798, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839963025786718e-12}, {"id": 573, "seek": 193524, "start": 1950.98, "end": 1956.22, "text": " It's when distinctions are integrated into a structure where they actually support each other's reconstruction.", "tokens": [51152, 467, 311, 562, 1483, 49798, 366, 10919, 666, 257, 3877, 689, 436, 767, 1406, 1184, 661, 311, 31565, 13, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1360308548499798, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839963025786718e-12}, {"id": 574, "seek": 195622, "start": 1956.22, "end": 1962.58, "text": " Okay, so if information is identifying a single threat, knowledge is an entire immune system's library of antibodies.", "tokens": [50365, 1033, 11, 370, 498, 1589, 307, 16696, 257, 2167, 4734, 11, 3601, 307, 364, 2302, 11992, 1185, 311, 6405, 295, 28356, 13, 50683], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 575, "seek": 195622, "start": 1963.0, "end": 1963.6200000000001, "text": " It's a network.", "tokens": [50704, 467, 311, 257, 3209, 13, 50735], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 576, "seek": 195622, "start": 1963.74, "end": 1964.24, "text": " Yeah, exactly.", "tokens": [50741, 865, 11, 2293, 13, 50766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 577, "seek": 195622, "start": 1964.4, "end": 1967.7, "text": " Or in human terms, memorizing the multiplication tables is knowledge.", "tokens": [50774, 1610, 294, 1952, 2115, 11, 10560, 3319, 264, 27290, 8020, 307, 3601, 13, 50939], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 578, "seek": 195622, "start": 1967.96, "end": 1969.7, "text": " You have built a network of distinctions.", "tokens": [50952, 509, 362, 3094, 257, 3209, 295, 1483, 49798, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 579, "seek": 195622, "start": 1970.0, "end": 1970.3, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [51054, 1079, 13, 51069], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 580, "seek": 195622, "start": 1970.78, "end": 1976.44, "text": " But as we know, you can memorize the multiplication tables without having any idea why 4 times 4 equals 16.", "tokens": [51093, 583, 382, 321, 458, 11, 291, 393, 27478, 264, 27290, 8020, 1553, 1419, 604, 1558, 983, 1017, 1413, 1017, 6915, 3165, 13, 51376], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 581, "seek": 195622, "start": 1976.66, "end": 1977.74, "text": " You just know the output.", "tokens": [51387, 509, 445, 458, 264, 5598, 13, 51441], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 582, "seek": 195622, "start": 1977.92, "end": 1979.0, "text": " You just memorize the pattern.", "tokens": [51450, 509, 445, 27478, 264, 5102, 13, 51504], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14540203339462981, "compression_ratio": 1.6862745098039216, "no_speech_prob": 1.314545802939826e-12}, {"id": 583, "seek": 197900, "start": 1979.0, "end": 1982.12, "text": " To know the why, you have to move to level three, understanding.", "tokens": [50365, 1407, 458, 264, 983, 11, 291, 362, 281, 1286, 281, 1496, 1045, 11, 3701, 13, 50521], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 584, "seek": 197900, "start": 1982.76, "end": 1985.7, "text": " Fliction defines understanding as a second-order phenomenon.", "tokens": [50553, 3235, 4105, 23122, 3701, 382, 257, 1150, 12, 4687, 14029, 13, 50700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 585, "seek": 197900, "start": 1986.22, "end": 1988.72, "text": " It is the reconstruction of reconstruction itself.", "tokens": [50726, 467, 307, 264, 31565, 295, 31565, 2564, 13, 50851], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 586, "seek": 197900, "start": 1989.1, "end": 1990.62, "text": " The reconstruction of reconstruction.", "tokens": [50870, 440, 31565, 295, 31565, 13, 50946], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 587, "seek": 197900, "start": 1990.76, "end": 1991.68, "text": " That's a dense phrase.", "tokens": [50953, 663, 311, 257, 18011, 9535, 13, 50999], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 588, "seek": 197900, "start": 1992.02, "end": 1993.04, "text": " How does that work mechanically?", "tokens": [51016, 1012, 775, 300, 589, 4236, 984, 30, 51067], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 589, "seek": 197900, "start": 1993.28, "end": 1994.22, "text": " Think about it this way.", "tokens": [51079, 6557, 466, 309, 341, 636, 13, 51126], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 590, "seek": 197900, "start": 1994.86, "end": 1998.38, "text": " Knowledge is having the ability to recover a specific distinction.", "tokens": [51158, 32906, 307, 1419, 264, 3485, 281, 8114, 257, 2685, 16844, 13, 51334], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 591, "seek": 197900, "start": 1999.36, "end": 2003.8, "text": " Understanding is recovering the mechanism that generated the distinction in the first place.", "tokens": [51383, 36858, 307, 29180, 264, 7513, 300, 10833, 264, 16844, 294, 264, 700, 1081, 13, 51605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 592, "seek": 197900, "start": 2003.94, "end": 2005.58, "text": " Ah, the mechanism.", "tokens": [51612, 2438, 11, 264, 7513, 13, 51694], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2001217235218395, "compression_ratio": 1.8515625, "no_speech_prob": 1.4839817742695605e-12}, {"id": 593, "seek": 200558, "start": 2005.58, "end": 2009.9399999999998, "text": " Back to your math example, memorizing the quadratic formula is knowledge.", "tokens": [50365, 5833, 281, 428, 5221, 1365, 11, 10560, 3319, 264, 37262, 8513, 307, 3601, 13, 50583], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 594, "seek": 200558, "start": 2010.08, "end": 2019.1999999999998, "text": " You can spit it out, but grasping the algebraic proof, understanding exactly why the formula works so that you can derive it from scratch.", "tokens": [50590, 509, 393, 22127, 309, 484, 11, 457, 29444, 3381, 264, 21989, 299, 8177, 11, 3701, 2293, 983, 264, 8513, 1985, 370, 300, 291, 393, 28446, 309, 490, 8459, 13, 51046], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 595, "seek": 200558, "start": 2019.26, "end": 2020.9399999999998, "text": " Or apply it to a totally new problem.", "tokens": [51049, 1610, 3079, 309, 281, 257, 3879, 777, 1154, 13, 51133], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 596, "seek": 200558, "start": 2021.04, "end": 2021.34, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51138, 7587, 13, 51153], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 597, "seek": 200558, "start": 2021.6799999999998, "end": 2022.6999999999998, "text": " That is understanding.", "tokens": [51170, 663, 307, 3701, 13, 51221], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 598, "seek": 200558, "start": 2022.8999999999999, "end": 2027.08, "text": " You aren't just storing the facts, you are storing the operators that generate the facts.", "tokens": [51231, 509, 3212, 380, 445, 26085, 264, 9130, 11, 291, 366, 26085, 264, 19077, 300, 8460, 264, 9130, 13, 51440], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 599, "seek": 200558, "start": 2027.22, "end": 2030.58, "text": " So in the immune system analogy, understanding isn't the antibody.", "tokens": [51447, 407, 294, 264, 11992, 1185, 21663, 11, 3701, 1943, 380, 264, 34507, 13, 51615], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 600, "seek": 200558, "start": 2031.1799999999998, "end": 2032.46, "text": " Understanding is the bone marrow.", "tokens": [51645, 36858, 307, 264, 9026, 47739, 13, 51709], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1427493643971671, "compression_ratio": 1.7326007326007327, "no_speech_prob": 1.796748188599706e-12}, {"id": 601, "seek": 203246, "start": 2032.46, "end": 2042.1200000000001, "text": " It is the architectural mechanism capable of generating entirely novel responses to novel threats because it grasps the underlying generative rules.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 307, 264, 26621, 7513, 8189, 295, 17746, 7696, 7613, 13019, 281, 7613, 14909, 570, 309, 29444, 1878, 264, 14217, 1337, 1166, 4474, 13, 50848], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 602, "seek": 203246, "start": 2042.32, "end": 2043.18, "text": " An excellent analogy.", "tokens": [50858, 1107, 7103, 21663, 13, 50901], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 603, "seek": 203246, "start": 2043.3400000000001, "end": 2047.16, "text": " And once you have the generative rules, you reach level four, wisdom.", "tokens": [50909, 400, 1564, 291, 362, 264, 1337, 1166, 4474, 11, 291, 2524, 1496, 1451, 11, 10712, 13, 51100], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 604, "seek": 203246, "start": 2047.58, "end": 2051.5, "text": " Okay, how do you think wisdom fits into a rigorous mathematical framework?", "tokens": [51121, 1033, 11, 577, 360, 291, 519, 10712, 9001, 666, 257, 29882, 18894, 8388, 30, 51317], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 605, "seek": 203246, "start": 2051.96, "end": 2055.78, "text": " Usually we think of wisdom as something mystical, like an old sage on a mountain.", "tokens": [51340, 11419, 321, 519, 295, 10712, 382, 746, 40565, 11, 411, 364, 1331, 19721, 322, 257, 6937, 13, 51531], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 606, "seek": 203246, "start": 2056.08, "end": 2059.0, "text": " But in this framework, it has to be a mechanical operation.", "tokens": [51546, 583, 294, 341, 8388, 11, 309, 575, 281, 312, 257, 12070, 6916, 13, 51692], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 607, "seek": 203246, "start": 2059.32, "end": 2061.32, "text": " It is a third-order level of operation.", "tokens": [51708, 467, 307, 257, 2636, 12, 4687, 1496, 295, 6916, 13, 51808], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.125509872771146, "compression_ratio": 1.6962457337883958, "no_speech_prob": 1.868604663363138e-12}, {"id": 608, "seek": 206132, "start": 2061.32, "end": 2065.86, "text": " Wisdom is the governance of reconstruction over long persistence horizons.", "tokens": [50365, 34143, 4121, 307, 264, 17449, 295, 31565, 670, 938, 37617, 7937, 892, 13, 50592], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 609, "seek": 206132, "start": 2066.1000000000004, "end": 2066.52, "text": " Governance.", "tokens": [50604, 5515, 719, 13, 50625], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 610, "seek": 206132, "start": 2066.76, "end": 2070.4, "text": " So making strategic choices about what to reconstruct and what to let decay.", "tokens": [50637, 407, 1455, 10924, 7994, 466, 437, 281, 31499, 293, 437, 281, 718, 21039, 13, 50819], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 611, "seek": 206132, "start": 2071.1600000000003, "end": 2071.6000000000004, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50857, 7587, 13, 50879], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 612, "seek": 206132, "start": 2072.4, "end": 2074.1000000000004, "text": " Understanding gives you immense power.", "tokens": [50919, 36858, 2709, 291, 22920, 1347, 13, 51004], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 613, "seek": 206132, "start": 2074.32, "end": 2076.94, "text": " It gives you multiple possible reconstruction pathways.", "tokens": [51015, 467, 2709, 291, 3866, 1944, 31565, 22988, 13, 51146], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 614, "seek": 206132, "start": 2077.5, "end": 2082.3, "text": " Because you understand physics, you know how to build a nuclear weapon, and you know how to build a solar panel.", "tokens": [51174, 1436, 291, 1223, 10649, 11, 291, 458, 577, 281, 1322, 257, 8179, 7463, 11, 293, 291, 458, 577, 281, 1322, 257, 7936, 4831, 13, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 615, "seek": 206132, "start": 2082.4, "end": 2084.36, "text": " But understanding doesn't tell you which one you should build.", "tokens": [51419, 583, 3701, 1177, 380, 980, 291, 597, 472, 291, 820, 1322, 13, 51517], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 616, "seek": 206132, "start": 2084.5, "end": 2084.76, "text": " No.", "tokens": [51524, 883, 13, 51537], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16208899938143218, "compression_ratio": 1.7529411764705882, "no_speech_prob": 1.9131519285453535e-12}, {"id": 617, "seek": 208476, "start": 2084.76, "end": 2086.84, "text": " Wisdom is the evaluative layer.", "tokens": [50365, 34143, 4121, 307, 264, 6133, 1166, 4583, 13, 50469], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11987514331423003, "compression_ratio": 1.4840425531914894, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248969621739494e-12}, {"id": 618, "seek": 208476, "start": 2086.84, "end": 2093.86, "text": " It evaluates which reconstruction policies will preserve long-term recoverability under irreducible uncertainty.", "tokens": [50469, 467, 6133, 1024, 597, 31565, 7657, 486, 15665, 938, 12, 7039, 8114, 2310, 833, 16014, 769, 32128, 15697, 13, 50820], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11987514331423003, "compression_ratio": 1.4840425531914894, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248969621739494e-12}, {"id": 619, "seek": 208476, "start": 2094.5400000000004, "end": 2102.38, "text": " So wisdom is recognizing that building a thousand nuclear weapons might offer a short-term local persistence advantage for one nation,", "tokens": [50854, 407, 10712, 307, 18538, 300, 2390, 257, 4714, 8179, 7278, 1062, 2626, 257, 2099, 12, 7039, 2654, 37617, 5002, 337, 472, 4790, 11, 51246], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11987514331423003, "compression_ratio": 1.4840425531914894, "no_speech_prob": 1.5248969621739494e-12}, {"id": 620, "seek": 210238, "start": 2102.38, "end": 2110.26, "text": " but it introduces a massive global fragility that threatens the long-term reconstructive capacity of the entire human species.", "tokens": [50365, 457, 309, 31472, 257, 5994, 4338, 9241, 1140, 300, 47511, 264, 938, 12, 7039, 16891, 21673, 6042, 295, 264, 2302, 1952, 6172, 13, 50759], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1535447005069617, "compression_ratio": 1.4921465968586387, "no_speech_prob": 1.5368590731631993e-12}, {"id": 621, "seek": 210238, "start": 2110.46, "end": 2110.82, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [50769, 7587, 13, 50787], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1535447005069617, "compression_ratio": 1.4921465968586387, "no_speech_prob": 1.5368590731631993e-12}, {"id": 622, "seek": 210238, "start": 2111.26, "end": 2115.02, "text": " Wisdom prevents us from optimizing for a local peak that eventually drops off a cliff.", "tokens": [50809, 34143, 4121, 22367, 505, 490, 40425, 337, 257, 2654, 10651, 300, 4728, 11438, 766, 257, 22316, 13, 50997], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1535447005069617, "compression_ratio": 1.4921465968586387, "no_speech_prob": 1.5368590731631993e-12}, {"id": 623, "seek": 210238, "start": 2115.4, "end": 2118.52, "text": " Wisdom preserves optionality, robustness, and systemic health.", "tokens": [51016, 34143, 4121, 1183, 9054, 3614, 1860, 11, 13956, 1287, 11, 293, 23789, 1585, 13, 51172], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1535447005069617, "compression_ratio": 1.4921465968586387, "no_speech_prob": 1.5368590731631993e-12}, {"id": 624, "seek": 211852, "start": 2118.52, "end": 2122.72, "text": " And finally, at the very top of this epistemic ladder, we reach the apex.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 2721, 11, 412, 264, 588, 1192, 295, 341, 2388, 468, 3438, 18325, 11, 321, 2524, 264, 48115, 13, 50575], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 625, "seek": 211852, "start": 2123.34, "end": 2123.78, "text": " Truth.", "tokens": [50606, 20522, 13, 50628], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 626, "seek": 211852, "start": 2124.2, "end": 2124.8, "text": " The summit.", "tokens": [50649, 440, 21564, 13, 50679], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 627, "seek": 211852, "start": 2125.0, "end": 2126.6, "text": " And truth isn't just a fact.", "tokens": [50689, 400, 3494, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 1186, 13, 50769], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 628, "seek": 211852, "start": 2127.0, "end": 2127.7, "text": " It's an alignment.", "tokens": [50789, 467, 311, 364, 18515, 13, 50824], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 629, "seek": 211852, "start": 2127.98, "end": 2130.12, "text": " Truth is not a primitive element you start with.", "tokens": [50838, 20522, 307, 406, 257, 28540, 4478, 291, 722, 365, 13, 50945], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 630, "seek": 211852, "start": 2130.68, "end": 2135.66, "text": " Truth is the culmination of stable alignment across all these reconstructive structures.", "tokens": [50973, 20522, 307, 264, 28583, 399, 295, 8351, 18515, 2108, 439, 613, 16891, 21673, 9227, 13, 51222], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 631, "seek": 211852, "start": 2135.74, "end": 2137.22, "text": " It's the whole stack working together.", "tokens": [51226, 467, 311, 264, 1379, 8630, 1364, 1214, 13, 51300], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 632, "seek": 211852, "start": 2137.3, "end": 2144.54, "text": " It is a structural correspondence between our internal models and the external world that survives transformations across the broadest possible domains.", "tokens": [51304, 467, 307, 257, 15067, 38135, 1296, 527, 6920, 5245, 293, 264, 8320, 1002, 300, 46231, 34852, 2108, 264, 4152, 377, 1944, 25514, 13, 51666], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1428042386485412, "compression_ratio": 1.6967509025270757, "no_speech_prob": 2.5337943548864317e-12}, {"id": 633, "seek": 214454, "start": 2144.54, "end": 2150.36, "text": " Truth is what remains recoverable when subjected to maximum transformational stress.", "tokens": [50365, 20522, 307, 437, 7023, 8114, 712, 562, 32153, 281, 6674, 4088, 1478, 4244, 13, 50656], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 634, "seek": 214454, "start": 2150.72, "end": 2158.14, "text": " So we build from information, network it into knowledge, learn the generative rules to achieve understanding, govern those rules with wisdom.", "tokens": [50674, 407, 321, 1322, 490, 1589, 11, 3209, 309, 666, 3601, 11, 1466, 264, 1337, 1166, 4474, 281, 4584, 3701, 11, 1980, 729, 4474, 365, 10712, 13, 51045], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 635, "seek": 214454, "start": 2158.5, "end": 2165.96, "text": " And when that entire architecture perfectly maps onto reality over deep time, we achieve truth.", "tokens": [51063, 400, 562, 300, 2302, 9482, 6239, 11317, 3911, 4103, 670, 2452, 565, 11, 321, 4584, 3494, 13, 51436], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 636, "seek": 214454, "start": 2166.08, "end": 2166.94, "text": " That's the progression.", "tokens": [51442, 663, 311, 264, 18733, 13, 51485], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 637, "seek": 214454, "start": 2167.3, "end": 2170.7599999999998, "text": " But wait, this creates the ultimate philosophical cliffhanger.", "tokens": [51503, 583, 1699, 11, 341, 7829, 264, 9705, 25066, 22316, 71, 3176, 13, 51676], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 638, "seek": 214454, "start": 2170.96, "end": 2172.96, "text": " Our mental models are aligning with reality.", "tokens": [51686, 2621, 4973, 5245, 366, 419, 9676, 365, 4103, 13, 51786], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 639, "seek": 214454, "start": 2172.96, "end": 2174.3, "text": " But what is reality?", "tokens": [51786, 583, 437, 307, 4103, 30, 51853], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13300477185295623, "compression_ratio": 1.6323024054982818, "no_speech_prob": 1.7616243750198657e-12}, {"id": 640, "seek": 217454, "start": 2174.54, "end": 2176.92, "text": " What is the bedrock that our truth is aligning with?", "tokens": [50365, 708, 307, 264, 2901, 17799, 300, 527, 3494, 307, 419, 9676, 365, 30, 50484], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 641, "seek": 217454, "start": 2177.16, "end": 2182.46, "text": " This brings us to the final, and arguably the most technically demanding and profound, section of the monograph.", "tokens": [50496, 639, 5607, 505, 281, 264, 2572, 11, 293, 26771, 264, 881, 12120, 19960, 293, 14382, 11, 3541, 295, 264, 1108, 3108, 13, 50761], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 642, "seek": 217454, "start": 2183.14, "end": 2190.88, "text": " Fliction takes this entire framework of recoverable distinction and turns it outward, applying it to the ultimate nature of existence, space-time, and causality.", "tokens": [50795, 3235, 4105, 2516, 341, 2302, 8388, 295, 8114, 712, 16844, 293, 4523, 309, 26914, 11, 9275, 309, 281, 264, 9705, 3687, 295, 9123, 11, 1901, 12, 3766, 11, 293, 3302, 1860, 13, 51182], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 643, "seek": 217454, "start": 2191.22, "end": 2192.22, "text": " Let's start with reality.", "tokens": [51199, 961, 311, 722, 365, 4103, 13, 51249], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 644, "seek": 217454, "start": 2192.56, "end": 2198.94, "text": " If objects are just temporary bundles of surviving distinctions, and identity is relative, what is actually real?", "tokens": [51266, 759, 6565, 366, 445, 13413, 13882, 904, 295, 24948, 1483, 49798, 11, 293, 6575, 307, 4972, 11, 437, 307, 767, 957, 30, 51585], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 645, "seek": 217454, "start": 2199.18, "end": 2202.12, "text": " Reality is not a physical catalog of stuff.", "tokens": [51597, 33822, 307, 406, 257, 4001, 19746, 295, 1507, 13, 51744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 646, "seek": 217454, "start": 2202.12, "end": 2204.06, "text": " You cannot put reality in a box.", "tokens": [51744, 509, 2644, 829, 4103, 294, 257, 2424, 13, 51841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1300033359077033, "compression_ratio": 1.6687116564417177, "no_speech_prob": 2.894069532632937e-12}, {"id": 647, "seek": 220454, "start": 2204.54, "end": 2210.18, "text": " Fiction defines reality operationally as the domain of persistent constraint.", "tokens": [50365, 479, 4105, 23122, 4103, 6916, 379, 382, 264, 9274, 295, 24315, 25534, 13, 50647], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2777755627265343, "compression_ratio": 1.664179104477612, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108455273474489e-12}, {"id": 648, "seek": 220454, "start": 2210.46, "end": 2211.36, "text": " Persistent constraint.", "tokens": [50661, 14006, 25367, 25534, 13, 50706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2777755627265343, "compression_ratio": 1.664179104477612, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108455273474489e-12}, {"id": 649, "seek": 220454, "start": 2211.46, "end": 2212.82, "text": " It is whatever pushes back.", "tokens": [50711, 467, 307, 2035, 21020, 646, 13, 50779], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2777755627265343, "compression_ratio": 1.664179104477612, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108455273474489e-12}, {"id": 650, "seek": 220454, "start": 2213.2599999999998, "end": 2217.36, "text": " It is whatever refuses or restricts our attempts at reconstruction.", "tokens": [50801, 467, 307, 2035, 33222, 420, 7694, 82, 527, 15257, 412, 31565, 13, 51006], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2777755627265343, "compression_ratio": 1.664179104477612, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108455273474489e-12}, {"id": 651, "seek": 220454, "start": 2217.46, "end": 2218.32, "text": " Refusal of reconstruction.", "tokens": [51011, 16957, 11765, 295, 31565, 13, 51054], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2777755627265343, "compression_ratio": 1.664179104477612, "no_speech_prob": 1.8108455273474489e-12}, {"id": 652, "seek": 221832, "start": 2218.32, "end": 2227.06, "text": " So if I try to walk through a solid brick wall, the physical properties of the wall refuse my body's attempt to reconstruct my spatial coordinates on the other side of it.", "tokens": [50365, 407, 498, 286, 853, 281, 1792, 807, 257, 5100, 16725, 2929, 11, 264, 4001, 7221, 295, 264, 2929, 16791, 452, 1772, 311, 5217, 281, 31499, 452, 23598, 21056, 322, 264, 661, 1252, 295, 309, 13, 50802], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11204389995998806, "compression_ratio": 1.355072463768116, "no_speech_prob": 1.984520837591819e-12}, {"id": 653, "seek": 221832, "start": 2227.1000000000004, "end": 2227.84, "text": " They block you.", "tokens": [50804, 814, 3461, 291, 13, 50841], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11204389995998806, "compression_ratio": 1.355072463768116, "no_speech_prob": 1.984520837591819e-12}, {"id": 654, "seek": 222784, "start": 2227.84, "end": 2231.48, "text": " That refusal, that hard mathematical constraint, is reality.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 48948, 11, 300, 1152, 18894, 25534, 11, 307, 4103, 13, 50547], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.31051514943440756, "compression_ratio": 0.9523809523809523, "no_speech_prob": 1.9736445550783133e-12}, {"id": 655, "seek": 223148, "start": 2231.48, "end": 2232.48, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [50365, 48746, 736, 13, 50415], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2732527542114258, "compression_ratio": 1.1428571428571428, "no_speech_prob": 3.116564731980853e-12}, {"id": 656, "seek": 223148, "start": 2232.48, "end": 2237.12, "text": " If there were no constraints in the universe, any transformation would be instantly possible.", "tokens": [50415, 759, 456, 645, 572, 18491, 294, 264, 6445, 11, 604, 9887, 576, 312, 13518, 1944, 13, 50647], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.2732527542114258, "compression_ratio": 1.1428571428571428, "no_speech_prob": 3.116564731980853e-12}, {"id": 657, "seek": 223712, "start": 2237.12, "end": 2241.38, "text": " You could reconstruct a lump of coal into a block of gold with zero effort.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 727, 31499, 257, 25551, 295, 10209, 666, 257, 3461, 295, 3821, 365, 4018, 4630, 13, 50578], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16209103610064532, "compression_ratio": 1.5509259259259258, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610427868909207e-12}, {"id": 658, "seek": 223712, "start": 2241.38, "end": 2246.16, "text": " The universe would just be infinite, featureless chaos, and alignment would be meaningless.", "tokens": [50578, 440, 6445, 576, 445, 312, 13785, 11, 4111, 1832, 14158, 11, 293, 18515, 576, 312, 33232, 13, 50817], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16209103610064532, "compression_ratio": 1.5509259259259258, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610427868909207e-12}, {"id": 659, "seek": 223712, "start": 2246.58, "end": 2249.44, "text": " Reality is the structural resistance of the universe.", "tokens": [50838, 33822, 307, 264, 15067, 7335, 295, 264, 6445, 13, 50981], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16209103610064532, "compression_ratio": 1.5509259259259258, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610427868909207e-12}, {"id": 660, "seek": 223712, "start": 2249.94, "end": 2256.92, "text": " And existence, what it means to actually be a thing, is simply persistent admissibility within those constraints.", "tokens": [51006, 400, 9123, 11, 437, 309, 1355, 281, 767, 312, 257, 551, 11, 307, 2935, 24315, 5910, 891, 2841, 1951, 729, 18491, 13, 51355], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16209103610064532, "compression_ratio": 1.5509259259259258, "no_speech_prob": 1.8610427868909207e-12}, {"id": 661, "seek": 225692, "start": 2256.92, "end": 2258.7400000000002, "text": " Persistent admissibility.", "tokens": [50365, 14006, 25367, 5910, 891, 2841, 13, 50456], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18174846710697298, "compression_ratio": 1.6358695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279085706341847e-12}, {"id": 662, "seek": 225692, "start": 2258.7400000000002, "end": 2272.1800000000003, "text": " You exist because the intricate web of universal constraints currently permits your specific biological and structural distinctions to be continuously reconstructed from one second to the next.", "tokens": [50456, 509, 2514, 570, 264, 38015, 3670, 295, 11455, 18491, 4362, 30990, 428, 2685, 13910, 293, 15067, 1483, 49798, 281, 312, 15684, 31499, 292, 490, 472, 1150, 281, 264, 958, 13, 51128], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18174846710697298, "compression_ratio": 1.6358695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279085706341847e-12}, {"id": 663, "seek": 225692, "start": 2272.32, "end": 2273.7400000000002, "text": " You fit into the allowed parameters.", "tokens": [51135, 509, 3318, 666, 264, 4350, 9834, 13, 51206], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18174846710697298, "compression_ratio": 1.6358695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279085706341847e-12}, {"id": 664, "seek": 225692, "start": 2274.56, "end": 2276.38, "text": " You are allowed to exist by the constraints.", "tokens": [51247, 509, 366, 4350, 281, 2514, 538, 264, 18491, 13, 51338], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18174846710697298, "compression_ratio": 1.6358695652173914, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279085706341847e-12}, {"id": 665, "seek": 227638, "start": 2276.38, "end": 2280.84, "text": " Yes. You are an admissible trajectory through the constraint space.", "tokens": [50365, 1079, 13, 509, 366, 364, 5910, 41073, 21512, 807, 264, 25534, 1901, 13, 50588], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12727378095899308, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.905632335957863e-12}, {"id": 666, "seek": 227638, "start": 2281.44, "end": 2290.02, "text": " But to understand trajectory, we have to look at Fliction's definition of time, which is a radical departure from both classical physics and common intuition.", "tokens": [50618, 583, 281, 1223, 21512, 11, 321, 362, 281, 574, 412, 3235, 4105, 311, 7123, 295, 565, 11, 597, 307, 257, 12001, 25866, 490, 1293, 13735, 10649, 293, 2689, 24002, 13, 51047], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12727378095899308, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.905632335957863e-12}, {"id": 667, "seek": 227638, "start": 2290.26, "end": 2291.28, "text": " Oh, time. Yeah.", "tokens": [51059, 876, 11, 565, 13, 865, 13, 51110], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12727378095899308, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.905632335957863e-12}, {"id": 668, "seek": 227638, "start": 2291.58, "end": 2295.94, "text": " Time is not a dimension we are traveling through, it is not a container, and it is not a flowing river.", "tokens": [51125, 6161, 307, 406, 257, 10139, 321, 366, 9712, 807, 11, 309, 307, 406, 257, 10129, 11, 293, 309, 307, 406, 257, 13974, 6810, 13, 51343], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12727378095899308, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.905632335957863e-12}, {"id": 669, "seek": 227638, "start": 2296.1, "end": 2298.28, "text": " This part forced me to reread it multiple times.", "tokens": [51351, 639, 644, 7579, 385, 281, 46453, 345, 309, 3866, 1413, 13, 51460], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12727378095899308, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.905632335957863e-12}, {"id": 670, "seek": 227638, "start": 2298.8, "end": 2301.58, "text": " If time isn't a dimension we move through, what is it?", "tokens": [51486, 759, 565, 1943, 380, 257, 10139, 321, 1286, 807, 11, 437, 307, 309, 30, 51625], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12727378095899308, "compression_ratio": 1.6666666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 1.905632335957863e-12}, {"id": 671, "seek": 230158, "start": 2301.58, "end": 2306.74, "text": " Time is the irreversible accumulation of constraint into a reconstruction history.", "tokens": [50365, 6161, 307, 264, 16014, 840, 964, 35647, 295, 25534, 666, 257, 31565, 2503, 13, 50623], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 672, "seek": 230158, "start": 2306.88, "end": 2308.4, "text": " Time is accumulated constraint.", "tokens": [50630, 6161, 307, 31346, 25534, 13, 50706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 673, "seek": 230158, "start": 2308.7, "end": 2311.5, "text": " Okay, I need to push back on this from a standard physics perspective.", "tokens": [50721, 1033, 11, 286, 643, 281, 2944, 646, 322, 341, 490, 257, 3832, 10649, 4585, 13, 50861], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 674, "seek": 230158, "start": 2311.52, "end": 2311.9, "text": " Okay, four.", "tokens": [50862, 1033, 11, 1451, 13, 50881], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 675, "seek": 230158, "start": 2312.38, "end": 2315.42, "text": " In Einstein's relativity, we often talk about the block universe.", "tokens": [50905, 682, 23486, 311, 45675, 11, 321, 2049, 751, 466, 264, 3461, 6445, 13, 51057], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 676, "seek": 230158, "start": 2315.42, "end": 2320.2599999999998, "text": " The past, present, and future all exist simultaneously in a four-dimensional block.", "tokens": [51057, 440, 1791, 11, 1974, 11, 293, 2027, 439, 2514, 16561, 294, 257, 1451, 12, 18759, 3461, 13, 51299], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 677, "seek": 230158, "start": 2320.94, "end": 2322.02, "text": " Time is just a coordinate.", "tokens": [51333, 6161, 307, 445, 257, 15670, 13, 51387], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 678, "seek": 230158, "start": 2322.68, "end": 2325.66, "text": " How does Fliction reconcile that with time being an accumulation?", "tokens": [51420, 1012, 775, 3235, 4105, 41059, 300, 365, 565, 885, 364, 35647, 30, 51569], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 679, "seek": 230158, "start": 2326.16, "end": 2330.64, "text": " This raises an important question about the intersection of epistemology and physics.", "tokens": [51594, 639, 19658, 364, 1021, 1168, 466, 264, 15236, 295, 2388, 43958, 1793, 293, 10649, 13, 51818], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20995888828246062, "compression_ratio": 1.696774193548387, "no_speech_prob": 2.2189975551478724e-12}, {"id": 680, "seek": 233064, "start": 2330.64, "end": 2339.2799999999997, "text": " This section argues the block universe is a mathematical abstraction that totally ignores the reconstructive asymmetry of reality.", "tokens": [50365, 639, 3541, 38218, 264, 3461, 6445, 307, 257, 18894, 37765, 300, 3879, 5335, 2706, 264, 16891, 21673, 37277, 9889, 295, 4103, 13, 50797], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 681, "seek": 233064, "start": 2339.8399999999997, "end": 2340.14, "text": " Meaning what?", "tokens": [50825, 19948, 437, 30, 50840], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 682, "seek": 233064, "start": 2340.74, "end": 2343.54, "text": " Why does the past feel fixed and unchangeable?", "tokens": [50870, 1545, 775, 264, 1791, 841, 6806, 293, 517, 15431, 712, 30, 51010], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 683, "seek": 233064, "start": 2343.94, "end": 2351.2999999999997, "text": " Because, in Fliction's model, the constraints of past events have already been incorporated into the structural geometry of the universe.", "tokens": [51030, 1436, 11, 294, 3235, 4105, 311, 2316, 11, 264, 18491, 295, 1791, 3931, 362, 1217, 668, 21654, 666, 264, 15067, 18426, 295, 264, 6445, 13, 51398], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 684, "seek": 233064, "start": 2351.52, "end": 2352.4, "text": " They are locked in.", "tokens": [51409, 814, 366, 9376, 294, 13, 51453], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 685, "seek": 233064, "start": 2352.54, "end": 2353.3399999999997, "text": " They are the foundation.", "tokens": [51460, 814, 366, 264, 7030, 13, 51500], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 686, "seek": 233064, "start": 2353.74, "end": 2356.04, "text": " They are the conditions upon which the present is built.", "tokens": [51520, 814, 366, 264, 4487, 3564, 597, 264, 1974, 307, 3094, 13, 51635], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 687, "seek": 233064, "start": 2356.22, "end": 2357.8599999999997, "text": " Why does the future feel open?", "tokens": [51644, 1545, 775, 264, 2027, 841, 1269, 30, 51726], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18649377555490654, "compression_ratio": 1.6985294117647058, "no_speech_prob": 1.598061418438268e-12}, {"id": 688, "seek": 235786, "start": 2357.86, "end": 2365.44, "text": " Because the future consists merely of admissible continuations that have not yet been subjected to the incorporation of constraint.", "tokens": [50365, 1436, 264, 2027, 14689, 17003, 295, 5910, 41073, 2993, 763, 300, 362, 406, 1939, 668, 32153, 281, 264, 8788, 399, 295, 25534, 13, 50744], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 689, "seek": 235786, "start": 2365.8, "end": 2366.3, "text": " And the present.", "tokens": [50762, 400, 264, 1974, 13, 50787], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 690, "seek": 235786, "start": 2366.7000000000003, "end": 2367.6, "text": " Where are we right now?", "tokens": [50807, 2305, 366, 321, 558, 586, 30, 50852], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 691, "seek": 235786, "start": 2367.96, "end": 2371.0, "text": " The present is not a location on a geometric timeline.", "tokens": [50870, 440, 1974, 307, 406, 257, 4914, 322, 257, 33246, 12933, 13, 51022], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 692, "seek": 235786, "start": 2371.5, "end": 2372.84, "text": " The present is an operation.", "tokens": [51047, 440, 1974, 307, 364, 6916, 13, 51114], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 693, "seek": 235786, "start": 2373.28, "end": 2373.6400000000003, "text": " An operation.", "tokens": [51136, 1107, 6916, 13, 51154], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 694, "seek": 235786, "start": 2373.88, "end": 2378.7200000000003, "text": " It is the active boundary where admissibility is converted into incorporated constraint.", "tokens": [51166, 467, 307, 264, 4967, 12866, 689, 5910, 891, 2841, 307, 16424, 666, 21654, 25534, 13, 51408], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 695, "seek": 235786, "start": 2379.2000000000003, "end": 2382.6200000000003, "text": " The present is the absolute edge of universal reconstruction.", "tokens": [51432, 440, 1974, 307, 264, 8236, 4691, 295, 11455, 31565, 13, 51603], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1867653727531433, "compression_ratio": 1.8384279475982532, "no_speech_prob": 1.610602493387625e-12}, {"id": 696, "seek": 238262, "start": 2382.62, "end": 2384.3199999999997, "text": " That is staggering.", "tokens": [50365, 663, 307, 42974, 13, 50450], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14955989424004612, "compression_ratio": 1.7918552036199096, "no_speech_prob": 2.25359661487623e-12}, {"id": 697, "seek": 238262, "start": 2384.8199999999997, "end": 2390.2799999999997, "text": " The universe is literally computing itself into existence at the boundary of the present, logging in constraints.", "tokens": [50475, 440, 6445, 307, 3736, 15866, 2564, 666, 9123, 412, 264, 12866, 295, 264, 1974, 11, 27991, 294, 18491, 13, 50748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14955989424004612, "compression_ratio": 1.7918552036199096, "no_speech_prob": 2.25359661487623e-12}, {"id": 698, "seek": 238262, "start": 2390.68, "end": 2397.7799999999997, "text": " And our biological brains experience that continuous incorporation as the subjective feeling of time passing.", "tokens": [50768, 400, 527, 13910, 15442, 1752, 300, 10957, 8788, 399, 382, 264, 25972, 2633, 295, 565, 8437, 13, 51123], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14955989424004612, "compression_ratio": 1.7918552036199096, "no_speech_prob": 2.25359661487623e-12}, {"id": 699, "seek": 238262, "start": 2397.94, "end": 2398.2999999999997, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51131, 7587, 13, 51149], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14955989424004612, "compression_ratio": 1.7918552036199096, "no_speech_prob": 2.25359661487623e-12}, {"id": 700, "seek": 238262, "start": 2398.54, "end": 2402.46, "text": " The sensation of time is literally just the sensation of constraint accumulating.", "tokens": [51161, 440, 20069, 295, 565, 307, 3736, 445, 264, 20069, 295, 25534, 12989, 12162, 13, 51357], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14955989424004612, "compression_ratio": 1.7918552036199096, "no_speech_prob": 2.25359661487623e-12}, {"id": 701, "seek": 238262, "start": 2402.98, "end": 2406.3399999999997, "text": " And if time is the accumulation of constraint, what is space?", "tokens": [51383, 400, 498, 565, 307, 264, 35647, 295, 25534, 11, 437, 307, 1901, 30, 51551], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14955989424004612, "compression_ratio": 1.7918552036199096, "no_speech_prob": 2.25359661487623e-12}, {"id": 702, "seek": 240634, "start": 2406.34, "end": 2409.28, "text": " Space is not an empty vacuum that holds objects.", "tokens": [50365, 8705, 307, 406, 364, 6707, 14224, 300, 9190, 6565, 13, 50512], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 703, "seek": 240634, "start": 2409.98, "end": 2412.6200000000003, "text": " Space is the organization of distinguishability.", "tokens": [50547, 8705, 307, 264, 4475, 295, 20206, 2310, 13, 50679], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 704, "seek": 240634, "start": 2413.3, "end": 2416.38, "text": " Meaning, distance isn't about physical meters or miles.", "tokens": [50713, 19948, 11, 4560, 1943, 380, 466, 4001, 8146, 420, 6193, 13, 50867], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 705, "seek": 240634, "start": 2416.78, "end": 2417.96, "text": " Distance is about effort.", "tokens": [50887, 9840, 719, 307, 466, 4630, 13, 50946], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 706, "seek": 240634, "start": 2418.6000000000004, "end": 2418.82, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50978, 1079, 13, 50989], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 707, "seek": 240634, "start": 2419.38, "end": 2421.8, "text": " Distance is a measure of reconstruction cost.", "tokens": [51017, 9840, 719, 307, 257, 3481, 295, 31565, 2063, 13, 51138], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 708, "seek": 240634, "start": 2422.6200000000003, "end": 2430.1000000000004, "text": " Two distinct points are close in space if it requires very little transformational work to map one to the other or to allow them to interact.", "tokens": [51179, 4453, 10644, 2793, 366, 1998, 294, 1901, 498, 309, 7029, 588, 707, 4088, 1478, 589, 281, 4471, 472, 281, 264, 661, 420, 281, 2089, 552, 281, 4648, 13, 51553], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 709, "seek": 240634, "start": 2430.28, "end": 2432.1800000000003, "text": " And they are far apart if it takes a lot of work.", "tokens": [51562, 400, 436, 366, 1400, 4936, 498, 309, 2516, 257, 688, 295, 589, 13, 51657], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14648159572056363, "compression_ratio": 1.6420233463035019, "no_speech_prob": 1.9279142084854817e-12}, {"id": 710, "seek": 243218, "start": 2432.18, "end": 2436.7, "text": " If it requires a massive amount of transformational energy or time for them to interact, yes.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 309, 7029, 257, 5994, 2372, 295, 4088, 1478, 2281, 420, 565, 337, 552, 281, 4648, 11, 2086, 13, 50591], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13245736371289502, "compression_ratio": 1.7132867132867133, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442460658270933e-12}, {"id": 711, "seek": 243218, "start": 2437.14, "end": 2441.0, "text": " Geometry itself is just the mathematical map of these distinguishability relations.", "tokens": [50613, 2876, 34730, 2564, 307, 445, 264, 18894, 4471, 295, 613, 20206, 2310, 2299, 13, 50806], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13245736371289502, "compression_ratio": 1.7132867132867133, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442460658270933e-12}, {"id": 712, "seek": 243218, "start": 2441.1, "end": 2445.66, "text": " So the whole universe, space-time itself, is what Fluxian calls the persistence manifold.", "tokens": [50811, 407, 264, 1379, 6445, 11, 1901, 12, 3766, 2564, 11, 307, 437, 3235, 2449, 952, 5498, 264, 37617, 47138, 13, 51039], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13245736371289502, "compression_ratio": 1.7132867132867133, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442460658270933e-12}, {"id": 713, "seek": 243218, "start": 2445.94, "end": 2447.08, "text": " The overarching structure.", "tokens": [51053, 440, 45501, 3877, 13, 51110], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13245736371289502, "compression_ratio": 1.7132867132867133, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442460658270933e-12}, {"id": 714, "seek": 243218, "start": 2447.48, "end": 2455.66, "text": " It is the joint geometry of distinguishability, which we experience as space, an accumulated constraint, which we experience as time.", "tokens": [51130, 467, 307, 264, 7225, 18426, 295, 20206, 2310, 11, 597, 321, 1752, 382, 1901, 11, 364, 31346, 25534, 11, 597, 321, 1752, 382, 565, 13, 51539], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13245736371289502, "compression_ratio": 1.7132867132867133, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442460658270933e-12}, {"id": 715, "seek": 243218, "start": 2456.46, "end": 2460.24, "text": " And mathematics, in this view, isn't just a tool we invented.", "tokens": [51579, 400, 18666, 11, 294, 341, 1910, 11, 1943, 380, 445, 257, 2290, 321, 14479, 13, 51768], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13245736371289502, "compression_ratio": 1.7132867132867133, "no_speech_prob": 2.0442460658270933e-12}, {"id": 716, "seek": 246024, "start": 2460.24, "end": 2467.14, "text": " No. Mathematics is the pure study of these persistence invariants, totally independent of their physical realization.", "tokens": [50365, 883, 13, 15776, 37541, 307, 264, 6075, 2979, 295, 613, 37617, 33270, 1719, 11, 3879, 6695, 295, 641, 4001, 25138, 13, 50710], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 717, "seek": 246024, "start": 2467.56, "end": 2470.4799999999996, "text": " Mathematics maps the absolute limits of what can persist.", "tokens": [50731, 15776, 37541, 11317, 264, 8236, 10406, 295, 437, 393, 13233, 13, 50877], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 718, "seek": 246024, "start": 2471.2599999999998, "end": 2474.24, "text": " Space-time is the ultimate reconstructive ecology.", "tokens": [50916, 8705, 12, 3766, 307, 264, 9705, 16891, 21673, 39683, 13, 51065], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 719, "seek": 246024, "start": 2474.3599999999997, "end": 2476.66, "text": " It really elegantly ties everything together.", "tokens": [51071, 467, 534, 14459, 3627, 14039, 1203, 1214, 13, 51186], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 720, "seek": 246024, "start": 2477.08, "end": 2479.9799999999996, "text": " Which leads to my final major question on the physics side.", "tokens": [51207, 3013, 6689, 281, 452, 2572, 2563, 1168, 322, 264, 10649, 1252, 13, 51352], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 721, "seek": 246024, "start": 2480.4199999999996, "end": 2484.3799999999997, "text": " Because the implications here rewrite how we view action and reaction.", "tokens": [51374, 1436, 264, 16602, 510, 28132, 577, 321, 1910, 3069, 293, 5480, 13, 51572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 722, "seek": 246024, "start": 2484.5, "end": 2484.9799999999996, "text": " Let's hear it.", "tokens": [51578, 961, 311, 1568, 309, 13, 51602], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12905112818667763, "compression_ratio": 1.5954198473282444, "no_speech_prob": 1.5251154289117053e-12}, {"id": 723, "seek": 248498, "start": 2484.98, "end": 2493.54, "text": " If space is distinguishability and time is constrained accumulation, this implies that causality itself, cause and effect, is purely geometric.", "tokens": [50365, 759, 1901, 307, 20206, 2310, 293, 565, 307, 38901, 35647, 11, 341, 18779, 300, 3302, 1860, 2564, 11, 3082, 293, 1802, 11, 307, 17491, 33246, 13, 50793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14916783709858739, "compression_ratio": 1.5574468085106383, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891248398622102e-12}, {"id": 724, "seek": 248498, "start": 2493.88, "end": 2494.98, "text": " Let's use a classic example.", "tokens": [50810, 961, 311, 764, 257, 7230, 1365, 13, 50865], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14916783709858739, "compression_ratio": 1.5574468085106383, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891248398622102e-12}, {"id": 725, "seek": 248498, "start": 2495.2, "end": 2498.7, "text": " I throw a heavy baseball and it hits a glass window, shattering it.", "tokens": [50876, 286, 3507, 257, 4676, 14323, 293, 309, 8664, 257, 4276, 4910, 11, 402, 14849, 309, 13, 51051], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14916783709858739, "compression_ratio": 1.5574468085106383, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891248398622102e-12}, {"id": 726, "seek": 248498, "start": 2498.92, "end": 2500.36, "text": " Okay. Standard physics problem.", "tokens": [51062, 1033, 13, 21298, 10649, 1154, 13, 51134], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14916783709858739, "compression_ratio": 1.5574468085106383, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891248398622102e-12}, {"id": 727, "seek": 248498, "start": 2500.72, "end": 2504.92, "text": " Instinctively, I think the physical mass and force of the baseball violently broke the glass.", "tokens": [51152, 2730, 5460, 3413, 11, 286, 519, 264, 4001, 2758, 293, 3464, 295, 264, 14323, 46728, 6902, 264, 4276, 13, 51362], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14916783709858739, "compression_ratio": 1.5574468085106383, "no_speech_prob": 1.2891248398622102e-12}, {"id": 728, "seek": 250492, "start": 2504.92, "end": 2509.28, "text": " But under Fliction's framework, is it true that physical force isn't the root reality?", "tokens": [50365, 583, 833, 3235, 4105, 311, 8388, 11, 307, 309, 2074, 300, 4001, 3464, 1943, 380, 264, 5593, 4103, 30, 50583], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 729, "seek": 250492, "start": 2509.84, "end": 2514.62, "text": " Is a breaking window actually just the propagation of constraints through admissibility domains?", "tokens": [50611, 1119, 257, 7697, 4910, 767, 445, 264, 38377, 295, 18491, 807, 5910, 891, 2841, 25514, 30, 50850], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 730, "seek": 250492, "start": 2514.98, "end": 2515.2400000000002, "text": " Yes.", "tokens": [50868, 1079, 13, 50881], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 731, "seek": 250492, "start": 2515.86, "end": 2518.1800000000003, "text": " Causality is entirely geometric in this framework.", "tokens": [50912, 7544, 301, 1860, 307, 7696, 33246, 294, 341, 8388, 13, 51028], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 732, "seek": 250492, "start": 2518.84, "end": 2519.86, "text": " Let's break down the baseball.", "tokens": [51061, 961, 311, 1821, 760, 264, 14323, 13, 51112], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 733, "seek": 250492, "start": 2520.52, "end": 2520.84, "text": " All right.", "tokens": [51145, 1057, 558, 13, 51161], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 734, "seek": 250492, "start": 2521.1, "end": 2524.4, "text": " The baseball flying through the air is a persistence trajectory.", "tokens": [51174, 440, 14323, 7137, 807, 264, 1988, 307, 257, 37617, 21512, 13, 51339], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 735, "seek": 250492, "start": 2525.06, "end": 2529.62, "text": " It carries specific constraints, its mass, its velocity, its structural integrity.", "tokens": [51372, 467, 16402, 2685, 18491, 11, 1080, 2758, 11, 1080, 9269, 11, 1080, 15067, 16000, 13, 51600], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.20762167826737507, "compression_ratio": 1.5947955390334572, "no_speech_prob": 1.5980730194015136e-12}, {"id": 736, "seek": 252962, "start": 2529.62, "end": 2534.98, "text": " The window also has constraints, mainly the tensile strength of the glass.", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4910, 611, 575, 18491, 11, 8704, 264, 10688, 794, 3800, 295, 264, 4276, 13, 50633], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11675574562766335, "compression_ratio": 1.66798418972332, "no_speech_prob": 1.4954036273162608e-12}, {"id": 737, "seek": 252962, "start": 2535.7599999999998, "end": 2541.6, "text": " When they intersect, the baseball doesn't force the window to break in a classical Newtonian pushing sense.", "tokens": [50672, 1133, 436, 27815, 11, 264, 14323, 1177, 380, 3464, 264, 4910, 281, 1821, 294, 257, 13735, 19541, 952, 7380, 2020, 13, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11675574562766335, "compression_ratio": 1.66798418972332, "no_speech_prob": 1.4954036273162608e-12}, {"id": 738, "seek": 252962, "start": 2541.7, "end": 2542.44, "text": " What does it do then?", "tokens": [50969, 708, 775, 309, 360, 550, 30, 51006], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11675574562766335, "compression_ratio": 1.66798418972332, "no_speech_prob": 1.4954036273162608e-12}, {"id": 739, "seek": 252962, "start": 2542.7, "end": 2548.04, "text": " The constraints of the baseball's trajectory alter the mathematical admissibility domain of the window's distinctions.", "tokens": [51019, 440, 18491, 295, 264, 14323, 311, 21512, 11337, 264, 18894, 5910, 891, 2841, 9274, 295, 264, 4910, 311, 1483, 49798, 13, 51286], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11675574562766335, "compression_ratio": 1.66798418972332, "no_speech_prob": 1.4954036273162608e-12}, {"id": 740, "seek": 252962, "start": 2548.3599999999997, "end": 2553.22, "text": " It changes the rules of what is allowed to exist in that specific region of space-time.", "tokens": [51302, 467, 2962, 264, 4474, 295, 437, 307, 4350, 281, 2514, 294, 300, 2685, 4458, 295, 1901, 12, 3766, 13, 51545], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11675574562766335, "compression_ratio": 1.66798418972332, "no_speech_prob": 1.4954036273162608e-12}, {"id": 741, "seek": 252962, "start": 2553.42, "end": 2553.98, "text": " Precisely.", "tokens": [51555, 48746, 736, 13, 51583], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11675574562766335, "compression_ratio": 1.66798418972332, "no_speech_prob": 1.4954036273162608e-12}, {"id": 742, "seek": 255398, "start": 2553.98, "end": 2559.14, "text": " The window shatters because its previous structural distinctions, being a solid, flat sheet of glass,", "tokens": [50365, 440, 4910, 402, 37690, 570, 1080, 3894, 15067, 1483, 49798, 11, 885, 257, 5100, 11, 4962, 8193, 295, 4276, 11, 50623], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 743, "seek": 255398, "start": 2559.34, "end": 2565.12, "text": " are literally no longer admissible under the new, overwhelming constraints introduced by the arrival of the baseball.", "tokens": [50633, 366, 3736, 572, 2854, 5910, 41073, 833, 264, 777, 11, 13373, 18491, 7268, 538, 264, 18365, 295, 264, 14323, 13, 50922], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 744, "seek": 255398, "start": 2565.3, "end": 2565.6, "text": " Wow.", "tokens": [50931, 3153, 13, 50946], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 745, "seek": 255398, "start": 2565.8, "end": 2569.32, "text": " The shattered glass is the only continuation that the universe will permit.", "tokens": [50956, 440, 35209, 4276, 307, 264, 787, 29357, 300, 264, 6445, 486, 13423, 13, 51132], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 746, "seek": 255398, "start": 2570.16, "end": 2574.04, "text": " Causality is just the propagation of constraint through the persistence manifold.", "tokens": [51174, 7544, 301, 1860, 307, 445, 264, 38377, 295, 25534, 807, 264, 37617, 47138, 13, 51368], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 747, "seek": 255398, "start": 2574.56, "end": 2579.16, "text": " It is all one unified, geometric structure of recoverable distinction.", "tokens": [51394, 467, 307, 439, 472, 26787, 11, 33246, 3877, 295, 8114, 712, 16844, 13, 51624], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 748, "seek": 255398, "start": 2579.52, "end": 2583.22, "text": " We've gone from ancient DNA to the geometry of cause and effect.", "tokens": [51642, 492, 600, 2780, 490, 7832, 8272, 281, 264, 18426, 295, 3082, 293, 1802, 13, 51827], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1745032753263201, "compression_ratio": 1.6549520766773163, "no_speech_prob": 2.0359664475166905e-12}, {"id": 749, "seek": 258322, "start": 2583.22, "end": 2586.8599999999997, "text": " And I think my understanding of reality has been fundamentally rewired.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 286, 519, 452, 3701, 295, 4103, 575, 668, 17879, 319, 86, 1824, 13, 50547], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 750, "seek": 258322, "start": 2587.4199999999996, "end": 2592.64, "text": " But we are reaching the end of our time here, which means we need to wrap up this incredibly deep dive.", "tokens": [50575, 583, 321, 366, 9906, 264, 917, 295, 527, 565, 510, 11, 597, 1355, 321, 643, 281, 7019, 493, 341, 6252, 2452, 9192, 13, 50836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 751, "seek": 258322, "start": 2592.72, "end": 2593.8399999999997, "text": " It's been a lot to process.", "tokens": [50840, 467, 311, 668, 257, 688, 281, 1399, 13, 50896], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 752, "seek": 258322, "start": 2594.06, "end": 2595.52, "text": " Let's recap the journey we've taken.", "tokens": [50907, 961, 311, 20928, 264, 4671, 321, 600, 2726, 13, 50980], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 753, "seek": 258322, "start": 2596.2, "end": 2601.56, "text": " We started by shedding the comfortable illusion that the universe is made of static, solid objects.", "tokens": [51014, 492, 1409, 538, 49934, 264, 4619, 18854, 300, 264, 6445, 307, 1027, 295, 13437, 11, 5100, 6565, 13, 51282], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 754, "seek": 258322, "start": 2602.0, "end": 2606.4399999999996, "text": " We learned to view reality as a boiling ocean of relentless transformation.", "tokens": [51304, 492, 3264, 281, 1910, 4103, 382, 257, 16208, 7810, 295, 46136, 9887, 13, 51526], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 755, "seek": 258322, "start": 2606.68, "end": 2608.02, "text": " The washing machine of the universe.", "tokens": [51538, 440, 13836, 3479, 295, 264, 6445, 13, 51605], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 756, "seek": 258322, "start": 2608.2799999999997, "end": 2608.6, "text": " Exactly.", "tokens": [51618, 7587, 13, 51634], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14091065100261144, "compression_ratio": 1.6210526315789473, "no_speech_prob": 1.958290734432877e-12}, {"id": 757, "seek": 260860, "start": 2608.6, "end": 2617.16, "text": " We saw how active repair and memory acting as constraints on reconstruction are the only forces saving distinctions from the decay of entropy.", "tokens": [50365, 492, 1866, 577, 4967, 10535, 293, 4675, 6577, 382, 18491, 322, 31565, 366, 264, 787, 5874, 6816, 1483, 49798, 490, 264, 21039, 295, 30867, 13, 50793], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11558740566938351, "compression_ratio": 1.6550218340611353, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858858280412558e-12}, {"id": 758, "seek": 260860, "start": 2617.7, "end": 2621.3399999999997, "text": " We explored how explanations act as global repair operators.", "tokens": [50820, 492, 24016, 577, 28708, 605, 382, 4338, 10535, 19077, 13, 51002], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11558740566938351, "compression_ratio": 1.6550218340611353, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858858280412558e-12}, {"id": 759, "seek": 260860, "start": 2621.56, "end": 2624.3399999999997, "text": " Moving from scattered traces to stable attractors.", "tokens": [51013, 14242, 490, 21986, 26076, 281, 8351, 5049, 830, 13, 51152], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11558740566938351, "compression_ratio": 1.6550218340611353, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858858280412558e-12}, {"id": 760, "seek": 260860, "start": 2624.38, "end": 2630.22, "text": " And we climbed the epistemic ladder from raw information up to the governance of wisdom and the ultimate alignment of truth.", "tokens": [51154, 400, 321, 28691, 264, 2388, 468, 3438, 18325, 490, 8936, 1589, 493, 281, 264, 17449, 295, 10712, 293, 264, 9705, 18515, 295, 3494, 13, 51446], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11558740566938351, "compression_ratio": 1.6550218340611353, "no_speech_prob": 1.5858858280412558e-12}, {"id": 761, "seek": 263022, "start": 2630.22, "end": 2638.18, "text": " And finally, we saw how existence itself is just persistent admissibility within the unfolding geometry of space-time.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 2721, 11, 321, 1866, 577, 9123, 2564, 307, 445, 24315, 5910, 891, 2841, 1951, 264, 44586, 18426, 295, 1901, 12, 3766, 13, 50763], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17974775048750866, "compression_ratio": 1.5530973451327434, "no_speech_prob": 1.846849496250913e-12}, {"id": 762, "seek": 263022, "start": 2638.18, "end": 2641.52, "text": " It is a framework that forces a profound realization.", "tokens": [50763, 467, 307, 257, 8388, 300, 5874, 257, 14382, 25138, 13, 50930], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17974775048750866, "compression_ratio": 1.5530973451327434, "no_speech_prob": 1.846849496250913e-12}, {"id": 763, "seek": 263022, "start": 2642.2599999999998, "end": 2643.3599999999997, "text": " Nothing is passive.", "tokens": [50967, 6693, 307, 14975, 13, 51022], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17974775048750866, "compression_ratio": 1.5530973451327434, "no_speech_prob": 1.846849496250913e-12}, {"id": 764, "seek": 263022, "start": 2643.9199999999996, "end": 2651.52, "text": " Everything that exists, from a stone to a civilization, is actively participating in its own ongoing reconstruction.", "tokens": [51050, 5471, 300, 8198, 11, 490, 257, 7581, 281, 257, 18036, 11, 307, 13022, 13950, 294, 1080, 1065, 10452, 31565, 13, 51430], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17974775048750866, "compression_ratio": 1.5530973451327434, "no_speech_prob": 1.846849496250913e-12}, {"id": 765, "seek": 263022, "start": 2652.48, "end": 2654.8199999999997, "text": " Existence is an act of relentless effort.", "tokens": [51478, 2111, 468, 655, 307, 364, 605, 295, 46136, 4630, 13, 51595], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17974775048750866, "compression_ratio": 1.5530973451327434, "no_speech_prob": 1.846849496250913e-12}, {"id": 766, "seek": 265482, "start": 2654.82, "end": 2663.6400000000003, "text": " And that connects directly to you, the listener, how you learn a new skill, how you reconstruct the memories of your childhood, how you build an understanding of your life.", "tokens": [50365, 400, 300, 16967, 3838, 281, 291, 11, 264, 31569, 11, 577, 291, 1466, 257, 777, 5389, 11, 577, 291, 31499, 264, 8495, 295, 428, 9278, 11, 577, 291, 1322, 364, 3701, 295, 428, 993, 13, 50806], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10017043352127075, "compression_ratio": 1.645631067961165, "no_speech_prob": 1.958467025706123e-12}, {"id": 767, "seek": 265482, "start": 2664.04, "end": 2667.5800000000004, "text": " None of it is just passively storing facts on a biological hard drive.", "tokens": [50826, 14492, 295, 309, 307, 445, 1320, 3413, 26085, 9130, 322, 257, 13910, 1152, 3332, 13, 51003], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10017043352127075, "compression_ratio": 1.645631067961165, "no_speech_prob": 1.958467025706123e-12}, {"id": 768, "seek": 265482, "start": 2667.7000000000003, "end": 2668.8, "text": " It's an act of process.", "tokens": [51009, 467, 311, 364, 605, 295, 1399, 13, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10017043352127075, "compression_ratio": 1.645631067961165, "no_speech_prob": 1.958467025706123e-12}, {"id": 769, "seek": 265482, "start": 2669.1400000000003, "end": 2673.1800000000003, "text": " You are performing an act of reconstructive repair every single second.", "tokens": [51081, 509, 366, 10205, 364, 605, 295, 16891, 21673, 10535, 633, 2167, 1150, 13, 51283], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10017043352127075, "compression_ratio": 1.645631067961165, "no_speech_prob": 1.958467025706123e-12}, {"id": 770, "seek": 267318, "start": 2673.18, "end": 2682.2999999999997, "text": " You are actively building persistence fields in your own mind, fighting back against the noise, trying to find stable alignment with a chaotic world.", "tokens": [50365, 509, 366, 13022, 2390, 37617, 7909, 294, 428, 1065, 1575, 11, 5237, 646, 1970, 264, 5658, 11, 1382, 281, 915, 8351, 18515, 365, 257, 27013, 1002, 13, 50821], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10148069675152119, "compression_ratio": 1.535, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491463363839775e-12}, {"id": 771, "seek": 267318, "start": 2682.46, "end": 2688.14, "text": " You are, quite literally, a localized persistence attractor within the manifold of reality.", "tokens": [50829, 509, 366, 11, 1596, 3736, 11, 257, 44574, 37617, 5049, 284, 1951, 264, 47138, 295, 4103, 13, 51113], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10148069675152119, "compression_ratio": 1.535, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491463363839775e-12}, {"id": 772, "seek": 267318, "start": 2688.3199999999997, "end": 2691.2599999999998, "text": " Which brings me to one final lingering thought to leave you with.", "tokens": [51122, 3013, 5607, 385, 281, 472, 2572, 49542, 1194, 281, 1856, 291, 365, 13, 51269], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10148069675152119, "compression_ratio": 1.535, "no_speech_prob": 1.5491463363839775e-12}, {"id": 773, "seek": 269126, "start": 2691.26, "end": 2707.2400000000002, "text": " If affliction's math is right, if existence is merely persistent admissibility within a set of constraints, and reality is just whatever pushes back and refuses our reconstructions, what happens to our own identity as human beings when our technology begins to fundamentally alter those constraints?", "tokens": [50365, 759, 2096, 75, 4105, 311, 5221, 307, 558, 11, 498, 9123, 307, 17003, 24315, 5910, 891, 2841, 1951, 257, 992, 295, 18491, 11, 293, 4103, 307, 445, 2035, 21020, 646, 293, 33222, 527, 31499, 626, 11, 437, 2314, 281, 527, 1065, 6575, 382, 1952, 8958, 562, 527, 2899, 7338, 281, 17879, 11337, 729, 18491, 30, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06173664993709988, "compression_ratio": 1.5810810810810811, "no_speech_prob": 1.9968928854224854e-12}, {"id": 774, "seek": 269126, "start": 2707.6400000000003, "end": 2710.32, "text": " It is the existential question of the 21st century.", "tokens": [51184, 467, 307, 264, 37133, 1168, 295, 264, 5080, 372, 4901, 13, 51318], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.06173664993709988, "compression_ratio": 1.5810810810810811, "no_speech_prob": 1.9968928854224854e-12}, {"id": 775, "seek": 271032, "start": 2710.32, "end": 2723.94, "text": " I mean, as we develop advanced artificial intelligence capable of mapping multidimensional biological states, as we invent cellular repair mechanisms, as we build neural interfaces that can directly edit the traces of our memory...", "tokens": [50365, 286, 914, 11, 382, 321, 1499, 7339, 11677, 7599, 8189, 295, 18350, 2120, 327, 332, 11075, 13910, 4368, 11, 382, 321, 7962, 29267, 10535, 15902, 11, 382, 321, 1322, 18161, 28416, 300, 393, 3838, 8129, 264, 26076, 295, 527, 4675, 485, 51046], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11251417490152213, "compression_ratio": 1.6883561643835616, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362743609336764e-12}, {"id": 776, "seek": 271032, "start": 2723.94, "end": 2725.8, "text": " We aren't just making tools anymore.", "tokens": [51046, 492, 3212, 380, 445, 1455, 3873, 3602, 13, 51139], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11251417490152213, "compression_ratio": 1.6883561643835616, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362743609336764e-12}, {"id": 777, "seek": 271032, "start": 2725.96, "end": 2726.26, "text": " No.", "tokens": [51147, 883, 13, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11251417490152213, "compression_ratio": 1.6883561643835616, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362743609336764e-12}, {"id": 778, "seek": 271032, "start": 2726.84, "end": 2729.92, "text": " We are changing the underlying constraints of the universe.", "tokens": [51191, 492, 366, 4473, 264, 14217, 18491, 295, 264, 6445, 13, 51345], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11251417490152213, "compression_ratio": 1.6883561643835616, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362743609336764e-12}, {"id": 779, "seek": 271032, "start": 2730.6800000000003, "end": 2734.28, "text": " And if we change the constraints, we fundamentally change what is admissible.", "tokens": [51383, 400, 498, 321, 1319, 264, 18491, 11, 321, 17879, 1319, 437, 307, 5910, 41073, 13, 51563], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11251417490152213, "compression_ratio": 1.6883561643835616, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362743609336764e-12}, {"id": 780, "seek": 271032, "start": 2735.1400000000003, "end": 2739.38, "text": " Are we about to reconstruct ourselves into an entirely new dimension of existence?", "tokens": [51606, 2014, 321, 466, 281, 31499, 4175, 666, 364, 7696, 777, 10139, 295, 9123, 30, 51818], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11251417490152213, "compression_ratio": 1.6883561643835616, "no_speech_prob": 2.0362743609336764e-12}, {"id": 781, "seek": 273938, "start": 2739.38, "end": 2740.56, "text": " It's very possible.", "tokens": [50365, 467, 311, 588, 1944, 13, 50424], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12613729151283823, "compression_ratio": 1.599406528189911, "no_speech_prob": 1.9585125621973676e-12}, {"id": 782, "seek": 273938, "start": 2740.86, "end": 2745.96, "text": " Will the specific structural distinctions that make us human even remain recoverable a thousand years from now?", "tokens": [50439, 3099, 264, 2685, 15067, 1483, 49798, 300, 652, 505, 1952, 754, 6222, 8114, 712, 257, 4714, 924, 490, 586, 30, 50694], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12613729151283823, "compression_ratio": 1.599406528189911, "no_speech_prob": 1.9585125621973676e-12}, {"id": 783, "seek": 273938, "start": 2746.26, "end": 2749.7000000000003, "text": " Or will they shatter under the transformation of our own technology?", "tokens": [50709, 1610, 486, 436, 402, 1161, 833, 264, 9887, 295, 527, 1065, 2899, 30, 50881], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12613729151283823, "compression_ratio": 1.599406528189911, "no_speech_prob": 1.9585125621973676e-12}, {"id": 784, "seek": 273938, "start": 2750.6800000000003, "end": 2756.78, "text": " It is something to seriously think about the next time you look at the coffee cup on your desk and assume it's just a solid, simple object.", "tokens": [50930, 467, 307, 746, 281, 6638, 519, 466, 264, 958, 565, 291, 574, 412, 264, 4982, 4414, 322, 428, 10026, 293, 6552, 309, 311, 445, 257, 5100, 11, 2199, 2657, 13, 51235], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.126137291512838